en</li>\n<li>Familiarity with Photoshop or at least one photo editing software</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Education</strong>: Undergraduates and graduates working toward a degree in marketing, communications, business, or related field.</p>\n<p><strong>Timing</strong>: Mid-January to end May 2014, 15-20 hours per week.</p>\n<p><strong>Compensation:</strong>Paid intern. Additionally, you will gain invaluable experience working with a leading travel company and understanding the digital marketing space. You will have the opportunity to lead in a collaborative environment and fully engage in the launch of online promotional campaigns.</p>\n <p><span ><em><strong>If interested, please upload&nbsp;resume and cover letter together in one pdf/word file.&nbsp;</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><em><strong>Please indicate "Apply Bilingual Marketing Intern 2014" in the subject line.</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>*Must have appropriate visas and work authority in U.S.</em></p>', '', 'jobs@studentuniverse.com', 5, 163, 2),
