(170, 1392707797, '', 'app', 'Technology', 'Beijing, China', 'China', 'Beijing', 'Beijing', 39.904030, 116.407524, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>app5 3Android SDK</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>The Role</strong><br /> We are actively searching for a Senior Android Developer to be at the cutting edge of internet tech as App Annie brings data analytics to Android. You will play a key role in shaping the experiences of millions of app publishers as you work directly with our game changing engineers while drawing on the resources of our product and marketing teams.</p>\n<p><strong>Your responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Act as &lsquo;Go-to&rsquo; Senior Developer for Android platform related projects</li>\n<li>In charge of the full development process of mobile apps</li>\n<li>Work with UI/UX Designer and develop user interface according to customer requirements and storyboards</li>\n<li>Develop standards, repeatable processes and reusable components</li>\n<li>Participate in project planning, including the development of timelines and resources required</li>\n<li>Work with the development team throughout all phases of the project, including requirements validation, detail design and implementation</li>\n<li>Collaborate as part of a diverse team in development, product planning, product verification and documentation to deliver high quality, complete product releases</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>You</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A bachelor''s degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience</li>\n<li>A passion for mobile device technologies, especially Android</li>\n<li>5+ years of software development experience</li>\n<li>3+ years hands on the Android SDK</li>\n<li>Thorough understanding of both client and web application architectures (AJAX, HTML, JavaScript, CSS)</li>\n<li>Good understanding of backend system, scalable and highly available architecture</li>\n<li>Experience in working with a code management system (Git, SVN)</li>\n<li>Management experience is a plus</li>\n<li>Good level of English to communicate in an international environment</li>\n<li>Should be excited about exponential growth opportunities at a successful start-up</li>\n</ul>', 'http://appannie.theresumator.com/apply/eHXt45/Senior-Android-Engineer.html?source=Linkedin', '', 5, 56, 2),
(171, 1392708125, '', 'Panda Express', 'Resturant', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="jobDescription mb20">\n<p>Panda Express45K+bonus5&nbsp;--</p>\n<p><strong>Restaurant Management Team responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lead all or some People aspects of a Panda Express restaurant including hiring, training, coaching, and development</li>\n<li>Ensure the safety of our Guests and Associates through training and execution of food safety and restaurant safety standards and guidelines</li>\n<li>Lead all or some Guest components of a Panda Express restaurant including excellent food quality, guest service, associate friendliness, and restaurant cleanliness through your team using proven systems and routines</li>\n<li>Lead all or some financial areas of a Panda Express restaurant including sales growth, cost management, and profit growth</li>\n<li>Applies thorough knowledge of all policies, procedures and practices utilized within unit managed</li>\n<li>Understands ways in which unit relates to and impacts PRG</li>\n<li>Demonstrates knowledge of PRG operations and objectives</li>\n<li>Seeks information regarding trends affecting food service industry</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>We offer our Full-Time Management Team:</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>Progressive Compensation Package and Excellent Bonus Opportunity</li>\n<li>5 or more Weeks of Comprehensive Training to prepare you for success</li>\n<li>On-Going Career &amp; Leadership Development</li>\n<li>Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance</li>\n<li>401 K with Company Match</li>\n<li>Paid Time Off and Paid Holidays</li>\n<li>Associate Discounts (Panda Express, Hibachi San, Panda Inn plus Theme Parks) and free meals when you work</li>\n<li>Lucrative Associate Referral Bonus</li>\n<li>Pre-Tax Dependent Care Flexible Spending Account</li>\n<li>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n</li>\n<li>College degree or equivalent experience preferred</li>\n<li>High school or GED required</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Additional expectations of our Management Team are:</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>Excellent leaders with great people skills</li>\n<li>Proactive &ndash; Sees life as choices and chooses to make a positive impact.</li>\n<li>People Oriented &ndash; enjoys working with our guests and associates, possess good communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n<li>Growth Oriented &ndash; knows that learning and growth are keys to personal and professional success and is willing and able to share learning with others.</li>\n<li>Results Oriented &ndash; focuses on getting results without compromising guest, people, and financial areas.</li>\n<li><strong>ADA Statement: While performing duties, counter areas are often hot with steam from steam table and food vapors. Work space is restricted and employees are expected to remain standing for long periods of time. Employees must prepare hot and cold foods, use Chinese cook knife and other kitchen equipment and work quickly without losing accuracy. Employees may be required to lift up to 50 lbs., stand up to four hours and reach across counter tops measured at 36 inches to serve customers. Kitchens are hot and noise levels are usually high; storage space is limited and shelving is high</strong></li>\n<li>Panda Restaurant Group, Inc is an Equal Opportunity Employer</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>', 'https://www.ziprecruiter.com/job/Now-Hiring-Managers-45k-Plus-Bonus-New-College-Grads-Welcome/4dd8cf63/?source=cpc-collegerecruiter', '', 5, 153, 2),
