(220, 1393871383, 'Software Development Engineer in Testing', 'Microsoft', 'Technology', 'Shenzhen, Guangdong, China', 'China', 'Guangdong', 'Shenzhen', 22.543098, 114.057869, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Division: </strong>Information Solutions</p>\n<p><strong>Title:</strong> Software Development Engineer in Testing</p>\n<p><strong>Location:</strong>&nbsp; Microsoft Asia Center for Hardware (MACH), Nan Shan Hi-tech Park, Shenzhen, China</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p>\n<p>Once in a generation our world of computing goes through an industry shaping transformation. The personal computer, client server solutions and the World Wide Web are the last few examples. We stand now on the edge of the next great transformation with the combination of Big Data and Cloud Computing. The company that can offer a trusted, reliable and high scale platform for the new class of applications in this new era of computing will win the hearts and minds of customers. We are building this platform.</p>\n<p>Information Solutions integrates world-class IT business solutions across enterprises, enabling our supply chain and driving flawless business performance. We partner closely with internal and external stakeholders to envision and implement advanced capabilities spanning the business lifecycle, from product design and marketing through manufacturing and supply chain to consumer service.</p>\n<p>Information Solutions China consists of engineer and support team now. Engineer team focuses on Business Intelligence (BI), and works with Redmond team to deliver world class BI. We are proud to showcase Microsoft&rsquo;s platform and application technologies in the High Tech Industry, empowering our clients with trustworthy information management and decision support. We are energetic and deep passion for our customer and technology. We love work and challenge!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you are interested in shipping millions of products, multiple software releases a year and are up for the challenge of bridging the gaps among three geographic locations, this is the job for you.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Position Description:</strong></p>\n<p>As a member of the MSCIS service transition team, you&rsquo;ll drive the supportability and manageability of our applications, guiding the product team through the release and deployment phase and help ensure the readiness of our Production Support team. You will interact with program and solutions management, development, and test to ensure we deliver quality applications that meet our customer requirements. You&rsquo;ll play a key role throughout the product development cycle, collaborating on designs, features, and driving quality requirements and ensuring the product is ready for a high-availability production environment. You&rsquo;ll design, develop and own appropriate monitoring solutions and provide Tier 3 Production Support.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications Include:</strong></p>\n<p>To qualify for this position, you must possess strong communication, organizational, and technical writing skills. You must function well in a fast-paced collaborative environment and be able to apply critical thinking and problem solving skills to complex production environment scenarios to ensure high availability. You will be able to demonstrate your strong troubleshooting and analytical skills through architecture and design discussions across technologies, through critical escalation support, and by mentoring others in your ownership area.</p>\n<p>Promising fresh graduates and students in the final year with adequate development experience in SQL Server are also welcomed to apply for this opening.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements Include:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Well experienced with BI. &nbsp;Minimum 2 years of demonstrated work experience in development/test related role in BI systems</li>\n<li>Expert of SQL &amp; backend Database</li>\n<li>Hands on Experience with C#, .NET</li>\n<li>Prior experience of EIP, SAMBI is preferred</li>\n<li>Knowledge of ATTD, CI, CD is highly desirable</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of VSTF &amp; TFS is required</li>\n<li>Good understanding of Microsoft Test Manager and Agile Methodology</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Design Patterns &amp; Performance Testing</li>\n<li>Troubleshooting skills for Build &amp; Deployment experience is desired</li>\n<li>Cross regional collaboration with Test Leads would be required for this role</li>\n<li>Good team player and willing to step up to team activities and requirements</li>\n<li>Sense of Accountability &amp; Fast learning aptitude is must for this role</li>\n</ul>', '', 'v-irwu@microsoft.com', 5, 74, 2),
(221, 1393872915, '', ' ()', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>2014 Summer Training Program</p>\n<p>Job Description:</p>\n<p>This is a four-week program designed to engage you in the day-to-day activities in our business units including Sales and Trading, Investment Banking, Research, Compliance and Financial Control. The program starts with an orientation and training where you will learn about the operations of CICC, as well as relevant business skills. You will also receive division-specific training designed to help you gain comprehensive understanding of the finance industry.</p>\n<p>After the training period, you will be assigned to work with financial professionals on a variety of projects. During the program, you will gain exposure to different aspects of industry. Successful Summer Interns may be invited back to join our Summer Analyst program next year, which is designed to prepare you for our full time position.</p>\n<p>Requirement:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Class of 2016, 2017 undergraduates from reputable universities;</li>\n<li>Strong passion for financial service industry;</li>\n<li>Excellent academic performance;</li>\n<li>Strong Analytical and leaning ability;</li>\n<li>Studious and able to work under pressure;</li>\n<li>Bilingual proficiency in English and Mandarin;</li>\n<li>Effective communicator and strong self-starter;</li>\n<li>Excellent interpersonal skills, integrating tact and diplomacy;</li>\n<li>Self-confident and energetic.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Location: New York</p>', '', 'zeyu.zhou@ciccus.com', 5, 743, 2),
