(224, 1393916111, 'Mobile Application Developer', 'SteadyRain', 'Technology', 'St. Louis, MO, United States', 'United States', 'Missouri', 'St Louis', 38.627003, -90.199402, '', '', '', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<h2>Mobile Application Developer</h2>\n<h3>Research &amp;&nbsp;Development<br />Full Time</h3>\n<p>Are you interested in taking your Mobile Development skills to the next level? SteadyRain is seeking a mobile application developer with a minimum of one (1) year of experience, professionally or recreationally, in the mobile technology field.</p>\n<p>This individual will support SteadyRain&rsquo;s Mobile Development Team and must possess the ability to analyze, research, and develop mobile applications using iOS and/or Android platforms. This position reports to SteadyRain''s Director of Mobile Technology.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with iOS and/or Android</li>\n<li>1 year or more of experience in mobile application development and/or web application development</li>\n<li>Fundamentals in object-oriented design, data structures, problem solving, and business requirements analysis</li>\n<li>Proficiency in at least one modern object-oriented language such as Objective C, C++, Java or C#</li>\n<li>Exceptional analytical aptitude and attention to detail</li>\n<li>Team player who is self-motivated and well organized</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Additional Preferred Skills:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Familiarity with mobile frameworks and libraries</li>\n<li>Familiarity with JSON, jQuery, REST and XML based web services</li>\n<li>Knowledge of hybrid mobile web frameworks such as Appcelerator, Xamarin or Cordova</li>\n<li>Experience working with web-browser DOM using JavaScript, AJAX and CSS</li>\n<li>Experience building iOS/Android apps that have been successfully delivered to customers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Full Time</li>\n<li>Paid Time Off &amp; Vacation</li>\n<li>Matching 401k Plan</li>\n<li>100% Coverag