(266, 1395207275, 'Energy Efficiency/Clean Energy Specialist, China Program', 'Environmental Defense Fund', 'Consulting', '', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>With world attention focused on both the environment and the economy, Environmental Defense Fund (EDF) is where policymakers and business leaders turn for win-win solutions. This leading green group, with programs from Boston to Beijing, has tripled in size over the past decade by focusing on strong science, uncommon partnerships and market-based approaches. You can be part of a vibrant workplace that welcomes diverse perspectives, talents and contributions, where innovation and a focus on results are a way of life.</p>\n<p>China Program</p>\n<p>China has experienced unprecedented economic growth over the past 30 years &ndash; but with rapid economic growth has come huge environmental problems. China is now the world''s leading greenhouse gas emitter. In 1996, EDF launched projects designed to cut sulfur dioxide pollution from power plants in several of China''s cities and provinces using economic incentives. Since that time, EDF''s program has grown and the office is expanding. EDF''s current goals are to help China bend the upward trajectory of its greenhouse gas emissions while addressing major health issues and lifting large numbers of rural Chinese out of poverty. To this end, in collaboration with the Chinese government, industries and individuals, our work focuses on three major initiatives: establish an effective system for managing greenhouse gas emissions that includes a rigorous cap on carbon emissions implemented through emissions trading systems, potentially combined with taxes, subsidies, command-and-control policies; accelerate renewables and other cleaner alternatives to coal; and slow the growth of energy demand, which can be achieved by finding ways to green the supply chain and promote energy efficiency, demand-side management and low-carbon urban development. <br />Overall Function</p>\n<p>Under the direction and supervision of the Deputy Director based in New York, the Energy Efficiency/Clean Energy Specialist supports the China Program in the design, development, implementation and expansion of a climate corps initiative in China. The initiative aims to reduce the environmental and climate impacts of products and services through corporate partnerships, generate business benefits for corporate partners, and create new industry-wide best practices in the adoption and utilization of innovative energy efficiency and clean technologies. He/she will also be responsible for assisting the Vice President and other non-mandarin speakers in the team to effectively communicate with Chinese contacts when necessary. <br />Key Responsibilities</p>\n<p>Together with the China Program team and in collaboration with EDF&rsquo;s U.S. climate corps team, design, develop, implement and expand a climate corps initiative in China.</p>\n<p>Localize, develop and oversee administration of toolkits for climate corps initiative in China referencing U.S. model.</p>\n<p>Help identify, recruit and train climate corps fellow candiates and develop relationships with universities and research institutes.</p>\n<p>Coordinate and execute training programs for climate corps fellows.</p>\n<p>Help identify and develop relationships with companies with the aim of gathering information, developing project ideas, and recruiting partners.</p>\n<p>Manage and support corporate partnerships by developing workplans, negotiating project agreements and scopes of work, ensuring timely and high-quality deliverables.</p>\n<p>In collaboration with the team, deliver high quality fellowship experiences for hosts and fellows.</p>\n<p>Develop appropriate indicators for evaluating project success.</p>\n<p>Support cross-pollination with other China Program&rsquo;s initaitives including greening supply chain, public procurement and carbon emissions trading.</p>\n<p>Communicate project goals, progress and achievements to internal and external constituenties through reports, presentations, public outreach and other methods.</p>\n<p>Support fundraising and prepration of grant propoals.</p>\n<p>Translation</p>\n<p>Translate research reports, speeches, and presentations between English and Chinese as needed.</p>\n<p>Provide general and technical interpretation to facilitate communications between U.S. and Chinese partners as needed.</p>\n<p>Qualifications</p>\n<p>Master''s degree in environment management, environmental policy, economics, or business administration. Knowledge of China''s environmental and energy policies a strong plus.</p>\n<p>Solid understanding of energy and environmental issues in business operation and supply chain management. Prior experience working on energy/environmental issues in a business context strongly preferred.</p>\n<p>Experience in project management; well organized and detail- oriented.</p>\n<p>Working knowledge of the current theory and practice of corporate sustainability.</p>\n<p>Broad understanding in climate, environmental and energy issues.</p>\n<p>Ability to multi-task, prioritize and meet deadlines.</p>\n<p>Highly proficient in MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and statistical software applications.</p>\n<p>Excellent written and oral communication skills in both English and Mandarin.</p>\n<p>Location <br />This position will be located in our New York, NY office.</p>\n<p>Due to the volume of employment applications and queries received, EDF is unable to respond to each application individually. Applicants will be contacted directly if selected as a candidate.</p>\n<p>Environmental Defense Fund is an Equal Opportunity Employer <br />Environmental Defense Fund - 1 day ago - save job - block</p>', 'http://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?k=Job&c=q339VfwU&j=oWcyYfwo', '', 5, 85, 2),
(267, 1395207699, '', '', 'Marketing', '', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Position Summary:</strong></p>\n<p>The Associate Specialist is primarily responsible for cataloguing and preparing consigned property for online sale channel, with responsibility for auction when required. In addition, this position works closely under the supervision of senior specialist colleagues to develop increased responsibility in the production of appraisals and proposals, increased knowledge of domestic client relationship management, and relevant markets for the art category, and increased negotiating and selling skills.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibility Data:</strong></p>\n<p>Research property including authenticity, bibliography, provenance and exhibition history<br />Catalogue property for online sales.<br />Prepare condition reports of consigned property prior to sale.<br />Prepare property for hilling sessions with the HoD (meetings to determine value, condition and marketability of property) and amend catalogue sheets after hilling sessions<br />Review incoming photo inquiries with senior specialist or department head to determine online sale potential.<br />Work with all client categories (collectors, dealers, corporations, institutions) in the areas of business-getting and selling, under the supervision of more senior specialist or department head.<br />Work with the Trusts, Estates &amp; Appraisals department on appraisals as a means of generating new business opportunities and in conjunction with the CWOA department.<br />Work closely with the HoD, other specialists and business getters on what to offer in online sale.<br />Work closely with the ecommerce admin.<br />Support the CWOA specialist team whenever there is no online sale scheduled:<br />Participate in CWOA catalogue production and layout process.<br />Prepare condition reports of consigned property prior to the CWOA auction sales.<br />Participate in CWOA pre-sale exhibition set-up.<br />Assist CWOA clients in the galleries during Asian sale week.<br />Participate in Telephone Bidding with clients during the CWOA auction.<br />View and visit competitors&rsquo; auctions and track overall results.<br />Actively participate in events, art fairs, and other functions to represent Christie&rsquo;s.<br />Serve as primary liaison with outside experts.<br />Other duties as assigned by Manager.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills and Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent work experience in applicable Art History or Decorative Arts category; M.A preferred.<br />Minimum of 4 years paid work experience in related field; or 2 years as a Junior Specialist.<br />Knowledge of the auction business.<br />Demonstrated ability in appraising property and business-getting.<br />Knowledge of E-mail, Spreadsheet, Word Processing and Presentation software (Microsoft Office preferred).<br />Ability to learn Christie&rsquo;s systems including Siebel, Property System, intranet and website.<br />Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, including superior written and spoken communication.<br />Superior client service skills.<br />Demonstrated ability to multi-task and prioritize.<br />Strong follow-up skills with attention to detail.<br />Ability to work within a team environment</p>\n<p><strong>Working Conditions:</strong></p>\n<p>Work is performed in an office setting, and off-site in various client settings (private, corporate and institution.)<br />Noise level in the office work environment is moderate, will vary for external locations.</p>\n<p><strong>Physical Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>Required to handle, inspect and/or take photographs of works of art for appraisal and consignment<br />Required to create written or recorded descriptions of inspected items<br />Required to attend events, exhibitions, art fairs locally, domestically and internationally<br />Required to meet with clients on-site and off-site<br />Required to travel as needed (local, domestic and international)<br />Tools and Equipment Used:</p>\n<p>Basic office equipment including personal computer, copy machine, fax machine, scanner; office supplies</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.christies.com/about/careers/lumesse/details.aspx?nPostingId=964&nPostingTargetId=1520&id=QJVFK026203F3VBQBV77968OB&lg=UK', '', 5, 71, 2),
(269, 1395272419, '', 'International aviation corporation', 'Engineering', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p >International aviation corporation is look for Full Time Aviation Spares Buyer to begin immediately at our New York City office.</p>\n <p >Primary responsibility is to support Purchasing Departments with critical part requirements to fulfill variable demands that impact the operation of airlines. The Buyer works closely with Engineering, Repair, and Inventory Planning sourcing aircraft parts, initiating purchase orders, expediting existing orders and coordinating logistics to meet immediate needs as well as long term requirements.</p>\n <p >Duties and Responsibilities include but are not limited to:<br />- Place purchase and repair orders to suppliers. Keep abreast of changes affecting both the supply and demand of needed parts and services.<br />-Work as liaison between Accounts Payable, material services and suppliers to resolve purchase order and invoice discrepancies in a timely manner.<br />-Establish, maintain and update vendor related information in the computer program data base; maintain first line of communication with vendors while building relationships to insure the parts requirement are processed and shipped in a prompt and timely manner.<br />-Negotiate agreements with supplier.<br />-Other administrative duties as assigned; this position includes some travel; must be flexible for occasional overtime assignments.</p>\n <p >Requirements:<br />- B.S. in Business, Trading, Aviation, Engineering or comparable related experience<br />- Excellent verbal, written and computer communication skills in <strong>English and Mandarin Chinese</strong><br />-Able to work independently in a team environment<br />-Ability to analyze technical data; possess excellent negotiation techniques; accuracy with attention to details and follow up skills<br />-Proficiency in MS Word, Excel and Outlook<br />-Valid Driver&rsquo;s License highly desired<br />- Internship and previous work experience in international trading or Aviation/Airlines welcome and preferred</p>', '', 'resume@pac-nyc.com', 5, 126, 2),
(270, 1395273843, 'Art Director', 'AdAsia Communications Inc', 'Design', 'Englewood, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Englewood', 40.892876, -73.972641, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary" >AdAsia is a full-service advertising agency catering to the Asian-American market. We provide our clients with the most effective ways to introduce, reinforce or promote their brands with over 17 million Asian- American consumers.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br />Ideal candidate must be a strong conceptual thinker capable of leading the art direction of various Asian- American advertising campaigns. This position will require superb visual storytelling skills along with knowledge of media requirements/terminology and external vendor capabilities. Candidate will work with Creative Directors in the development of a wide range of campaign tactics that include TV, print, online videos, display banners and other digital creatives for the client''s Retail and Branding efforts.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><strong >Responsibilities<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></strong><br /></span></p>\n<ul>\n <li><span class="summary" >Collaborate with copywriters and varying departments to understand the client''s needs and to develop relevant strategic campaigns<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Supervise all visual aspects of the campaign from concept to final execution<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Management of the quality of finished art and conceptual materials<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Attend relevant internal meetings, core team brainstorming sessions, strategic discussions, et cetera<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Supervise/mentor junior staff in training and development as well as overseeing projects<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >5+ years of agency experience as an Art Director or other design-related position<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Solid verbal communication skills to present thoughtful rationale to clients and to the agency regarding our creative concepts<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Solid skills in InDesign, Photoshop, Illustrator, etc<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Strong organizational skills<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" ><strong>Chinese</strong> <strong>language skills are a major plus</strong><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n <li><span class="summary" >Digital experience is a must</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'jobs@adasia-us.com', 5, 62, 2),
(271, 1395427335, '', 'ReneSola ', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>Marketing Intern, social media press release writing, customer spotlights and testimonials.Associated Press style. writing samples</p>\n<div class="WB_text">&nbsp;</div>\n<p>COMPANY OVERVIEW<br /> ReneSola Ltd. (NYSE: SOL) is a leading global photovoltaic manufacturer with world-class R&amp;D team and advanced production equipment. Established in 2005, ReneSola has 40 subsidiaries across Europe, the Americas and the Asia-Pacific regions. With our innovative technology capabilities and quality products, ReneSola is actively expanding the downstream business, providing integrated solutions for commercial, agricultural and large-scale projects to continuously improve the strategic status of solar energy and to further improve our innovative capability.<br /> <br /> JOB SNAPSHOT<br /> Working Hours: 20-24hrs/week<br /> Job Type: Paid Internship<br /> Location: San Francisco, CA<br /> <br /> JOB DESCRIPTION<br />  Create and implement social media strategy aligned to company''s marketing objectives;<br />  Create and develop content to various company''s social media;<br />  Handle press release writing, customer spotlights and testimonials;<br />  Assist Marketing function with customer engagement issues<br />  Perform related and special duties as assigned<br /> <br /> JOB QUALIFICATION<br />  Bachelor''s degree required, preferably in journalism, public relations, communication or related field;<br />  Solar industry/LED Lighting industry knowledge and experience working with social media desired;<br />  Must demonstrate highly developed skills in writing, grammar and spelling, preferably in Associated Press style;<br />  Desire to work in a fast-paced environment and ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously;<br />  Work effectively and efficiently as part of a team<br /> <br /> ReseSola is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Welcome to join our work family.<br /> Hiring Organization: ReneSola</p>', '', 'hrus@renesola.com', 5, 107, 2),
(272, 1395428430, '', 'AMES-IT', 'Technology', 'Ames, IA, United States', 'United States', 'Iowa', 'Ames', 42.023350, -93.625626, '', '', '', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p></p>\n<p>(Ames IT and Numeric Solutions, LLC)AmesITIT201050H1BH1b</p>\n<p>OPT</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp; &nbsp; </strong><strong>BusinessIntelligence Developer: </strong><strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Position:&nbsp; &nbsp; BI Internship </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Jr.BI Developer (MSBI)</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Required skills and experience:</strong></p>\n<p>-B.S. degree inComputer Science, MIS, Statistics/Math or related major and 1 years of relatedexperience;</p>\n<p>-Basicunderstanding of Business Integration/Data Warehousing (BI/DW) concepts;</p>\n<p>-Experience with SQL reporting services,writing scripts and creating packages is preferred;</p>\n<p>-Knowledge and experience with SQL querylanguage and Relational Database;</p>\n<p>-Excellent analytical/problem-solvingskills;</p>\n<p>-Excellent written and verbalcommunication skills in English</p>\n<p>-Strong experience or good hand-onexperience with Excel/Access preferred;</p>\n<p>-Self-motivatedand great teamwork spirit;</p>\n<p>-Able to coordinate with multi-task andmulti-culture work environment;</p>\n<p>-Seek for someone who would look for atechnical position in the long run.</p>\n<p><strong>Preferredskills and experience</strong></p>\n<p><strong>-</strong>Oracle, SQL Server, Excelsheets or other relational databases experience</p>\n<p>-Application Supportexperience with financial and data warehouse applications,</p>\n<p>-Experience with one ormore BI tools such as Cognos, Tableau or Business Objects</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibility</strong>:</p>\n<p>-Business Consultant analyzes the business objectives of the stakeholderand develops solutions to their business issues.</p>\n<p>-Data Analyst develops a logical data model.</p>\n<p>-Requirements Analyst identifies, analyzes, and documents businessrequirements and deliver