(287, 1395782927, 'Gallery Associate', ' Chambers Fine Art', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="txtChinese">\n<p>Christophe W. Mao2000. (Sir William Chambers) 200919522 (Frank Gehry) (Shigeru Ban)(Jean Nouvel) (High Line)</p>\n</div>\n<p>Established Chelsea gallery specializing in contemporary Chinese art seeks a full-time Gallery Associate to work closely with Directors and gallery staff to support a dynamic exhibition program between our NY and Beijing locations. We are a closely-knit hard-working team and are looking for a highly motivated individual who will contribute to all aspects of the gallery&rsquo;s operations including exhibition-planning, sales, artist-relations, registrarial duties and PR. This is an excellent opportunity to gain experience working closely with the gallery&rsquo;s senior staff and there is significant room for growth based on ability.&nbsp;<br /><br />Candidate must have at least 2 years prior experience working full-time in a gallery, museum, or related art institution.&nbsp;<br /><br />The position&rsquo;s responsibilities include, but are not limited, to the following:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Work closely with senior staff to plan exhibitions including organizing opening-receptions and artist-related events; coordinating shipping and installation; preparing related PR materials.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage gallery&rsquo;s PR outreach including maintaining relationships with journalists and developing new contacts, assembling press-materials and maintaining gallery&rsquo;s web presence.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Directors with sales-outreach including creating and assembling sales-material&nbsp;<br />&bull; Support Directors during art-fairs including working at the fair as necessary.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Registrar with managing gallery inventory including organizing incoming and outgoing shipments of artwork, as well as registering and maintaining inventory database.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Co-ordinate events organized by gallery, both on-site and off-site.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain gallery&rsquo;s contact database.&nbsp;<br />REQUIREMENTS:&nbsp;<br />&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree with at least 2 years experience working in a gallery, museum, or related art institution..&nbsp;<br />&bull; Fluent in PC based applications including MS Office/Word/Outlook/Excel, as well as gallery data-base software such as ArtSystems or ArtBase.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Experienced with photoshop and manipulating digital images&nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong organizational and time management skills.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class="summary">If interested, please send resume, cover-letter and at least two references.</span></p>', '', 'cfa@chambersfineart.com', 5, 167, 2),
(288, 1395783057, 'Summer 2014 Intellectual Property Intern', 'Tory Burch', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>Overview:&nbsp;<br />The Tory Burch legal team seeks qualified law student interns for summer 2014 with an interest in intellectual property.&nbsp;<br /><br />Responsibilities:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assist Senior Counsel on all aspects of brand protection and anti-counterfeiting, specifically online enforcement</li>\n<li>Monitor online platforms based in the US, Asia, and South America for counterfeit Tory Burch products and conduct take-downs on said platforms;</li>\n<li>Assist in civil enforcement as necessary (drafting cease and desist letters, preparing evidence for litigation);</li>\n<li>Maintain IP Enforcement Database for all global anti-counterfeiting matters, includes entering information into system, scanning, saving, and preparing updates and summaries as needed;</li>\n<li>Draft memoranda on relevant legal issues related to IP or other areas of law.</li>\n<li>Assist on any other tasks as assigned by members of the legal department.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />Qualifications:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum of full-time commitment June 2nd through August 8th</li>\n<li>Ability to assist with legal and non-legal issues as they arise in a fast-paced corporate environment.</li>\n<li>Must be motivated, eager, and excited to join a growing fashion company.</li>\n<li>Organized, hard-working, and an attention to detail.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li>Experience in trademark and copyright law.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li>Ability to read and <strong>speak Chinese</strong> and/or Korean is a plus.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li>This is a paid position ($10/hr)</li>\n</ul>', 'https://careers-toryburch.icims.com/jobs/2221/summer-2014-intellectual-property-intern/job', '', 5, 194, 2),
