(293, 1395786275, '', '', 'Resturant', '', 'United States', 'California', 'Glendale', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'California', 'Glendale', 'None', 'Full Time', '<section id="job-description" class="row-fluid">\n<p>Din Tai Fung was ranked No. 1 in the inaugural "101 Best Restaurants in Asia (2013)" by&nbsp;<em>The Daily Meal</em>. We are the world leader in contemporary Chinese food and have received Michelin Stars in our locations in Hong Kong. With over 80 locations in Asia, Din Tai Fung is just beginning to grow in the United States.</p>\n<p>We are looking for bartenders that can deliver great customer service with a smile. Our bars have full food service, so applicants should have restaurant experience.</p>\n</section>', '', 'm93gfb9ehw@jobs.shiftgig.com', 5, 128, 2),
(294, 1395871729, 'Chinese Speaking Scheduling Specialist', 'ComplexCare Solutions', 'Service', '', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are looking for a Chinese speaking individual to work with our Chinese speaking Medicare Members. Prefer someone with customer service and working in a high volume call center environment.&nbsp;<br /><br />Scope:&nbsp;<br /><br />The Scheduling Specialist works with the MLTC RN''s and Nurse Practitioners scheduling the Managed Long Term Care Assessments for CCS members and managing multiple clinician calendars. Also responsible for explaining the program to our members and speaking with the primary care physician. The Specialist must enjoy speaking with people on the phone, and possess the in-depth understanding and the diverse skills to overcome member issues, hesitation or objections. The Specialist will coordinate calendaring for clinical field staff managing member needs and field staff availability and geography. The Specialist is accountable for making a high volume of calls with exceptional member service.&nbsp;<br /><br />RESPONSIBILITIES&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Conduct outbound calls to Medicare Advantage members to schedule in-home visits by nurse practitioners or other clinical staff&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Provide a member orientation when consent is obtained for the in-home appointment ensuring the member comprehends all the features and benefits of the program&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Coordinate schedules of field staff to accommodate member needs, geography and program priorities&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Field inbound calls with a positive attitude, building rapport and trust with members&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Interact with other departments such as Care Coordination, Social Work, and Care Managers, to resolve member issues&nbsp;<br /><br />&bull; Organize time/tasks and work without direct and daily supervision&nbsp;<br /><b