(298, 1395874193, 'A/R Supervisor', 'American Chung Nam', 'Finance', '', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 0.000000, 0.000000, 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="jvdescriptionbody">\n<p>This is a unique opportunity to join a high performing team and enhance your professional profile. You will work with and manage a team to determine and verify the correct calculations, postings, verifying and/or reporting data. You will be required to communicate the results of your work to direct and senior management.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Major Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Responsible for A/R and resolution of discrepancies with vendors</li>\n<li>Monitor accounts receivables. Participate in monthly aging reviews and present to Accounting management team.</li>\n<li>Review posted payments and prepare monthly statements of accounts.</li>\n<li>Data entry into accounting system.</li>\n<li>Monitor internal controls to assure compliance with established procedures related to accounts receivable</li>\n<li>Enhance the company&rsquo;s policies and procedures surrounding the accounts receivable cycle</li>\n<li>Communicates and coordinates accounting policies, practices and procedures with the department and company managers</li>\n<li>Performs other job related duties and projects as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><br />Required qualifications and competencies:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>BS in Accounting or Finance.</li>\n<li>4-6 years of combined accounting and A/R experience in logistics, ocean freight, trucking.</li>\n<li>Experience in the banking industry and/or with foreign exchange rates highly preferred.</li>\n<li>LC experience highly desired.</li>\n<li>Management and/or supervisory experience required.</li>\n<li>Experience with A/R duties, including with credit and collections.</li>\n<li>Team-player with excellent interpersonal and influencing skills.</li>\n<li>Integrity, commitme