(317, 1396563925, 'Relationship Banker', 'JP Morgan Chase', 'Finance', 'Arcadia, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Arcadia', 34.139729, -118.035347, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h5>Job Description</h5>\n<p>Play a vital role in the customer banking experience at Chase! As part of JPMorgan Chase, a leading global financial services firm, Chase has over 5,600 locations where our bankers build relationships with customers by providing them with products and services to meet their ever-changing needs.</p>\n<p>The Relationship Banker is a branch based customer facing position whose primary goal is to acquire, retain, deepen and manage relationships with our customers. Relationship Bankers are responsible for generating growth in balances through the sale, marketing, promotion and referral of products utilizing a proactive and disciplined approach. You will take a lead role in creating an outstanding customer experience and helping the Branch meet sales objectives contributing to the success of the firm. As a Relationship Banker, you will have an assigned portfolio of customers and proactively meet with them - face to face and over the phone - to discover their financial needs and provide product and service recommendations. In this role you will also continue to develop and cultivate your existing customer relationships. You will also partner with specialists (such as Loan Officers, Business Bankers, and Financial Advisors), to ensure our customers get access to experts who can help them with specialized financial needs</p>\n<p>If you are interested in building a career at Chase, there are plenty of career development opportunities available. Many successful Relationship Bankers develop skills to move into roles such as Branch Managers, Assistant Branch Manager Sales, Relationship Managers, Mortgage Officers and Financial Advisors - or other career paths.</p>\n<p>This position is subject to the Dodd Frank/Truth in Lending Act qualification requirements for Loan Originators. As such, an employment offer for this position is contingent on JPMC''''s review of your criminal conviction history, credit report, information available through NMLS, and any other information relevant to a determination by JPMC that you demonstrate financial responsibility, good character, and general fitness for the position. Note that any felony conviction within the last seven years will disqualify you from consideration for this position. Your continued employment in this position would be contingent upon compliance with Truth in Lending Act/Dodd Frank Loan Originator requirements.</p>\n<p>In addition, this position requires National Mortgage Licensing System and Registry (NMLS) registration under the SAFE Act of 2008. As such, upon active employment with JPMorgan Chase, you will be required to either register on NMLS, or to update your existing registration as necessary to grant access to and reflect your employment with JPMorgan Chase. Your continued employment in this position with JPMorgan Chase is contingent upon compliance with the SAFE Act, including successful registration immediately after your start date, and timely completion of annual renewal and required updates thereafter.</p>\n<p>Any information obtained during the registration, update, and renewal processes or through NMLS notifications may impact your employment with the firm. Any of the completed information you provide during the Chase on-line application process may be transferred, on your behalf, to NMLS by JPMorgan Chase. Please carefully review the information you provide to Chase for accuracy and consistency and with any current NMLS record, if applicable, before submitting. Further information about NMLS and registration requirements of registration can be found at: http://mortgage.nationwidelicensingsystem.org/SAFE/Pages/default.aspx.</p>\n<h5>Qualifications</h5>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>College degree preferred or High school degree/GED or foreign equivalent</li>\n<li>Minimum of one year Branch Sales Experience or equivalent Financial Services Sales experience with proven success in establishing new clients, revenue generation, and the ability to deliver results.</li>\n<li>Series 6/7, state registration (including 63 if required), and life licenses REQUIRED. If unlicensed, must be obtained within 90 days of joining Chase</li>\n<li>Ability to establish credibility and rapport, be friendly and personable and look for ways to benefit the customer''''s financial relationship both over the phone as well as in person.</li>\n<li>Excellent customer contact skills; comfortable asking questions/interviewing customers about their financial situation; strong listening skills comfortable making outbound calls</li>\n<li>Understands how to present features, and benefits of products and services to customers with differing needs</li>\n<li>Self motivated, assertive, performs well in a competitive sales environment</li>\n<li>Professional, thorough and organized; able to follow standard operating policies and procedures</li>\n<li>Ability to learn products, services and procedures quickly and accurately; explain concepts clearly to customers</li>\n<li>Understand how to interpret numbers, trends and data to make effective decisions</li>\n<li>Ability to work branch hours, including weekends and some evenings</li>\n</ul>\n<p>JPMorgan Chase is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer M/F/Disability/Veteran</p>', 'http://jpmchase.jobs/arcadia-ca/relationship-banker-fashion-park-arcadia-ca-chinese-mandarin-speaking-required/45735930/job/', '', 5, 189, 2),
(318, 1396646694, '', 'Lyft', 'Technology', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'H1B', 'Full Time', '<p>startupLyftUberDfunding H1b<br /><br />UI/UX<strong></strong></p>', 'https://www.lyft.me/jobs', 'mlchen85@hotmail.com', 5, 254, 2),
(319, 1396722380, 'Funeral Arranger', 'Duggan''s Serra Mortuary', 'Service', 'Daly City, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Daly City', 37.687923, -122.470207, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p >No funeral experience necessary-will train-Must be fluent in Mandarin/Clear fluent English, basic Cantonese a plus Candidate must enjoy working with the public. Candidate will be trained to meet with families, to plan services and direct funeral services. Candidates should have experience working in an office environment and/or busy service oriented business.</p>\n <p >Job Description and Duties:<br />Requirements: Clear communication is very important in our business. Applicants must have excellent command of English (speaking, reading, and writing), as well as speak fluent Mandarin, basic Cantonese (reading/writing a plus); must be able to work well with public and co-workers in a kind, respectful and compassionate manner. Intermediate computer skills (WORD, EXCEL), excellent telephone skills and have an ability to work well under pressure, attention to detail a must.</p>\n <p >Language Skills: Clear communication is very important with the families we serve. Applicants must have excellent command of fluent English (speaking, reading, and writing), fluent Mandarin and basic Cantonese (a plus).</p>\n <p >Work Schedule: Office is open 7 days a week from 8:00am &ndash; 9:00pm. Schedule depends on need, will discuss open schedules with applicants.</p>\n <p >Duggan&rsquo;s Serra Mortuary is the largest family-owned funeral home in Northern California. Duggan''s Serra has been serving families with kindness and compassion in the San Francisco Bay Area at their Daly City location for over 50 years. Opened in 1963 by Bud and Madeline Duggan and their four children, Bill, Dan and the late Maureen and Patty, their legacy in the funeral industry began in 1885 and continues today with their 4th and 5th generations. Duggan&rsquo;s is family owned and operated business by Bill and Dan Duggan serving all faiths, denominations and cultures. (Duggan&rsquo;s website: www.duggansserra.com)</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Duggan''s-Serra-Mortuary/jobs/Funeral-Arranger-Will-Train-5b51d21d1ab86d45?r=1', '', 5, 124, 2),
(320, 1396722841, 'Human Resource Assistant', 'Chinese American Service League', 'Service', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="post_description" >\n<p>Working under the Deputy Director, performs Human Resources duties including administration of employees timesheets, maintaining personnel files, updating employees data on ADP system, etc.&nbsp; This position also backs up the front desk receptionists, and assists with the purchasing function, as well as other clerical and administrative tasks needed in the Administration Department.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The ideal candidate must be detail-orientated and able to maintain confidentiality. Microsoft Office skills are a must as well as bilingual <strong>Chinese</strong> (Cantonese) and English skills.&nbsp; Excellent reading and writing skills in English is required, and reading and writing in Chinese is preferred but not required.&nbsp; The educational requirement is high school graduate with at least two years of college.&nbsp; A Bachelor&rsquo;s degree is preferred and experience in either Human Resources, Administration or related field is also preferred.</p>\n</div>', '', 'jobs@caslservice.org', 5, 158, 2),
(321, 1396723454, 'Project Portfolio | Delivery Manager - Microsoft Projects', 'Catapult Systems ', 'Technology', 'Seattle, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 47.606209, -122.332069, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>High performing team members. Challenging projects. A stable and profitable company. And a great place to work! This is what you can expect if you join the Catapult Systems team! Founded in 1993 and headquartered in Austin, Texas, Catapult Systems &ndash; a Chinasoft Int''l (CSI) company &ndash; is a global IT services provider and one of the top Microsoft National Systems Integrators in the United States. It is a very exciting time for Catapult Systems, and we are currently expanding our delivery leadership team in <strong><em>Redmond, WA</em></strong> as we continue our growth in the Northwest.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>What do we attribute our award-winning success to? The people we hire, of course! We provide you the tools and leadership that you need to be successful, and let you do what you do best. We enable you to make the decisions that you feel are in the best interest of our clients, and we trust your judgment. &nbsp;This type of empowerment, independence and an ongoing commitment to solving real business problems through the innovative use of Microsoft technologies, has resulted in Catapult being <strong><em>voted one of the best places to work year after year!</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>What role will I be playing?</h3>\n<p>The Project Portfolio | Delivery Manager (DM) role will entail managing multiple software development projects and teams for Catapult''s Microsoft (MS) Corporate client business in Redmond. Responsibilities will include:</p>\n <ul >\n<li>Managing delivery expectations for your assigned MS clients; primary client contact once engaged with client</li>\n<li>Acting as the liaison between the onsite project teams at the Microsoft campus and our China Program Manager/offshore delivery project lead(s) to communicate project status, progress, budget, challenges, risk, etc.</li>\n<li>Working closely with&nbsp;Catapult Project Manager(s) to accurately forecast and manage the project assignments and utilization</li>\n<li>Managing and delegating project responsibilities and priorities to project management, lead and development staff</li>\n<li>Serving as the face of Catapult to your team of consultants and assisting with interviewing, retaining and growing that team</li>\n<li>Working closely with Catapult''s Account Executives on sales opportunity strategy and positioning Catapult''s value proposition to your MS clients</li>\n<li>New and ongoing project and resource planning with your MS clients</li>\n<li>Preparing formal client documentation as required</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>What''s&nbsp;required?</h3>\n <ul >\n<li>First and foremost, you should be an energetic leader and enjoy what you do! This role requires a significant amount of team/client interaction, communication and coordination. Excellent interpersonal skills including a passion for people is critical to this role.</li>\n<li>A minimum of 8 years of related leadership and professional IT consulting delivery and project management experience; ability to measure and report the health of projects</li>\n<li>A positive leader who promotes a culture of trust and teamwork</li>\n<li>Ability to delegate, motivate and influence your team(s)</li>\n<li>Credible and professional presence; strong analysis skills and ability to make critical business recommendations; ability to think and interact strategically with clients</li>\n<li>Strong attention to detail, organization and negotiation skills</li>\n<li>Ability to conduct evening conference calls with the China team</li>\n<li>Experience using Microsoft Project</li>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree in Business or related field</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>What else would make me stand out?</h3>\n <ul >\n<li>Previous experience in a delivery leadership role with a Microsoft Systems Integrator (SI) and/or Microsoft Corporate in Redmond</li>\n<li>Previous experience successfully forecasting resource utilization and assignments, and managing a team of consultants</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of Microsoft platform products and solutions (SharePoint, CRM, .NET&hellip;)</li>\n<li>Fluent speaking <strong>Mandarin</strong></li>\n<li>PMP Certification</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.catapultsystems.com/careers/job-opportunities/Pages/Project-Portfolio-Delivery-Manager-Microsoft-Projects.aspx', '', 5, 115, 2),
(322, 1396764043, ' Credit Analyst- Trade Finance', '', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>This exciting position at the New York Branch will report to the Head of Trade Services and Finance for the Marketing Department.</strong></p>\n<p><strong><u>Responsibilities:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Support soliciting Trade Finance clients.</li>\n<li>Participate in client meetings and prepare call reports.</li>\n<li>Conduct client due diligence</li>\n<li>Support Relationship Manager including Credit Proposal Memo and other loan documentations preparation in both English and Chinese.</li>\n<li>Prepare&nbsp; the credit application and approval process together with Relationship Manager</li>\n<li>Set up and maintain the credit files.</li>\n<li>Perform periodic credit reviews.</li>\n<li>Conduct client surveys to understand existing and potential client needs</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Support marketing event such as seminars, receptions and sponsorship events</li>\n<li>Develop client and business database Prepare periodic reports.</li>\n<li>Prepare periodic reports to the Head Office.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><u>Skills and Experience:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fluent in written and verbal English and <strong>Chinese</strong>.</li>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance or Accounting; Master&rsquo;s degree preferred.</li>\n<li>Minimum of zero to three years of professional marketing experience.</li>\n<li>Strong collaboration and personal leadership skills with the ability to influence others.</li>\n<li>Strong organizational, analytical and communication skills.</li>\n<li>Strong computer skills are essential.&nbsp; Proficient in MS Office (Work, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n<li>Open to learning new skills and new products.</li>\n<li>Flexibility, adaptability and team approach.</li>\n<li>Able to prioritize and multi-task; demonstrate flexibility and acceptability.</li>\n<li>Proven experience in working in a team environment and seen as a strong team player.</li>\n<li>Willingness to take initiative.</li>\n<li>Willingness to travel if required.</li>\n<li>Strong integrity</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This position offers an opportunity for professional growth within the Bank. Successful applicants will be asked to show proof that they can legally work in the U.S. <u>without</u> requiring visa sponsorship. Please submit your resume and cover letter.</p>', '', 'MarketingCareers@ny.cmbchina.com', 5, 334, 2);
