(332, 1397107710, '', 'Panda Express', 'Management', 'Rosemead, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Rosemead', 34.080566, -118.072845, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><strong>Descriptions:<br /></strong>&bull;&nbsp;Develops and implements positive workforce practices and strategies in collaboration with Operations leaders and HR.&nbsp; Aligns practices and strategies with the company&rsquo;s Mission, Values, Culture as well as desired work environment and business goals.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Responds to and Investigates associate or guest complaints related to associate relations issues, such as discrimination, harassment, wage and hour laws, or unfair treatment.&nbsp; Maintains accurate records in compliance with company procedures and recommends actions to be taken. <br />&bull;&nbsp;Resolves associate relations concerns following federal and state laws and company policies through effective interaction with associates and Operations leaders.&nbsp; Ensures consistency with company policies.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Prepares formal written responses and supporting documentation related to any associate relations charges (e.g., discrimination, harassment, etc.) as required from within the company and from external agencies.&nbsp; Prepares for EEO hearings and mediations and assists in negotiating settlements.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Reviews and investigates all requests for suspension, corrective action, and termination to ensure requested action complies with company policy.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;"><br /></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d872917e337.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.d872917e339.row1" class="inlinepanel" style="display: inline;" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial;">JOB REQUIREMENTS:</span></strong></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&bull;&nbsp;Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in HR or related field required; recruiting experience preferred <br />&bull;&nbsp;Minimum five years of experience in HR handling associate relations issues, preferably in a retail/hospitality operations environment<br />&bull;&nbsp;Must be available for alternative work week schedules, including weekends and non-business hours<br />&bull;&nbsp;Successful completion of annual store training.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial;">KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES:</span></strong></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&bull;&nbsp;Ability to demonstrate and teach Panda&rsquo;s Mission, Values, and Culture<br />&bull;&nbsp;Comprehensive knowledge of local, state, and federal laws and regulations pertaining to employment (i.e., discrimination and harassment, wage and hour, etc.)<br />&bull;&nbsp;Strong analytical and research skills <br />&bull;&nbsp;Computer proficiency, including Microsoft Office Suite<br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to prepare investigation reports and related written documentation<br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to effectively communicate the values of the organization and to exemplify the highest level of interpersonal skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;Strong communication, listening, presentation, writing, and assessment skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to work effectively with Operations leadership, providing guidance on company policies and practices related to associate relations <br />&bull;&nbsp;Ability to embrace change and continuous learning</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&bull;&nbsp;Office conditions; flexible work schedule, including weekends and non-business hours; occasional travel to stores</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Panda Restaurant Group&rsquo;s culture is strongly guided by our Mission and Values, highlighted on the Panda websites.&nbsp; We recommend all interested candidates become familiar with our Mission and Values, as well as the principles of The Seven Habits of Highly Effective People, by Stephen Covey.</span></p>\n</div>', 'https://pandarg.taleo.net/careersection/panda+corporate/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=13000226', '', 5, 96, 2),
(333, 1397108151, 'Contract Music Content Editor (Mainland China Specialist) ', 'Gracenote', 'Entertainment', 'Emeryville, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Emeryville', 37.831318, -122.285248, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>At Gracenote, we live and breathe music. Gracenote&rsquo;s products and services power products from Apple, Amazon, BMW, Sony, and others. We''re the company behind many innovative music and video products.&nbsp;<br /><br />Our Music Content team is made of up real music experts with a deep knowledge of regional music trends and genres. As part of this team, the content editor will ensure that album and artist metadata are of highest quality. Daily responsibilities include applying independent judgment to target, prioritize, create, review and correct music-related data elements according to established standards and practices. The editor will also be responsible for analyzing internal reports, and tracking various internal and external popularity measures to ensure and improve data quality, content coverage and product performance.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of music that is relevant in mainland China with demonstrated expertise in one or more major genres, including detailed subgenres;</li>\n<li>Excellent English writing, editing and verbal communication skills</li>\n<li>Fluency in Mandarin Chinese, literacy in Simplified Chinese</li>\n<li>Excellent basic computer skills (Microsoft Word, Excel, etc.), especially experience working with large amounts of data</li>\n<li>In-depth research skills</li>\n<li>Knowledgeable about database operations and data access methods, including MS Access, MySQL, etc</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be detail-oriented, and show familiarity with data-standardization policies and techniques, styles guides, and/or normalization routines</li>\n<li>Able to work independently, with little or no direct supervision, surfacing problems or issues for approval as necessary</li>\n<li>Able to establish, communicate, and follow agreed upon project priorities</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />B.A. or B.S. in relevant field, or equivalent related experience&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>PLUSES&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Literacy in Traditional Chinese</li>\n<li>Familiarity with other Chinese dialects (esp. any dialects of Wu, Min, Hakka, or Yue)</li>\n<li>Familiarity with schemes for Romanization of Chinese, especially pinyin</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of Chinese internet structure and culture with an eye to research</li>\n<li>Any practical knowledge of SQL and relational databases</li>\n<li>Previous experience in a music technology, music retail, music industry or related media industry job</li>\n</ul>', 'http://ch.tbe.taleo.net/CH01/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=GRACENOTE&cws=1&rid=399&source=Indeed.com', '', 373, 85, 2),
(334, 1397108230, 'China Energy Analyst', 'Eurasia Group', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Eurasia Group is seeking an experienced and motivated analyst of Chinese politics and energy policy.<br /> <br /> Candidates are expected to have:<br /> <br /> &bull;A strong understanding of China''s political system and economy, along with geopolitics-- with particular expertise regarding China''s role in global energy markets.<br /> <br /> &bull;The ability to analyze specific sectors of the Chinese economy.<br /> <br /> &bull;The ability to produce in-depth research and forward-looking policy analysis.<br /> <br /> &bull;Excellent analytical and presentation (oral and written) skills in a succinct style at native English standard.<br /> <br /> &bull;Commitment and ability to deliver on tight deadlines.<br /> <br /> &bull;<strong>Reading, writing, and speaking fluency in both English and Chinese</strong>.<br /> <br /> &bull;Familiarity and experience with managing and coordinating complex research projects.<br /> <br /> Requirements include:<br /> <br /> &bull;A minimum of 3-5 years of professional experience in a relevant field connected to producing policy analysis and/or consulting work for the private sector.<br /> <br /> &bull;An advanced degree in political science, regional studies, economics, or another relevant discipline.<br /> <br /> &bull;Extensive knowledge of China''s energy sector and dynamics in the global energy markets.<br /> <br /> &bull;Significant in-country experience.<br /> <br /> Applications from more experienced candidates are welcome.<br /> <br /> Applicants will be considered for the firm''s Washington, London, or New York offices. All applicants must be eligible to work in either the United States or the United Kingdom.<br /> <br /> To apply for the position, please submit resume, cover letter and salary requirements (MS Word, Plain Text or PDF only) in a single document by following the instructions below. This position is available immediately. The resume evaluation process will take place on an on-going basis until the position has been filled.</p>', 'http://www.eurasiagroup.net/careers/view/analyst_china_energy_washington', '', 5, 126, 2),
(335, 1397108995, '', 'Skidmore, Owings & Merrill LLP', 'Engineering', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="job_details_ats_requisition_description" class="cell_input   dhtml_editor_render ">\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Primary Responsibilities: <br /></strong>&bull; Contribute to the detailed preparation of design and construction documents on assigned projects <br /> &bull; Assist with finding solutions to general architectural problems <br /> &bull; Perform work on project segments, <strong>incl. technical specification and drawing document translation from Mandarin into English and from English into Mandarin</strong> <br /> &bull; Communicate with Design Institutes and Consultants to resolve code compliance, technical and coordination issues <br /> &bull; Check and coordinate details and dimensions <br /> &bull; Review selective shop drawings and samples <br /> &bull; Coordinates work with the project team <br /> &bull; Assist in the preparation of punchlists and field observation reports <br /></span></p>\n</div>\n<div class="cell_label">&nbsp;</div>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Background and skillset:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">&bull; Completion of five or six-year architectural degree program or graduate of four-year program <br /> &bull; Minimum of 3 years experience in preparation of construction documents and design development <br /> &bull; Ability to speak, read, write and type fluently in Mandarin Chinese and English. <br /> &bull; Demonstrated general knowledge of building materials, detailing, construction techniques related engineering principles and building codes <br /> &bull; Demonstrated proficiency in AutoCAD (including AutoCAD 2008) <br /> &bull; Previous experience working for an American firm doing business with companies in the People''s Republic of China strongly prefe