(343, 1397369620, 'Educational Consultant', '', 'Consulting', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary"><strong>Essential duties and Responsibilities:</strong><br /> Provide an overall application plan; mentor students on a one-on-one basis in the application process, and ensure the applications quality and completion <br />Brainstorm essay topics, and design individual plans for students based on their interests and background. <br />Provide college application and interview strategy, as well as information concerning the visa application <br />Be familiar with top universities and their departments <br /><br /> <strong>Salary :</strong> 20 0000 - 30 0000 RMB per year <br /><br /> <strong>Location :</strong> Beijing, Shanghai, Xiamen, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Wuhan, Nanjing, Guiyang, Kunming, Chengdu, Dalian, Shenyang, Xi''an, Taiyuan, Changchun, Zhengzhou <br />In addition to educational consultants, we offer the following positions: SAT and TOEFL instructor, marketing specialist, national and international activity planner </span></p>', '', 'overseahr@zmnedu.com', 5, 270, 2),
(344, 1397456713, 'International Store Operations Associate', 'Forever 21', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Department Summary:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> Forever 21 is seeking an innovative, energetic, and passionate team player to add to our dynamic&nbsp;Operations team.<br /> <br /> <strong>Job Purpose</strong>: <br /> The International Operations Associate will assist Regional/District Managers in monitoring sales generation, operational, and personnel functions for Forever 21 international stores in the assigned region to ensure customer satisfaction, profitability, business growth, and compliance with company procedures. <br /> <br /> <strong>Deliverables:</strong><br /> &bull;&nbsp;Partner with International Regional/District Store Managers and field Operations personnel to communicate all business performance/sales goals, customer satisfaction expectations and to understand the needs of each region<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Communicate with Store, District and Regional Mangers, as well as internal stakeholders such as IT and Accounting, to gather necessary data to produce performance reports from<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Collaborate with the Regional Manager to understand business best-practices in the region and suggest any business changes/adjustments that could be made to better position Forever 21 in the market <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Partner with the International Regional Manager is assessing the motivational needs of the region&rsquo;s store employees, assisting with employee engagement initiatives <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Serve as a resource for International Regional, District and Store Managers for any questions or issues related to company or industry best-practices<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Communicate with store employees within the region to identify and resolve employee concerns; gather feedback and ensure that any customer-related issues in the region are addressed <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Work with in-country Human Resources personnel to resolve any employment or labor related issues <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Act as a point-of-contact for regional communication, information requests, management conferences/meetings and community events<br /> <br /> <strong>Knowledge, Skills, and Qualifications:</strong> <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must have a High School diploma or equivalent; Associate or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree is a plus<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must speak, read and write <strong>Mandarin and Cantonese</strong> <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must have 1-2 years of previous experience in an administrative/support role, preferably in a corporate retail environment<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Previous retail experience is required<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Must have advanced skills in Microsoft Office Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Excellent organizational and time-management skills<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Ability to prioritize workloads and manage time effectively<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Excellent written and verbal communication skills<br /> &bull;&nbsp;Attention to detail and ability to handle multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment <br /> &bull;&nbsp;Ability to develop effective business relationships with all levels; strong customer service skills</p>\n<p>At Forever 21, style isn&rsquo;t dictated&hellip;It&rsquo;s inspired. Forever 21 is the leading fashion retailer of the latest trends and the season&rsquo;s hottest styles at can&rsquo;t-resist-prices. U.S. and international locations stay true to the fast-fashion destination&rsquo;s iconic store aesthetic giving fashion fans all over the globe the unforgettable shopping experience that is the one and only Forever 21.<br /> <br /> Joining the Forever 21 family means joining an incredible team of talented, passionate and innovative people who work together to bring fashion to everyone, everywhere.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re always on the lookout for talented individuals eager to thrive in our fast-paced, dynamic environment filled with vast opportunities for career growth and development. This is a place where your ideas become actualized, creativity is encouraged and the possibilities are endless. Be part of something epic. Be part of Forever 21. Apply today!</p>', 'https://forever21.tms.hrdepartment.com/cgi-bin/a/highlightjob.cgi?jobid=12856', '', 5, 143, 2),
(345, 1397457034, '', '', 'Marketing', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div>\n<p>Lancome Beauty Advisor Part Time- City of Industry</p>\n<p><strong>Fluency in Chinese (Mandarin or Cantonese) is highly desirable.</strong></p>\n<p>Lancome is the #1 luxury global beauty brand that delivers luxurious service and innovative products to women all over the world. Beauty Advisors are the ambassadors of the brand. As a Beauty Advisor, in a retail store environment, you will advise, coach, and help women fulfill their expressed beauty image.</p>\n<p><strong>Specific Responsibilities</strong>:&bull; Greet customers in a welcoming and timely manner&bull; Communicate effectively with clients by asking questions and listening attentively&bull; Recommend and inspire others to try our products through product demonstrations&bull; Take initiative to ensure client satisfaction&bull; Strengthen relationships with clients by following-up, recommending new products and inviting them to promotional events&bull; Work independently and as a team to achieve sales goals&bull; Become a Brand advocate and product expert&bull; Stay current on the latest beauty products and trends&bull; Maintain a clean and professional counter by stocking inventory, creating displays, merchandising, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Qualifications:</strong>&bull; Customer service-oriented&bull; Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills&bull; Sales experience&bull; Ability to build and maintain relationships with clients and peers&bull; Motivated by challenge and thrives working in a goal-oriented, fast-paced environment.</p>\n</div>', 'http://talentdesk.com/job/44845/loreal/lancme-beauty-advisor-part-time-fluency-in-chinese-mandarin-or-cantonese', '', 5, 164, 2),
