n style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 17.333332061767578px; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; display: inline !important; float: none;">communication skills<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<ul style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 17.333332061767578px; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\n<li>Basic computer knowledge and skills</li>\n<li>Fluent in English and <strong>Mandarin</strong> preferred</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://ztecareers.hua.hrsmart.com/hrsmart/ats/Posting/view/532', '', 5, 256, 2),
(355, 1397713380, 'Associate Specialist, Asian 20th Century & Contemporary Art', '', 'Art', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="JD-AllFields" style="color: #000000; font-family: Times; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #f6f6f6;">\n<div id="JD-Field1">\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Position Summary:<br /></span></strong>The Associate Specialist is primarily responsible for cataloguing and preparing consigned property for sale.&nbsp; In addition, this position works closely under the supervision of senior specialist colleagues to develop increased responsibility in the production of appraisals and proposals, increased knowledge of domestic client relationship management, and relevant markets for the art category, and increased negotiating and selling skills</p>\n</div>\n<div id="JD-Field2">\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Responsibility Data:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Research property including authenticity, bibliography, provenance and exhibition history.</li>\n<li>Catalogue property for public and private sales and write and prepare catalogue essays.</li>\n<li>Prepare property for hilling sessions (meetings to determine value, condition and marketability of property) and amend catalogue sheets after hilling sessions.</li>\n<li>Review incoming photo inquires with senior specialist or department head to determine sale potential.</li>\n<li>Work with all client categories (collectors, dealers, corporations, institutions) in the areas of business-getting and selling, under the supervision of more senior specialist or department head.</li>\n<li>Function as liaison with the Trusts, Estates &amp; Appraisals department, working on appraisals as a means of generating new long-term business opportunities and reconnecting with inactive clients.</li>\n<li>Participate in catalogue production and layout process.</li>\n<li>Prepare condition reports of consigned property prior to the auction.</li>\n<li>Participate in pre-sale exhibition set-up.</li>\n<li>Assist clients in the galleries during sale week.</li>\n<li>Participate in Telephone Bidding with clients during the auction.</li>\n<li>View and visit competitors&rsquo; auctions and track overall results.</li>\n<li>Actively participate in events, art fairs, and other functions to represent Christie&rsquo;s.</li>\n<li>Serve as primary liaison with outside experts.</li>\n<li>Other duties as assigned by Manager.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id="JD-Field3">\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Skills and Requirements:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent work experience in applicable Art History or Decorative Arts category; M.A preferred.</li>\n<li>Minimum of 4 years paid work experience in related field; or 2 years as a Junior Specialist.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of the auction business and contemporary art preferred.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability in appraising property and business-getting.</li>\n<li>Proficiency in Chinese (Mandarin) preferred.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of E-mail, Spreadsheet, Word Processing and Presentation software (Microsoft Office preferred), Filemaker.</li>\n<li>Ability to learn Christie&rsquo;s systems including Siebel, Property System, intranet and website.</li>\n<li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, including superior written and spoken communication.</li>\n<li>Superior client service skills.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to multi-task and prioritize.</li>\n<li>Strong follow-up skills with attention to detail.</li>\n<li>Ability to work within a team environment</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id="JD-Field4">\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Working Conditions:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work is performed in an office setting, and off-site in various client settings (private, corporate and institution.)</li>\n<li>Noise level in the office work environment is moderate, will vary for external locations.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id="JD-Field5">\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Physical Requirements:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required to handle, inspect and/or take photographs of works of art for appraisal and consignment</li>\n<li>Required to create written or recorded descriptions of inspected items</li>\n<li>Required to attend events, exhibitions, art fairs locally, domestically and internationally</li>\n<li>Required to meet with clients on-site and off-site</li>\n<li>Required to travel (local, domestic and international)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id="JD-Field6">\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Tools &amp; Equipment Used:</span></strong></p>\n<p>Basic office equipment including personal computer, copy machine, fax machine, scanner; office supplies</p>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://emea3.recruitmentplatform.com/syndicated/lay/jsoutputinitrapido.cfm?component=lay9999_jdesc100a&nPostingID=939&nPostingTargetID=1671&option=52&sort=DESC&respnr=1&ID=QJVFK026203F3VBQBV77968OB&Resultsperpage=10&lg=UK&mask=extcareersite', '', 5, 105, 2),
(356, 1397713730, '', 'ReneSola', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>ReneSola America seeks a highly motivated, dynamic, and self-starting individual with an understanding of general marketing strategies and tactics, to join its North America team.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong><br />&bull; Identify conferences and speaking opportunities in which to take part in the solar, renewable energy, and financing sectors. <br />&bull; Understand new product offerings and how to effectively pull features to benefits into go-to-market launch strategy. <br />&bull; Own new product launch life cycle from start to finish, including booking, execution of publicity events, and follow up.<br />&bull; Monitor and gauge lead quality, based on a pre-determined lead flow chart, scoring process, and other parameters.<br />&bull; Monitor the potential of emerging markets in the US, Canada, and South America and recommend strategies to effectively penetrate those markets as an industry leader.<br />&bull; Capitalize on and seek VOC opportunities, by implementing third party endorsements into marketing collateral.<br />&bull; Manage customer rewards and incentive programs while consistently evaluating opportunities to improve and effectively grow such programs.<br />&bull; Create and present reports with drilled-down statistics to Marketing Director and President, showing effectiveness of specific marketing programs.<br />&bull; Attend trade shows and customer events willingly as needed.<br />&bull; Recommend and identify tactics to effectively launch new product offerings. <br />&bull; Analyze competitor activity and pricing and provide monthly reports to President and Marketing Director, to use as guidance for product pricing.<br /><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<h3 style="margin-bottom: 5px;">Job Requirements</h3>\n<p>The ideal candidate will have at least two years of marketing experience, a minimum of a BA/BS (MBA preferred) degree in marketing and/or communications and/or PR and a proven track record of successfully building brand and creating and managing programs. <strong>Candidate who speaks Mandarin is highly preferred</strong>. This position is designed for a marketing pro with a "roll-up-your-sleeves" mentality, who is more interested in generating closed deals rather than leads. Experience in solar or other areas of clean tech preferred</p>', '', 'HRUS@renesola.com', 5, 100, 2),
(358, 1397750586, '', 'Orbitz', 'Technology', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job"><strong>Overview</strong>:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p style="margin: 0px;">The Product Manager will report to the Director of Product Management in the Hotel group and will be dedicated to a Feature Team that is focused on expanding our hotel site functionality in our Asia Pacific market.&nbsp; He /she needs a strong understanding of the metrics and drivers behind consumer product selection, consumer preferences, patterns and how they contribute to the positioning of our hotel inventory to our customers.&nbsp; The Product Manager is responsible for articulating requirements and the underlying feature value to the Feature Team while providing insight, clarification and guidance on acceptance criteria.&nbsp; He/she is also responsible for prioritizing defects associated with new and existing features as well as leading the post-launch feature analysis to understand the impact of new functionality on customer behavior.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p style="margin: 0px;"><em>Problem Solving and Innovation</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Understands the product vision from the customer perspective and evaluates various approaches to implement solutions</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Provides direction and encourages debate of alternative solutions with Hotel Sourcing, Technology, Operations, Consumer Insights and BI/Reporting</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Drives product design and innovation</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Projects how potential new ideas may play out in the marketplace</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Makes decisions based upon a mixture of analysis, wisdom, experience, and judgment - sometimes with incomplete information and under tight deadlines and pressures</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Continuously looks for process improvements within the product development lifecycle</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Drives resolution on escalated issues</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin: 0px;"><em>Analytical</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lead competitive analysis to determine requirements and to break down features into stories</li>\n<li>Identify approaches for evaluating product success</li>\n<li>Evaluate product release performance against success metrics and customer feedback</li>\n<li>Prioritize feature requirements and defects based on key metrics (customer value, cost, time to market, etc.) and acceptance criteria</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin: 0px;"><em>Technical</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Articulate tangible product requirements in the form of a backlog of features, epics and stories</li>\n<li>Develop functional specifications including use cases, process/workflow, error messages and interface specifications</li>\n<li>Define &ldquo;done&rdquo; in terms of acceptance criteria</li>\n<li>Prioritize stories and defects, enabling transparency into the justifications used</li>\n<li>Manage a single backlog for Feature Team containing stories and defects and modify based on progress and customer value</li>\n<li>Participate in development sprint planning and feature prioritization</li>\n<li>Ensure quality and completeness of the finished product by user acceptance testing and reviewing test cases</li>\n<li>Determine releasable feature milestones based on value to be delivered to customer</li>\n<li>Manage functional production issues for features introduced into the site &ndash; this includes problem identification and monitoring through resolution, using bug-tracking tools and working with internal/external suppliers on data quality</li>\n<li>Support and validate features contained in Feature Team&rsquo;s production releases</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin: 0px;"><em>Communication</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Create and distribute product release&nbsp;communications across the product organization and key stakeholders</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Provide appropriate transition of features from development to product support teams (e.g. Business Operations, Customer Service, Service Operations)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Maintain documentation associated with new features and functionality in the product group&rsquo;s centralized documentation portal</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Communicate health and quality of product delivery throughout development lifecycle to Feature Team Lead, Product Leadership, Solution Architect, Group Manager and other relevant stakeholders</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Own risk identification, mitigation strategies/impact analysis, resolution, and communications to teams and stakeholders</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin: 0px;"><em>Leadership</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mentor junior Product Analysts</li>\n<li>Identify opportunities for sharing subject matter expertise with the broader organization, peers, or more junior product staff</li>\n<li>Periodically participates in product community of practice</li>\n<li>Identifies ways to drive team morale</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">3+ years of product management experience</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;"><strong>Fluent in speaking Mandarin as well as ability to read and write in Chinese</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Strong understanding of Chinese consumer preferences</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">B.S. degree required</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Experience with eCommerce product placement and customer facing display</p>\n</li>\n<li>Successfully demonstrated leadership in product management</li>\n<li>Effective cross-functional leadership</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Knowledge of project management and software development methodologies &ndash; Agile methodology experience a plus</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Travel industry knowledge a plus</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">Software development experience a plus</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style="margin: 0px;">MBA a plus</p>\n</li>\n</ul>', 'https://careers-orbitz.icims.com/jobs/4897/2014-4897/job', '', 5, 232, 2),
(359, 1397751810, '', 'Mandarin Quarterly New York City', 'Media', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="mbs _5pbx userContent" style="margin-bottom: 5px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.38; color: #141823; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;" data-ft="{&quot;tn&quot;:&quot;K&quot;}">\n<p style="margin: 0px; display: inline;"></p>\n</div>', '', 'sonhyy8809@gmail.com', 5, 222, 2),
(360, 1397752316, '', '', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="box-Jobdescription" class="box widget imagine  opened" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; display: block; color: #333333; font-family: ''Ideal Sans SSm A'', ''Ideal Sans SSm B'', ''Trebuchet MS'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 21px; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">\n<div class="body" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 1em; margin: 0px; background-color: white; -webkit-box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0745098) 0px 0px 0px 1px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0745098) 0px 0px 0px 1px;">\n<div id="listing-description" class="description formattedText" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">1966,,,,,,,<br style="color: #58595b; font-family: Tahoma, Helvetica, Arial, sans; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 14px; orphans: auto; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #c7c8ca;" /><br />\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Development Manager:</strong><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>This is a full-time position reporting to the President and Director of Development. If the candidate works out, NCUSCR expects that the position will become permanent at the end of 2014. The prospective candidate will play a vital role in the success of all fundraising initiatives (with emphasis on the gala dinner set for November 10, 2014). S/he should be an experienced, energetic team player, a self-starter who can work independently while the Director of Development is on leave. Excellent project management and communication skills, ability to multi-task, as well previous experience with event planning required.</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Main Responsibilities/Activities</strong></p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">-Cultivate &amp; solicit corporate sponsors and major donors (establish and meet monthly fundraising goals).</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">-Build relationships with key corporate contacts at all levels and in a variety of functions to help advance the partnership.</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">-Develop Gala Dinner outreach lists as well as print and online media materials.</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">-Manage fundraising constituent relationships including tracking systems for current and prospective donors, maintaining accurate and detailed donor records, creating and distributing reports of gifts, activities, contact lists, and writing and sending donor acknowledgments.</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Position Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">Education: Bachelor''s Degree, plus additional related college courses or professional training</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">Years of Experience: 4 years minimum, longer preferred</p>\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.75em;">Skills or Related Knowledge: Directly-related development work including major gifts, sales, fundraiser execution, capital campaign, progressively responsible experience within an organization, strong relationship-management skills, superior communication and interpersonal skills. Degree or coursework in a China-related field, and ability to speak Chinese preferred</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'applications@ncuscr.org', 5, 173, 2),
(361, 1397862211, 'Destination Services Group Reservations Specialist', 'Kuoni', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Department/Function:</span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Destination Services/ Destination Services Group Reservations Specialist</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Location: </span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">New York, NY</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Band/Level: </span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">G10</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Job Profile: </span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Supporting various departments, suppliers in services reservation as a local specialist</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Reporting &amp; Key Relationships:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Customer Service/Destination Services Manager</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Key Activities:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Confirming all non-hotel services for group clients in North and Latin America </span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Ensuring that services are confirmed by the finalization date</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Checking itineraries making sure services are planned correctly</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Maintaining accurate and up-to-date information on all services bookings </span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Liaising with sales staff and suppliers on a daily basis by phone and e-mail </span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Ensuring that all requests/TID&rsquo;s are answered within 24-48hrs of initial request</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Negotiating rates and researching suitable group product for go ahead groups </span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Processing prepayment requests by credit card, check or wire transfer</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Liaising with the data team and Accounts Payable to help resolve rate or service issues and handling accounts queries</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Assisting coordination with complaint booking issues</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Creating and maintaining excellent relationships with our suppliers and ensuring suppliers provide service to our clients in line with GTE contract procedures / guidelines</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Assisting with special projects and all other duties as assigned by Management</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Investigating and answering all queries from suppliers and GTE staff in a timely and accurate manner.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Researching and obtaining resolution to a variety of complicated customer issues</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Providing all information as necessary to operations teams worldwide in the required timeframe.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Understanding international business culture and responding the market requirements</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Complexity:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">The jobholder will be required to work with a variety of queries within established procedures. </span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Changing priorities or differing situation in order to achieve the required results, in compliance with established methods of working.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Work will be allocated but the jobholder will have to consider and agree priorities with those providing the work. At this level the jobholder will be expected to provide appropriate advice, develop relationships and resolve problem with our sales offices and suppliers. </span></p>\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Knowledge, Skills &amp; Experience:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Fluency in Mandarin and English is a must. Fluency in Cantonese or any other language is a plus</span></strong></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Possess excellent written and verbal communication skills</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Organization skills and able to meet deadline</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Must have extensive knowledge of the United States, Canada and Latin America </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Ability to build good relationships with suppliers and customers </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Motivated and a team player with a pro-active attitude </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Ability to work well under pressure</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Must be detail-oriented and organized</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Previous hospitality or travel experience a plus</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Personal Characteristics:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">A driven self-starter who has excellent communication skills, ambitious, understanding culture differences, hardworking, coping with pressure and can proactively solve problems in a dynamic, highly energized environment. </span></p>\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Core Competencies:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Communication</span></span></li>\n<li><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Quality and Commitment</span></span></li>\n<li><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Customer Focus</span></span></li>\n<li><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial;">Team Work and Collaboration</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><strong><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Financial:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Financial &ndash; No budget responsibilities</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size: 10pt;">Staff &ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; Part of a team of 5</span></p>', '', 'hr@gta-travel.com', 5, 105, 2),
(362, 1397845813, 'Assistant Director', ' university of washington', 'Management', 'Seattle, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 47.606209, -122.332069, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table style="margin: 0px 0px 1.4em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 19.5px; vertical-align: middle; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; width: 657px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1">\n<tbody style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\n<tr style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\n<td class="TDRegular" style="margin: 0px; padding: 4px; border: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: normal; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: middle; text-align: left; float: none !important; color: black; background-color: #ffffff; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" colspan="3"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">CIWA has an excellent opportunity for an Assistant Director.</strong><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>The CIWA Assistant Director is responsible for day-to-day management and oversight of CIWA projects, budgets, office, and activities, as well as development of new CIWA projects. The Assistant Director will work with the CIWA D