(366, 1397883632, 'Modeler needed for a bank', 'Major Bank at Buffalo', 'Finance', 'Buffalo, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'Buffalo', 42.886448, -78.878372, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>THIS IS A RARE&nbsp;OPPORTUNITY FOR FRESH STATISTICS GRADUATE TO GET INTO BANKING BUSINESS AS A MODELER.</p>\n<p>PREFER STATISTICS MASTER OR HIGHER, FRESH GRADUATE WELLCOME, BUT sas SKILLS HAS TO BE SUFFICIENT AND MUST BE A QUICK LEARNER BOTH IN PEOPLE SKILL AND TECHNICAL SKILLS.</p>\n<p>MORE THAN ONE POSITION, TECHNICAL HELP FROM A EXPERIENCE MODELR AVAILABLE FOR THESE SPECIFIC POSITIONS.</p>\n<p>NEED TO BE IMMEDIATELY AVAILABLE. ONE YEAR COMMITMENT GUARANTEED, IF PERFORMANCE IS GOOD, LONG TERM POSSIBLE (MAY BE PROVIDED OPPORTUNITY TO JOIN A START-UP COMPANY (BASED IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA, SPECIALIZED IN BANKING SOFTWARE) IF QUALIFIED). $35-45/H. H1B VISA POSSIBLE, BUT NOT QUARANTEED.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'garfield_200200@yahoo.com', 524, 103, 2),
(369, 1398096164, '', 'Baker Tilly', 'Finance', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h2 class="medium" style="margin: 1.5em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; color: #333333; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 21px; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Baker Tilly Virchow Krause&rsquo;s values of integrity, passion and stewardship define us as an organization and an employer. We recognize that our approach, strategy and culture are driven by our people. Their focus and commitment has resulted in Baker Tilly Virchow Krause being ranked as one of the top 20 largest public accounting and advisory firms in the United States and our offices consistently earning &ldquo;best place to work&rdquo; honors. Our people have been fundamental in getting us to where we are today and where we will go in the future.&nbsp;We are seeking an<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">International Assistant</strong><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>to work closely with executives from Baker Tilly affiliates from other nations providing support as they acclimate to various differences in language, the country&rsquo;s culture and Baker Tilly Virchow Krause&rsquo;s culture.&nbsp;<strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It&rsquo;s an exciting time to join Baker Tilly!</strong>&nbsp;Baker Tilly Virchow Krause is ranked as one of the top 20 largest public accounting and advisory firms in the United States. With a staff of more than 1600, Baker Tilly provides a wide range of accounting, tax, assurance and consulting services to premier companies and leading organizations in industries that drive our economy. As an independent member of Baker Tilly International, the world&rsquo;s 8th largest network of accounting firms (with a combined worldwide revenue of $3 billion) we bring our clients and our people access to market-specific knowledge in more than 125 countries.ResponsibilitiesProvide cultural guidance.\n<ul style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Advise, as needed, on appropriate use of the English language.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Advise, as needed, on appropriate cultural customs and behaviors.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Assist in traveling and locating points of interest.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Provides other advice relating to conducting business and living in the United States.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\nProvide high level administrative support to visiting executive.\n<ul style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Contact and respond to high ranking individuals.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Makes decisions on the behalf of the executive as delegated.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Ensure requests for action or information are relayed to the appropriate person for response.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Composes correspondence from minimal or no notation.&nbsp; Handles sensitive and confidential information on a regular basis with discretion.\n<ul style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Correspondence may be in English or in executive&rsquo;s home language.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Handles sensitive and confidential information on a regular basis with discretion</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Screen executive&rsquo;s telephone calls.&nbsp;</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Assist with management and special projects.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Maintains the executive&rsquo;s calendar and travel logistics.<strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n</ul>\nAssist with general office functions.\n<ul style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Opens and distributes mail, schedules and prepares materials for meetings, coordinates collection and preparation of operating reports, such as budget expenditures, and statistical records of performance data.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Maintain paper-based and electronic files.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Assists on projects as needed.<strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n</ul>\nMaintain and expand knowledge base in area of expertise.\n<ul style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Attend courses to develop and keep skills and knowledge current.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Comply with continuing education requirements.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Increase efficiencies, technical ability and interpersonal skills.<strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -- Other duties as assigned.</div>\n<h2 class="medium" style="margin: 1.5em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; color: #333333; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 21px; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\n<ul style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Fluent in Mandarin and English</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Ability to work 30-40 hours a week in July and August and ability to continue to work various hours through September.&nbsp;</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Minimum of one (1) to three (3) years of business experience. Prior experience in a professional services firm preferred.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Ability to work independently with minimal supervision.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Advanced working knowledge of MS Office suite and any other specialized software required to do the job.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Outlook and scheduling experience. Experience with office machines, including facsimile, high speed copier, multi-line phone, dictation equipment (machine/tapes) and 10 key calculators required.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Keen sense of accuracy and attention to detail and ability to follow directions/procedures required. Ability to work in a fast-paced, time sensitive environment with frequent interruptions.</li>\n<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; list-style: disc;">Ability to read, write and speak in visiting executive&rsquo;s home language.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'http://www.moneyjobs.com/jobs/-/J3F1GB6DHKZG35C3792', '', 5, 524, 2),
(370, 1398233165, '', 'BASIS Independent Schools', 'Language', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Primary Job Responsibilities include but are not limited to:</strong><br />1) Teach higher level content than grade standard in an interactive learning environment to deliver exceptional results for all students;<br />2) Tutor students in content-specific knowledge and skills to heighten the trajectory of their academic and career success;<br />3) Implementation of BASIS curriculum by designing effective and creative lessons and assessments to display your passion for the subject and educate students at an internationally competitive level;<br />4) Collaborate with other BASIS teachers to form a community of smart, talented and interesting people who are passionate about their work and readily willing to work in a professional, academic environment; and<br />5) Management of student behavior to foster academic achievement, personal responsibility, intellect and individuality in all students.<br /><br /><strong>Job Qualifications:</strong><br />Minimum Qualifications: A Bachelor&rsquo;s degree and ability to obtain a valid fingerprint clearance are required to teach at BASIS. In addition to a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree, a major (24-30 credit hours) or advanced degree in the teaching subject fulfills the highly qualified requirement. Highly qualified teacher requirements vary by state. In some cases a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree and documentation of passage of a state authorized subject test in the teaching area may fulfill the highly qualified requirement. Coursework or experience in education is not required, nor is certification.<br /><br />Preferred Qualifications: Subject matter postgraduate work (Master&rsquo;s or Ph.D.) is preferred. Together with a high level of educational attainment, a successful applicant will demonstrate strong communication skills in teaching ide