(371, 1398097528, 'Chemist - R&I, Global Talent Program, China', '', 'Engineering', 'Clark, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Clark', 40.627804, -74.312759, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>L&rsquo;Or&eacute;al was established in 1909 by visionary scientist, Eugene Schueller, and is committed to progressive research and development, state-of-the-art manufacturing, quality products, and making beauty accessible to everyone around the world. L&rsquo;Oreal is the #1 beauty company in the world investing approximately 3.3% of its consolidated sales into its world-wide research facilities while filing 600+ patents and launching over 500 new products each year. Our Research and Innovation team pushes the boundaries of science to invent and perfect innovative, high performance cosmetic products to meet the diverse needs of men and women all over the world. <br /><br />Through our L&rsquo;Oreal R&amp;I Global Talent Program we are committed to recruit outstanding scientific talent to help us reach even greater heights in our Research &amp; Innovation center in China. If you are currently a Chinese student completing graduate research studies in the USA with at least two years of relevant research experience you could be eligible. The components of the program are: <br /><br /><strong>Option 1</strong>: You will be required to commit to: &middot; Start in the US for an assignment from 6 and up to 12 months maximum during your OPT period. &middot; During the time in the US, you are placed in a Formulation Lab or Applied Research Lab (Skin Care, Hair Care, Hair Color, Color Cosmetics or Fragrance) to learn procedures, raw materials, systems, &amp; processes. &middot; At the end of the US assignment, you will be assigned back to China for a local full-time opportunity. <br /><br /><strong>Option 2</strong>: &middot; You will be assigned directly in China to an open position. <br /><br /><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong>: <br />&middot; Masters or PhD degree in Chemistry (Physical, Polymer, Organic, Analytical), BioChemistry, Materials Science completed between December 2013 or June 2014 &middot; Previous internship experience a must <br />&middot; Post-doc experience or two years relevant research experience a plus <br />&middot; Demonstrated leadership and project management skills <br />&middot; Must be creative, analytical and have excellent communication/interpersonal skills <br />&middot; Must have a desire to work in a fast-paced, dynamic and challenging work environment and possess strong computer skills <br />&middot; <strong>Must be fully bilingual (English/Mandarin) written and spoken</strong> <br />&middot; An eye for color and a passion for art and science <br />&middot; Geographical flexibility and openness to international assignments are a must <br />&middot; Interested candidates must agree to relocation to China post-graduation or within end of employment assignment in the USA <br />&middot; <strong>Must be an F1 Visa holder</strong><br /><br /></p>', 'https://careers.peopleclick.com/careerscp/client_thebodyshop/loreal_ext/jobDetails.do?functionName=getJobDetail&jobPostId=70270&localeCode=en-us', '', 5, 160, 2),
