ted field, or equivalent experience as determined by management.</span></span></p>\n<p style="line-height: normal; background-color: white; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #333333; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 12.0pt; line-height: 13.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #333333; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;">REQUIRED:</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #333333;"><br /></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Speaking&nbsp;<strong>Chinese</strong>&nbsp;was needed.</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #333333;"><br /><br /></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 12.0pt; line-height: 13.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #333333; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;">PREFERRED:</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #333333;"><br /><br /><span style="background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;">&bull;Knowledge in real estate development or construction field was plus. </span></span></p>', '', 'joy@homeparadise.com', 5, 110, 2),
(421, 1398702801, 'Program Coordinator', 'US-China Business Training Center', 'Management', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span lang="EN">Are you interested in international affairs and promoting US and China exchanges?&nbsp;&nbsp;Do you have a curious mind and an innovative spirit?&nbsp;&nbsp;The US-China Business Training Center is seeking a creative Program Coordinator to become an integral team member of the Training Department.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Program Coordinator will provide support for designing quality training and enrichment programs in diverse topics and in facilitating academic, business and cultural exchanges.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">Responsibilities will include:&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">researching industry topics and trends</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">identifying and contacting potential hosts and speakers</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">coordinating multiple facets of programs with an international focus</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">evaluating delegation and host feedback of training programs</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">providing overall administration and program support for the Training Department</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">Qualifications</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Requires a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a related field or an equivalent combination of education and/or experience that demonstrates knowledge and interest</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Project or program management experience working in a complex, fast-paced professional environment</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Excellent interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills to work with diverse American and Chinese audiences</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Ability to work independently in a team environment</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Excellent organizational skills</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Knowledge of and/or experience in China is preferred</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">Additional Information</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Must be eligible to work legally in the US</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN">-<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="EN">Working knowledge in Chinese language is preferred, but not required</span></p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Program-Coordinator-Job-City-of-Industry-CA-US-133361237.aspx', '', 5, 317, 2),
