(391, 1398295550, '', 'Bank of the West', 'Service', 'Arcadia, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Arcadia', 34.139729, -118.035347, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p><strong>Position Summary</strong></p>\n<p>Provides high quality customer service by meeting the needs of customers in an efficient and friendly manner.&nbsp;Identifies sales and cross-selling opportunities. Performs routine office and clerical duties.&nbsp;&nbsp;Maintains operational quality and standards.&nbsp;&nbsp;Acts as the customers'' first "point-of-contact" with the Bank.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This description applies to three levels (Job Codes 1673, 1672, 1670, &amp; 4299)&nbsp;&nbsp;Level assignment is based on a variety of factors including, but not limited to, scope and complexity of transactions and experience and expertise of customer service representative. (Job code 4299 may occasionally perform MLO duties and will require approval from Regional Managers.)</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p><strong>Position Accountabilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ensures positive public perceptions of the Bank by extending a courteous greeting and welcome to customers and visitors.&nbsp;&nbsp;Provides accurate and timely customer service.</li>\n<li>Supports the Bank&rsquo;s sales objectives and campaigns by cross-selling basic products, or by referring customers to other Bank employees responsible for closing sales.</li>\n<li>Adheres to Bank&rsquo;s security and audit procedures.</li>\n<li>Protects the Bank''s financial interests by controlling and balancing the assigned cash drawer and negotiable items received/disbursed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Maintains acceptable balancing record per established standards.</li>\n<li>Processes customer transactions efficiently and accurately.&nbsp;&nbsp;Follow policies/procedures to minimize losses.</li>\n<li>Answers telephone inquiries.&nbsp;&nbsp;Directs questions to appropriate Branch personnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;Responds to customer mail inquiries.&nbsp;&nbsp;Researches/resolves customer problems.</li>\n<li>Performs routine office and clerical duties (i.e., filing signature cards; preparing bank bag for pickup; night deposit, ATM custodian, etc.).</li>\n<li>Performs other duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Required Education or Equivalent Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>High School or equivalent combination of training and experience</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Required Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>0 &ndash; 1 year teller or cash handling experience (level I)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Field of Experience</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Basic knowledge of bank products and services (level I)</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Representative Duties</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Process Customer/ATM/Night Drop Deposits</li>\n<li>Cash Checks/Savings Withdrawals</li>\n<li>Process Consumer Loan Payments</li>\n<li>Process Credit Card Cash Advances</li>\n<li>Process TT &amp; L Payments</li>\n<li>Sell Travelers Cheques, Money Orders, Cashiers Checks</li>\n<li>Sell and Redeem Savings Bonds</li>\n<li>Place Stop Payments, Special Instructions, and Deposit Holds</li>\n<li>CTR/MIL Completion</li>\n<li>Complete Wire Transfer Form</li>\n<li>Safe Deposit Entrance Procedures</li>\n<li>Filing (Signature Cards/Reports)</li>\n<li>Prepare Bank Work Bag for Pick Up</li>\n<li>Product Knowledge</li>\n<li>Referral Tracking System (RTS)</li>\n<li>IS View</li>\n<li>E-Vision</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Administrative/Technical Skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Customer service skills</li>\n<li>Answers telephone and screens calls</li>\n<li>Balance figures</li>\n<li>Calculator</li>\n<li>Filing and typing documents</li>\n<li>Operate a ten-key adding machine</li>\n<li>Perform math and analysis</li>\n<li>Photocopier</li>\n<li>Research information</li>\n<li>Use fax machine</li>\n<li>Detail orientation</li>\n<li>Computer terminal</li>\n</ul>', 'https://botw.taleo.net/careersection/external/jobdetail.ftl?job=48943&lang=en', '', 5, 162, 2),
(392, 1398307538, ' ', 'Belkin', 'Engineering', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>What you&rsquo;ll do </strong></p>\n<p>As a <strong><em>Senior Embedded Hardware Engineer - Networking</em></strong>, you will help architect, design, and develop embedded hardware and firmware based systems for use in the latest Belkin, Linksys, and WeMo brand consumer and business networking products, including wired and wireless routers, gateways, range extenders, switches, and smart home devices.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Contribute to product line roadmaps as well as product ideas, definitions, specifications, feasibility, and schedules. Collaborate with electrical, firmware, software mechanical and manufacturing engineers, product developers and other engineering teammates located in Playa Vista, Irvine and globally. Lead, oversee, and review design work done by engineering and manufacturing partners in Asia.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You will have current system and circuit level engineering experience with latest networking chipsets from Broadcom, Qualcomm, Marvell, Mediatek, Realtek and other industry leaders. Oversee and assist our partners with the design, debugging, troubleshooting, and documenting of high speed mixed signal hardware including 32bit microcontrollers with high speed memory and I/O interfaces including gigabit Ethernet, USB3, and SATA. Participate in design reviews of the overall architecture, block diagrams, chipset selection, schematics, BOMs and PCB designs for products built with high-speed, mixed signal multilayer PCBAs. Provide leadership for creating and managing power and heat rise budgets during product planning and development. RF experience with 2.4 and 5GHz Wi-Fi, Zigbee, and Bluetooth radios and antennas is a plus.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You will also be familiar with new product introduction activities as part of transition to manufacturing. This position requires a self-starting individual who can deliver on commitments made without a lot of guidance, solving problems with creative out-of-the-box thinking tempered by experience and overall corporate objectives.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Excellent command of oral and written English is essential. Command of Mandarin is a plus.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>How you&rsquo;ll do it </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lead, oversee, direct, and/or review the design, analysis, and testing of residential and commercial wireless and wired networking systems built with single and multicore 32 bit MIPS and ARM embedded microcontrollers and SOCs that use on chip and external high-speed RAM and flash memory as well as USB 3, Ethernet, SPI, JTAG, and other standard and custom I/O interfaces.</li>\n<li>Work closely with Firmware and Software Architects and developers to create both standard and custom solutions for new and innovative embedded system based router designs.</li>\n<li>Work closely with outsource engineering, manufacturing and other external resources and represent Belkin interests on-site as part of an engineering team.</li>\n<li>Occasional domestic and international travel.</li>\n<li>Work closely with internal Sourcing and Supply Chain partners and chipset vendors to identify, qualify and recommend new chipsets having strategic value for use in new products.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Represent Engineering&rsquo;s interest in the identification, qualification, and selection of new ODM and JDM manufacturing partners.</li>\n<li>Work closely with Program and Product mangers to create product specifications and development schedules.</li>\n<li>Design compliance to EMI/EMC, and Safety regulations.</li>\n<li>Prepare, present and lead peer to peer and cross functional design review meetings</li>\n<li>Commitment to working independently and in a team environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>What you&rsquo;ll need </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Requires a Bachelor of Science degree, or may have a Master of Science degree, in Electrical Engineering from a four year college or university, or equivalent combination of education &amp; experience.</li>\n<li>Employees entering this job typically have a minimum of ten years of directly related experience in embedded systems design and development with a demonstrated record of leadership, and a proven track record in designing and shipping microcontroller based wireless networking hardware and firmware using Internet Protocols.</li>\n<li>Demonstrate working knowledge of cross-functional and related technical areas such as mechanical design, component location and sourcing, quality techniques, regulatory compliance.</li>\n<li>Ability to prepare and present technical material to a wide audience including nontechnical clientele will be helpful.</li>\n<li>Outstanding interpersonal and leadership skills.</li>\n<li>Previous experience supervising others.</li>\n<li>Proven analytical problem-solving ability.</li>\n<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>What you&rsquo;re getting into</strong></p>\n<p>We&rsquo;ve got big collaborative spaces for your big ideas, so bring an open mind and leave your suit in the closet. We all are committed to creating unique and rewarding consumer experiences. Everyone is interested in succeeding &ndash; for the team, for themselves and for the business. Cross-functionally and across the company, everyone has common goals and aspires to be their best.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You will learn something new or at least look at things differently every day. There are so many smart and creative people around that you&rsquo;ll be motivated to pursue the ideal.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Team spirit is infectious. Belkin is an extremely open workplace, where communication is essential. Not every idea will be accepted, but you&rsquo;ll be asked for your point of view. Innovation thrives on multiple and varied levels. At Belkin we challenge conventional wisdom and refuse to accept that something cannot be done.</p>', 'http://www.belkin.com/us/careers/11850/', '', 5, 98, 2);
