(398, 1398310026, '', 'Lakeside School', 'Language', 'Seattle, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 47.606209, -122.332069, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Lakeside School, an independent coeducational day school located in North Seattle, is currently recruiting for a<strong> part-time Mandarin Chinese Teacher </strong>for our Upper School starting with the 2014-2015 school year (beginning in mid to late August, 2014). At Lakeside School, we are focused on developing global citizens, educational excellence, and building a diverse and inclusive community.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Responsibilities</span></strong></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">The Mandarin Chinese Teacher position, reporting to the Upper School Language Department Head, will join a department that consists of 10 faculty members, teaching approximately 34 language sections each year (Latin, French, Spanish &amp; Mandarin Chinese), with a maximum class size of 18 students per class. &nbsp;&nbsp;Specific responsibilities include:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Classroom instruction, with an emphasis on building oral proficiency, promoting students&rsquo; ability to read and write in the language, and exploring the culture and history of China;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Written evaluations of students four times during the year;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Maintain class webpage on Haiku on a regular basis;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Acting as a co-advisor to a group of eight to ten Upper School students;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Conferences with students and colleagues;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Active participation in the work of the Languages Department on curriculum development and pedagogy;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Attending department and faculty meetings as scheduled;</span></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Active participation in the life of the school community.&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Requirements and Qualifications</span></strong></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Successful candidates will hold a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree (Master&rsquo;s preferred) in Chinese or a related field and should possess native or near-native proficiency in both Mandarin and English (must be able to interact with colleagues, students and families proficiently in English). Candidates with experience teaching Mandarin in a high school or late middle-school level using communicative and task-based pedagogical practices are preferred. Also, candidates should have experience working collaboratively on a teaching team. The ideal candidate will have experience living in China or Taiwan; be computer literate; and proficient on a PC platform.&nbsp; Candidates must satisfactorily complete a nationwide criminal background check.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Compensation and Benefits</span></strong></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Lakeside School is committed to attracting and retaining outstanding faculty candidates who will add to the racial, cultural, economic and gender diversity of our school community.&nbsp; We provide a competitive compensation package which includes, but is not limited to, a monthly salary, excellent health and welfare benefits, access to funds for professional development, housing down payment assistance program, and school-provided lunches.&nbsp; Additionally, Lakeside offers Faculty and Staff opportunities to participate in non-classroom teaching programs such as Global Service Learning, Summer School, coaching, etc., for extra compensation.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Additional Information</span></strong></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">Lakeside School was founded in 1919, and currently enrolls 811 students in grades 5 through 12 from diverse ethnic, racial, religious, and economic backgrounds.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: times new roman,times,serif;">The School&rsquo;s Mission and the shared commitment of all Lakeside employees is to develop in intellectually capable young people the creative minds, healthy bodies, and ethical spirits needed to contribute wisdom, compassion, and leadership to a global society. We provide a rigorous, dynamic academic program through which effective educators lead students to take responsibility for learning.&nbsp; We are committed to sustaining a school in which individuals representing diverse cultures and experiences instruct one another in the meaning and value of community and in the joy and importance of lifelong learning. <br /></span></span></p>', 'http://ch.tbe.taleo.net/CH04/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=LAKESIDESCHOOL&cws=1&rid=512', '', 5, 196, 2),
(399, 1398310822, '', 'American Kidz Academy Management', 'Language', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Cambria;">Come join our growing team!<br /><br />The American Kidz Academy provides an Elite Urban Education&reg; curriculum that focuses on social, emotional, physical and intellectual growth for children six weeks to six years.<br /><br />We are looking for Bi-lingual teachers for our Enrichment programs for our pre-school program.&nbsp; Bi-linugal qualifications include teachers in who are fluent in the following:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Cambria;">&nbsp;Mandarin/English</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Cambria;">Sign Language</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">Primary Responsibilities</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Create and develop lesson plans in accordance with curriculum objectives that demonstrate development and our philosophy</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Meet the emotional, social, physical and cognitive needs of each child</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Maintain a healthy and fun classroom that promotes development and growth</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Foster a team environment by working with AKA team members by making sure center operations are maintained at high standards, helping with different age groups as needed, and sharing ideas with other team members to ensure the best curriculum for AKA students</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Stay in compliance with Health and Safety standards</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Create weekly newsletters to correspond with parents</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Build strong relationships with the children and the parents by engaging and caring for the children in daily activities and pleasantly greeting and communicating with parents on a daily basis</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-size: 12px;"><br /><strong>Qualifications</strong></span><span style="font-size: 12px;"><br /></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Fluency in English as well Spanish, Manadarin or Sign Language</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Bachelors degee in TESOL preferred<br /></span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">Experience in teaching second languages to children ages 3-6 years</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 12px;">At least nine credits in early childhood preferred<br /></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-size: 12px;">We offer competitive salaries and benefit packages.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Mandarin-Early-Childhood-Teacher-Job-Chicago-IL-US-133163242.aspx', '', 5, 163, 2),
(400, 1398313459, '', 'Ferrante', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.714352, -74.005974, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Manhattan-based, multidisciplinary law firm with strong international orientation is seeking an articulate and outgoing individual. The duties include answering multi-line phone, greet clientele, organizing legal documents, photocopying, file maintenance, inventory of office supplies, project research, providing administrative support to the firm, and other clerical tasks.</p>\n<p>This individual must be proficient in MS Office (Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint), ability to multi-task, strong oral and written communication, must be detail oriented, and interact with a variety of people in a fast-paced friendly environment. 1 year Administrative experience within a law firm is preferred but not required.</p>\n<p>Speak and write fluent Mandarin is a plus. Candidates who meet these qualifications should e-mail a resume and salary requirements to <a style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;" href="mailto:recruitment@ferrantelawfirm.com">recruitment@ferrantelawfirm.com</a></p>', '', '', 5, 112, 2),
(401, 1398314179, 'Product Planning Manager', 'Amtec', 'Management', 'Cypress, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Cypress', 33.816959, -118.037285, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div>\n<div>Amtec is seeking a Product Planning Manager to work for a global leader in consumer electronics, located in Cypress, CA.<br /><br /> Responsibilities:<br /><br /> &bull;&nbsp; Supporting duties as required by Product Planning group leader<br /><br /> &bull;&nbsp; Coordination Management<br /><br /> o&nbsp; Product Planning Strategy support, with management.<br /> o&nbsp; Product Line-up creation with management.<br /> o&nbsp; Marketing / Technical Report and Studies as required.<br /> o&nbsp; Coordination of efforts with company affiliates, vendors, partners.<br /><br /> &bull;&nbsp; Product Planning<br /><br /> o&nbsp; Category / product planning for responsible product lines.<br /> o&nbsp; Competitive product evaluation, benchmarking.<br /> o&nbsp; Feature and development specification.<br /> o&nbsp; Creation of related materials.<br /><br /> &bull;&nbsp; Product Development Support<br /><br /> o&nbsp; Support of Product Development process and adherence to Product Development Policy.<br /> o&nbsp; Vendor discovery and relations.<br /> o&nbsp; Business plan creation and coordination.<br /> o&nbsp; Design Review leadership and support as appropriate.<br /> o&nbsp; Other Product Development Support as required.<br /><br /> &bull;&nbsp; Marketing / Retail Admin Support<br /><br /> o&nbsp; Support in creation of promotional materials for Marketing / Admin&nbsp; departments including, but not limited to; catalogs, price lists, advertisements, promotional videos, sales handbooks, flyers.<br /> o&nbsp; Preparation and presentation of materials for customers as required.<br /> o&nbsp; Show support as required.<br /> o&nbsp; Customer activity and research as required.<br /><br /> Other duties as determined by company management.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<di