(420, 1398702465, '', 'Michael Chen, CPA', 'Finance', 'Alhambra, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Alhambra', 34.095287, -118.127014, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="jobwrapper">\n<div id="jobcopy">\n<div id="jobBodyContent"><span id="TrackingJobBody">ACCOUNTANT: Review personal and business financial records and prepare periodic financial statements, income tax returns, payroll tax returns &amp; summaries for client''s financial position; interpret US and State Tax Law and regulations to clients in Mandarin or Cantonese; provide bookkeeping training. </span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span id="TrackingJobBody">Req: Bachelor focus on Accounting + exp. w / "Quickbook," "Taxact," "Lacerte," &amp; "Laserfiche;" bilingual in English, <strong>Mandarin and Cantonese</strong>. $5,093/mo. </span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span id="TrackingJobBody">Job &amp; Interview: Alhambra, CA. </span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span id="TrackingJobBody">Contact: Michael Chen, Michael Chen, CPA, A Professional Accountancy Corporation, 33 E. Valley Blvd., Ste. 217, Alhambra, CA 91801</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'michaelchencpa@hotmail.com', 44, 159, 2),
(422, 1398703421, 'Component Engineer', 'GoPro', 'Engineering', 'San Mateo, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Mateo', 37.562992, -122.325523, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div>GoPro is seeking a top tier candidate for the Component Engineer role. As Component Engineer you will have responsibility for identifying, qualifying, documenting and releasing components from a variety of commodities for our line of products. This position will provide support to engineering and operations by providing specification review and ensuring the accuracy of our PLM system. You will be responsible for finding alternate sourcing and tracking component qualification. In addition you will be responsible for coordinating, evaluating and tracking all component PCNs and FA reports, implementing corrective actions and assessing the risk to projects.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div>In this fast paced and dynamic organization it will be necessary for you to drive the component selection process and perform your work in a consultative manner as the subject matter expert. The position requires strong communication skills in an individual that is self-directed and capable of meeting aggressive schedules. Must possess exceptional organizational skills and be capable of managing several projects in parallel.&nbsp;</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong>Responsibilities</strong></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identifying, qualifying, documenting and releasing components from a variety of commodities for our line of products</li>\n<li>Support engineering and operations by providing specification review and assisting in the qualification of second sources</li>\n<li>Coordinate component failure analysis with component manufacturers</li>\n<li>Responsible for coordinating, evaluating and tracking all component PCNs and FA reports, implementing corrective actions and assessing the risk to projects</li>\n<li>Reviewing all components released to our PLM system for accuracy and working with our manufacturing partners to ensure accurate synchronization with GoPro&rsquo;s PLM system&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Recommend up-screening, if required, to qualify device to a more rigorous environment than original device specification.</li>\n<li>Recommend alternative part if specified part is unavailable or if it cannot be made to meet requirement</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div><strong>Requirements</strong></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>BSEE, MSEE</li>\n<li>5+ years relevant experience as a Component Engineer</li>\n<li>Must be capable of coordinating cross-functionally with internal teams and ODMs/CMs to resolve issues pertaining to component selection and use</li>\n<li>Must have understanding of the fundamentals of electrical testing and the use of tools and test equipment (e.g. supplies/generators, meters, signal analyzers, logic analyzers, oscilloscopes, etc.)</li>\n<li>Should be knowledgeable on a wide range of semiconductor components including analog ICs, digital ICs, memory, timing devices, and microprocessors</li>\n<li>Complete understanding and working knowledge of engineering documentation (e.g. schematics, component data sheets, footprints, RoHS, etc.) and standard document control practices (e.g. ECRs, ECOs, MCOs, Deviations, etc.)</li>\n<li>Strong problem solving skills</li>\n<li>Ability to interface effectively across organizational and geographic boundaries</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills, both written and oral</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal and planning skills</li>\n<li>Highly proficient with Excel and related Microsoft Products</li>\n<li>Experience working with Arena or Agile PLM</li>\n<li>Fluent in English</li>\n<li>(Desired) <strong>Fluent in Mandarin</strong></li>\n</ul>', 'http://gopro.com/careers/?gnk=job&gni=8acda1104096878a0140c600d8ee77ec', '', 5, 95, 2),
(423, 1398720159, 'Associate ()', '', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '', '', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1598.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Overview</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The RMB Initiative has been established as a group-wide strategic priority for HSBC.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">With the goal of becoming the leading international bank for RMB services in the Americas, Senior Management has recently given ultimate responsibility to the CF COO and Business Development team to lead this front for both Banking &amp; Capital Financing, across the continent.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">As the RMB Initiative in the Americas continues to grow in importance and scope, there is a need for a dedicated junior support to help lead the day-to-day articulation, coordination and execution of the China-related business development strategy in the region. This position is key to help avoid the risk of losing a front-runner position to win RMB business, as well as ensuring we establish the necessary management framework and equip RMs with the tools necessary to succeed in an increasingly competitive environment.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></span></div>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Development of China-related business</span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Support new RMB-specific business opportunities &ndash;particularly those connected to new trial zones, regulations and product solutions</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Conduct a comprehensive market-sizing study, with the ultimate goal of identifying both existing and new clients with the largest overall RMB opportunities and specific scenarios with each</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Pursue opening of relevant regional desks with Banking Multis team in Shanghai, and determine appropriate set up (i.e., one Americas desk, NAM/LAM desks, US or Brazil desks, etc.)</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Develop a comprehensive strategy to extract synergies and expand the US$460M of existing revenue being generated from Americas clients in China and Chinese satellites (especially Hong Kong) and US$30M of exiting Chinese inbound revenues</span></li>\n<li>\n<p>Help ensure Americas&rsquo; participation in broader RMB Internationalization Strategy, interacting on a daily basis with colleagues in London and HBCN</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Potentially participate in client-facing interactions &ndash;once competency is fully establishes- that RMs can leverage&nbsp; Take a client-facing role in select meetings where appropriate</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Management and execution of the RMB Initiative</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;Create an Americas RMB committee of appropriate stakeholders that meets at appropriate intervals and act as secretary to drive agenda towards productive sessions and meaningful output</li>\n<li>Establish strong relationships with RMB teams in mainland China and other offshore centres, chiefly Hong Kong</li>\n<li>Produce MI that adequately tracks overall progress on growing RMB revenues, as well as specific opportunities that have been identified and signed-up to</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Education, Communication and Marketing</span></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Keep abreast of relevant China related news for the Americas client base, leveraging such information to drive specific incremental revenue opportunities and disseminating to bankers as appropriate</li>\n<li>Coordinate external and internal RMB related events, ensuring high engagement and high impact through careful planning and preparation</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Leverage and modify existing training materials, as well as supplement with new materials as necessary, to empower RMs to pitch RMB business to clients with knowledge and credibility</span></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1656.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1672.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel">&nbsp;</span>\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Essential Experience</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Post-graduate or experienced hire career opportunity</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Demonstrable 3-5 years of relevant work experience necessary</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Post-graduate degree in general management / business / finance from a top international program &nbsp;highly desirable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Previous work experience in a client-facing or strategy role in the financial services industry or a top-consulting firm also highly desirable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Familiarity of working in a client-facing role or product team facing Chinese customers strongly preferable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">An understanding of the Chinese economy, its financial sector and related regulatory change also preferable&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Previous experience working with HSBC -particularly in GBM- considered a plus</span></li>\n<li><strong><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Proficiency in Mandarin essential</span></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><strong>Essential Skills/Competencies</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Strategic mind-set</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Superior interpersonal ability, and ability to influence outcomes without formal authority&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Strong verbal/presentation and written communication skills</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Ability to win support and interact diplomatically with a diverse group of senior stakeholders and business partners</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Analytical ability and attention to detail</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Track record of &nbsp;working independently and proven ability to prioritise work under pressure</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Flexibility and pragmatism to cope with abrupt changes to plans</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Willingness and interest to travel occasionally outside of their main work location</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://hsbc.taleo.net/careersection/external/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en_GB&job=263226', '', 5, 267, 2),
(424, 1398721096, 'Contract Chinese Editor', 'CORESTAFF Services', 'Language', 'Seattle, WA, United States', 'United States', 'Washington', 'Seattle', 47.606209, -122.332069, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>CORESTAFF&nbsp;Services&nbsp;is&nbsp;seeking&nbsp;a&nbsp;contract&nbsp;Editor&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;long&nbsp;term&nbsp;contract&nbsp;positions<br />for&nbsp;a&nbsp;large&nbsp;internet&nbsp;client&nbsp;located&nbsp;in&nbsp;downtown&nbsp;Seattle.&nbsp;You&nbsp;must&nbsp;be&nbsp;proficient&nbsp;in<br />applying&nbsp;DITA&nbsp;structure&nbsp;to&nbsp;documentation&nbsp;and&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;background&nbsp;in&nbsp;technical&nbsp;writing,<br />editing,&nbsp;and&nbsp;information&nbsp;design.&nbsp;You&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;working&nbsp;with&nbsp;complex&nbsp;content&nbsp;sets<br />involving&nbsp;conditions&nbsp;and&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;output&nbsp;destinations,&nbsp;reviewing/editing&nbsp;content<br />produced&nbsp;by&nbsp;others,&nbsp;and&nbsp;providing&nbsp;education&nbsp;and&nbsp;mentoring&nbsp;on&nbsp;our&nbsp;new&nbsp;XML/CMS<br />authoring&nbsp;environment.&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;3&nbsp;month&nbsp;contract&nbsp;paying&nbsp;up&nbsp;to&nbsp;$27/hr.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&shy;Fluent&nbsp;Chinese&nbsp;language&nbsp;skills&nbsp;required</li>\n<li>DITA</li>\n<li>XML</li>\n<li>Strong&nbsp;time&nbsp;management&nbsp;skills</li>\n<li>Strong&nbsp;communication&nbsp;skills&shy;</li>\n</ul>', 'https://ess.impellam.com/job/JO000007926', '', 5, 205, 2),
(425, 1398721690, 'Entry Level IT/Marketing Position', 'iGavel Auctions', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.705631, -73.978004, '', '', NULL, 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="Content" class="centered Content">\n<div class="Classifieds">\n<div id="ClassifiedsContent">\n<div class="ListingPage">\n<div class="Description">Seeking an entry-level college graduate for a position working with the IT and marketing departments for a premier fine art and antiques auction house.</div>\n<div class="Description">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="Description">Duties include:<br /><br />&bull; Updating and maintaining various web presences, including auction content<br />&bull; Client relations and technical support for buyers and sellers<br />&bull; Graphic design for advertising and marketing purposes<br />&bull; IT/Systems support for a Mac-based office and Filemaker database system<br /><br />A high degree of knowledge of HTML/CSS, Photoshop and InDesign a must. PHP/Javascript, Applescript, and Filemaker a plus. This position will report to the Director of Media and Technology. Computer Science, Marketing, Graphic Design, or Art History degree preferred. Must be a hard and versatile worker. Experience with auction houses, art galleries, or direct client relations a plus. <strong>Chinese speaking (Mandarin or Cantonese) a plus</strong>.</div>\n<div class="DescriptionLabel">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class="DescriptionLabel">Application Instructions</div>\n<div class="Description">Please email with a cover letter, a copy of your resume, and two references</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', '', 'customerrelations@igavelauctions.com', 5, 199, 2),
