(427, 1398788734, 'LAX Premium Services Concierge Representative', 'American Airline', 'Service', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div align="center"><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em>American Airlines is seeking candidates for part-time<br />Premium Services Concierge Representative (Mandarin Speaker Required) to work at Los Angeles International Airport.<br />Comprehensive Benefit Package provided and airline travel privileges at an hourly rate of $15.67 USD for the first thirty (30) days and $10.91 USD thereafter.<br /></em></span></strong></div>\n<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em>&nbsp;</em></span></strong></p>\n<div class="large-12 columns nopadding description-body">\n<div>The Premium Services Concierge Representative provides superior hospitality, excellent customer service, extensive ticketing and problem resolution for our premium guests in all areas covered by the Premium Services department including Admirals Club, Flagship/Premium Lounges, ConciergeKey, Five Star and Executive Center locations. &nbsp;Will also be responsible for in-house Concierge Services. &nbsp;Acts as the "Face" of American Airlines and&nbsp;<strong>one</strong>world products.&nbsp; While working in all areas of Premium Services which includes, but is not limited to Admirals Clubs, Premiums Lounges and ConciergeKey/Five Star, provides enhanced, extraordinary services in a positive, enthusiastic, courteous and friendly manner to any visiting member or guest. &nbsp;Will perform comprehensive domestic and international ticketing functions, day of and future date ticketing. &nbsp;Manage guest needs during off-schedule operations, including reroute travel itineraries.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Concierge Services will assist guests/customers with destination features, special events, restaurant recommendations, cars, hotels and sightseeing. &nbsp;Proactively assists guests/customers utilizing mobile technology on concourse and within lounges. &nbsp;Provide assistance with operational functions in all areas of Premium Services and work closely with Customer Services, Sales and Marketing. &nbsp;Utilize successful customer service techniques by listening and showing interest with guest''s concerns and/or needs and taking the initiative to proactively prevent customer service failures and be observant for service deficiencies. &nbsp;Promote Admirals Club/American services and products to members and guests. &nbsp;Remain current on all departmental and applicable AA products, services, features and marketing promotions with ability to speak to value of benefits while identifying potential new business involving corporate and leisure guests and refer leads to sales and/or marketing. &nbsp;Be well-versed in entire suite of Small Medium Enterprise (SME) products to demonstrate knowledge and identify leads for follow-up.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Expertise in JointBusiness and&nbsp;<strong>one</strong>world airline policies, procedures with ability to assist customers with policies and benefits in order to proactively develop local relationships to provide assistance to customers of JointBusiness partner airlines and&nbsp;<strong>one</strong>world airline.&nbsp; Participates regularly with various internal departments helping to support and deliver their goals and initiatives. &nbsp;Engages in required and rigorous hospitality and service training. &nbsp;At Executive Center locations may make conference room bookings and performs all Executive Center duties, including assistance with airline transactions.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class="large-12 columns nopadding qualifications-header">\n<h2 class="large-title">Qualifications</h2>\n</div>\n<div class="large-12 columns nopadding qualifications-body">\n<ul>\n<li>Mandarin Speaker Required (will be tested)</li>\n<li>High School diploma or GED</li>\n<li>Must be able to read, write, fluently speak and understand the English language</li>\n<li>Bilingual language skills required in some locations</li>\n<li>Sabre proficiency preferred</li>\n<li>Prior field experience preferred</li>\n<li>Prior customer hospitality experience required</li>\n<li>Must be well-groomed with a professional appearance</li>\n<li>Strong organizational and administrative skills required</li>\n<li>Excellent salesmanship skills/interpersonal skills with ability to interact effectively with all levels of management and public contact</li>\n<li>Ability to work under pressure, handle a multitude of projects concurrently while paying close attention to detail and customer service</li>\n<li>Actively demonstrate extraordinary customer service and customer engagement in an environment of hospitality</li>\n<li>Ability to assume various passenger services duties and functions within the realm of Premium Services Rep tour of duty - including but not limited to ATO, ticket lift, baggage services, Customer Services Manager</li>\n<li>Bar service preferred</li>\n<li>PC experience preferred</li>\n<li>Required to complete a variety of administrative reports detailing club sales, liquor controls, budget tracking</li>\n<li>Ability to work irregular and/or extended hours, including weekends and holidays</li>\n<li>Must fulfill FAA criminal background checks to qualify for unescorted access privileges to airport security identification display areas (SIDA)</li>\n<li>Must be able to secure appropriate airport authority and/or US Customs security badges</li>\n<li>Must report to work on a regular and timely basis</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'http://careers.aa.com/en/ac/jobpost/4671', '', 5, 292, 2),
(428, 1398788840, '', 'East West Bank', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="bodytext">\n<p>East West Bank is seeking a Full Time Customer Service Representative (CSR). The Customer Service Representative must be able to perform in a fast-paced, high volume capacity with face-to-face interaction with customers in a banking center. The CSR is the frontline representative who processes transactions and introduces bank&rsquo;s products/services at the teller line.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Duties include, but are not limited to:</strong></p>\n<span class="bodytext"><span class="bodytext"><br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Cashing checks, processing deposits, withdrawals, transfers and loan payments&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Documenting larger deposits using Currency Transaction Reports&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Identifying and selling East West Bank products and services beneficial to customer needs&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Addressing customer questions/concerns referring to appropriate internal resources for resolution&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Identifying fraudulent activity to prevent potential losses to the Bank&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Developing new customer relationships and opening new accounts for customers</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="largeheaders">Job Requirements</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Qualifications/Requirements:</strong></p>\n<span class="bodytext"><span class="bodytext"><br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>At least 6 months of recent customer service experience &lsquo;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>At least 6 months of recent cash handling experience&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bilingual Mandarin and Cantonese preferred&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Previous teller and new accounts experience in a banking institution a plus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Excellent customer service skills&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Proficiency in Word and Excel&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Must have reliable transportation&nbsp;</li>\n<li>High School Diploma required or equivalent, Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree preferred</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/jobs/jobdetails.aspx?Job_DID=J3H5FX74ZPGYQJVR7H5', '', 5, 146, 2),
(429, 1398788955, 'Project Architect', 'amphibianArc', 'Engineering', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>amphibianArc, founded in 1992, represents a philosophy of design and architecture that is informed by the idea of evolution in the formation of human spirit and habitation. amphibianArc has been designed a wide range of projects in both the U.S. and China.</p>\n<p>Our Los Angeles office is seeking a Project Architect with 10+ years experience primarily in commercial, retail, and/or institutional work.&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Prior working experience in China and proficiency in Mandarin is preferred</strong>, but not required.&nbsp; Candidates should have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>An MArch or BArch from an accredited architectural program</li>\n<li>Excellent design skills, and the ability to convey ideas well in various media</li>\n<li>Strong communication, organizational and collaborative skills</li>\n<li>Excellent Autocad knowledge, BIM proficiency desired</li>\n<li>Managed relevant projects through all phases of design and construction administration</li>\n<li>Ability to work in a fast-paced and rigorous environment&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualified candidates should submit a cover letter, resume, portfolio samples, and salary requirements, stating the applicant&rsquo;s role in each project to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:jobs@amphibianarc.com" target="_blank">jobs@amphibianarc.com</a>. Please reference "Project Architect &ndash; Los Angeles" in the subject line of your e-mail. Submission to be in A SINGLE PDF DOCUMENT, NO MORE THAN 10MB. Only applicants that meet the qualifications will be contacted.&nbsp;</p>', 'http://archinect.com/jobs/entry/98855841/project-architect', 'jobs@amphibianarc.com', 5, 115, 2),
(430, 1398789789, 'Event Sales Associate', 'UBMAsia', 'Marketing', 'Manhasset, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'Manhasset', 40.797878, -73.699577, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div>\n<p>UBMAsia serves the needs of US companies to gain access to the Asia Market, as either a supplier to these markets or as a buyer of Asian goods. Apart from serving the jewelry trade, including the largest Int&rsquo;l jewelry fairs in Asia (twice a year in HK, three times a year in China), once in Japan, twice in Macau, three fashion jewelry fairs in Hong Kong, Asia&rsquo;s Fashion Jewelry Review. UBM Asia&rsquo;s New York office also serves the vast health industry, including the leading Japan health &amp; beauty fairs, Sign China &amp; Cashmere World.</p>\n<p>This position works with the Sales Manager to generate new sales revenue for the trade shows (mainly Jewelry industry) organized by UBM Asia while maintaining follow up on the existing customers.</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>UBM, LLC, is a subsidiary of UBM, PLC,&nbsp;</strong>a global events-led marketing and communications services business. We help organizations make connections, communicate their proposition and do business effectively. We help professional people in more than 30 countries around the world succeed by enabling them to connect with each other and with the markets they serve. And we do this by whatever means works best &ndash; at live events, through digital media or in publications.</p>\n<p><strong>Our 5,500 expert staff</strong>&nbsp;are deeply embedded in the many specialist communities we serve, bringing both an unusual depth of understanding and real know-how. We organize hundreds of live events each year and provide a range of related market-leading digital and print marketing and media products, and we support professional marketers and communicators through our targeting, distribution and monitoring services.</p>\n<p><strong>Our culture of innovation and collaboration</strong>&nbsp;brings our people together around common interests to create value, enhancing our ability to do exactly the same for UBM customers and the communities UBM serves. So, whatever their business and wherever they operate, our customers do better business through us.</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>Prospecting and identifying new customers (exhibitors, advertisers &amp; visitors) by cold-calling and going out on sales trips, and customer visits at trade shows and clients&rsquo; offices</li>\n<li>Responsible for booking space for the trade shows and Advertisement spaces in all show publications and Websites</li>\n<li>Assisting the Sales Manager as well as working independently on finalizing sales contracts/agreements and providing service to visitors</li>\n<li>Following up with existing clients and maintaining recurring business in order to build up the business by &lsquo;up sale&rsquo; from existing revenue.</li>\n<li>Organizing sales leads and providing close follow ups. Also must be able to close sales and collect payment within the given deadlines</li>\n<li>Attending trade shows for prospecting new customers &amp; promoting the fair name by distribution of show information booth by booth. Also helping to set up/tear down our own booth on the set up day and at closing of the show.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Business Acumen &ndash; Ability to learn and understand the trade show business and develop key relationships with customers.</li>\n<li>Customer focus &ndash; Very customer oriented so that business relationships are developed as a win/win situation for customers and UBM Asia. Must be professional &amp; proactive to the customer&rsquo;s needs while keeping in mind the company&rsquo;s business objectives.</li>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills &ndash; Ability to maintain good record keeping and organization.</li>\n<li>Initiative - Ability to provide business-value suggestions that can improve efficiency or revenue for the business. Willingness to contribute creative ideas.</li>\n<li>Leadership &ndash; Ability to learn the business and work independently on work assigned on a timely basis. Should be able to handle multiple assignments, be deadline oriented and able to work under pressure.</li>\n<li>People Development &ndash; A true team player that is willing to help colleagues to be successful through collaborative efforts, creative thinking, and completing a project or helping a visitor on little things.</li>\n<li>Sales Abilities &ndash; Ability to develop good relationships with existing clients for recurring business, cold calling for new business development, and sales forecasting (periodic projections of business objectives versus goal). Able to expand business by prospecting new clients and opportunities and Closing sales.</li>\n<li>B.A. or B.S. and proven sales experience a must</li>\n<li><strong>Fluency in Mandarin or Cantonese preferred**</strong></li>\n<li>Good computer skills using Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint). Also some knowledge of Customer contact system (i.e. ACT or Access)</li>\n<li>Proven sales abilities working with customers</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://hiring.accolo.com/jobs/Manhasset/New_York/Event_Sales_Associate/330133222/job.htm', '', 5, 166, 2),
(431, 1398790259, '', '', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>*Positions available in San Francisco and Sacramento, CA</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Provides professional and knowledgeable consultation</li>\n<li>Demonstrates Shiseido products through services such as Facial Massage / Make-up application and maintains minimum service goals set forth by AE.</li>\n<li>Contributes to improvements in customer service</li>\n<li>Keeps store clean and neat.</li>\n<li>Establishes friendly and comfortable atmosphere.</li>\n<li>Reports customer&rsquo;s opinions and needs to the company</li>\n<li>Works in a team to increase sales for stores.</li>\n<li>Achieves sales goals.</li>\n<li>Uses automated systems effectively.</li>\n<li>Maintains proper inventory level</li>\n<li>Displays merchandises attractively.</li>\n<li>Reflects "pride" &amp; "spirit" as Shiseido representative.</li>\n<li>Communicates effectively with SCA staff.</li>\n<li>Be reliable, dependable and self starter.</li>\n<li>Conducts business consistent with Shiseido standards</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speaks Cantonese/Mandarin</strong> (Arcadaia/Santa Anita opening only)</li>\n<li>Bilingual (Spanish) is helpful, not required</li>\n<li>Willing to demonstrate facial services</li>\n<li>Cosmetics background preferable</li>\n<li>Basic computer skills (helpful not required)</li>\n<li>Ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with store people, coworkers, and the general public.</li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/job/beauty-consultant-3f19284063ffb326', '', 5, 191, 2),
