(444, 1400688612, 'Merchandise Coordinator  (Fluent Mandarin)', 'Cloud Imperium Games', 'Management', 'Santa Monica, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Santa Monica', 34.019455, -118.491188, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Cloud Imperium Games is looking for a highly-analytical, articulate seasoned Merchandise Coordinator (fluent in Mandarin) to develop strategies for optimizing inventory levels to achieve sales, turn and margin goals.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>&bull; Communicate and collaborate with overseas factories on a daily basis to ensure their strict adherence to time-critical deadlines and detailed design specifications.<br />&bull; Monitor and troubleshoot all production assignments through entire project life cycle, from initial product development prototypes to full-scale bulk production.<br />&bull; Define and enforce quality control production standards with regard to size consistency, construction and component integrity.<br />&bull; Interface with design team and management to finalize and confirm product construction details, from color selection to coordinating the production of sample test units and bulk units.<br />&bull; Coordinate with buyers, product designers, shipping/logistics, quality control and component vendors to guarantee all production requirements are met on time.<br />&bull; Track all projects; maintain an up-to-date understanding of all projects at all times.<br />&bull; Provide periodic reports to management team.<br />&bull; Devise seasonal merchandise plans by monitoring weekly sales, analyzing style performances, and market trends; fill assortment plans, ensuring that merchandise concepts are aligned with assortment strategies<br />&bull; Conduct weekly analysis of stock-to-sales ratio by merchandise category, identifying trending as well as underperforming areas; work closely with Planning team to adjust open to buy needs in season, quickly reacting to topline sales and adjusting category and monthly penetrations where necessary<br />&bull; Review weekly sales performance by style to identify potential re-order opportunities, styles that require markdowns and transfers to different entities of business; provide actionable recommendations to Buyers and Product Developers for improving merchandise mix&nbsp;<br />&bull; Create price and markup strategy within designated area to compete with market, as well as to meet company financial targets<br />&bull; Coordinate with cross-functional partners in Production, Design, and Trend in order to make sure designs are adoptable, costs are measured, and concepts are clearly defined for the target customer<br />&bull; Clearly communicate to Buyers and Product Development teams monthly assortment plans to understand development needs in order to achieve open to buy goals<br />&bull; Work closely with Allocation and Planning team to clearly understand process of allocating goods and ensure that all opportunities for new styles are maximized by store<br />&bull; Perform competitor and market analysis by researching competitors&rsquo; price points, promotional campaigns, and emerging trends in colors, materials, categories and silhouettes</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>&bull; Must be fluent in Mandarin (speaking, reading, writing and typing)<br />&bull; Must have a college degree (preferably in Merchandising)<br />&bull; Must have at least 3 years of merchandising experience with a successful track record of high volume business growth and bottom line results<br />&bull; Must possess the ability to understand and act upon financial retail indicators such as sales, gross margin, inventory productivity, sell-through and turn<br />&bull; Must possess excellent verbal and written communication skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Must have strong proficiency in Microsoft Excel for reporting and analysis</p>\n<p><strong>This position is temp to hire</strong></p>', 'http://cloudimperiumgames.com/jobs/98-Merchandise-Coordinator-Fluent-Mandarin', 'hr@cloudimperiumgames.com', 5, 233, 2),
