(517, 1403627194, ' Phone Banker', 'Wells Fargo', 'Finance', 'El Monte, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'El Monte', 34.068623, -118.027565, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>IMPORTANT NOTE: Please ensure your contact information (e-mail address and phone number) is current in your Wells Fargo Jobs Profile. Initial contact will be made via e-mail. Please check your e-mail regularly for updates.</p>\n<p>Please note: If there is an exceptionally high volume of applicants for this job posting, this job posting may close before the indicated expiration date.</p>\n<p>Currently hiring for a training class starting on August 4th. Training hours are 8:30am &ndash;5:00pm Monday-Friday for 6 weeks (Must be available to attend entire paid training class).</p>\n<p>Current schedules being offered after training will be:</p>\n<p>Mandarin &ndash; 8:00am-4:30pm or 9:00am-5:30pm with Saturday and Sunday off</p>\n<p>Cantonese &ndash; 6:00am-2:30pm with Saturday and Sunday off</p>\n<p>Salary Range - $13.62/hr. - $14.81/hr. DOE plus eligible to participate in the WFCC Service Incentive Plan</p>\n<p>Our next big investment is in you! Wells Fargo offers:</p>\n<p>A broad array of medical, dental, and vision plans<br />Paid Time Off<br />401 (k) and Stock Purchase Plans<br />Discounts and Savings on Wells Fargo financial products, home mortgages and services<br />Tuition Reimbursement<br />Wellness Benefits<br />Commuter Benefits<br />Please review the requirements for a Phone Banker before applying. A Phone Banker spends nearly 100% of his/her time on the phone answering questions for Wells Fargo customers. The working environment is fun and relaxed with a casual dress code but is also demanding and structured, and involves overcoming customers&rsquo; banking concerns which can include some escalated issues.</p>\n<p>Phone Bankers are expected to sell products and services and achieve aggressive sales goals which are measured daily. Our best Phone Bankers thrive on customer interaction and never miss an opportunity to enhance the customer&rsquo;s relationship with Wells Fargo by marketing new products and services. They always handle each customer with a friendly, courteous touch while following strict procedures for handling various types of inquiries.</p>\n<p>We provide our Phone Bankers with continuous coaching and development which not only enhances their ability to provide exemplary service and product solutions to our customers, but also enhances the Phone Bankers&rsquo; career growth. Our successful bankers demonstrate self-motivation, a positive attitude, have the ability to work well on a team and have a solid work history. They also demonstrate strong listening, written and verbal communication skills. They are receptive to coaching and feedback, have the desire to meet/exceed goals and solve problems while working in a fast paced environment.</p>\n<p>Our Phone Bankers play a critical role in our customers&rsquo; lives; therefore, predictable and reliable attendance is an essential function of the position.</p>\n<p><br />Basic Qualifications</p>\n<p>6 months customer service and sales experience.<br />Minimum Qualifications</p>\n<p>Basic computer skills including the ability to navigate multiple windows and applications and utilize search tools to find information.</p>\n<p>6+ months sales experience (list specific sales experience in resume/work history)</p>\n<p>Experience with supporting both Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese) and English speaking customers.</p>\n<p>The successful passing of the language proficiency assessment (speaking and reading) is required to qualify for the bilingual Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese)/English queue (administered during the interviewing process).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://employment.wellsfargo.com/psc/PSEA/APPLICANT_NW/HRMS/c/HRS_HRAM.HRS_APP_SCHJOB.GBL?Page=HRS_APP_JBPST&FOCUS=Applicant&SiteId=1&JobOpeningId=5009238&PostingSeq=2&', '', 5, 120, 2),
(518, 1403627299, '', 'Jimway, INC', 'Finance', 'Compton, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Compton', 33.895847, -118.220070, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><span class="summary">Looking forcareer opportunities with a great company? Join JIMWAY, INC!&nbsp;<br /><br />JIMWAY, is amanufacturer and distributor of quality residential and commercial lightingproducts located in Rancho Dominguez, California, is currently recruiting for SeniorAccountant.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span class="summary"><br />Our idealcandidate has five + years experience in accounting, AR, AP and reconciliation.You must be a self-motivated, who is detail oriented, strong analyticabilities, has a sense of urgency, great at multi-tasking, have excellentcommunication skills, and able to work in a team environment.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />Supervise one junior accountant to handle and monitor daily direct import shipments modem download and weekly wire payment preparation to overseas brokers and vendors.&nbsp;<br /><br />Prepare cash transaction on Excel spreadsheet and journal entry for daily bank transactions.&nbsp;<br /><br />Monthly bank reconciliation&nbsp;<br /><br />Present L/C or Open account shipping documents to bank and monitor the payment collection.&nbsp;<br /><br />Reconcile GL accounts balance and resolve the pending issue with related teams&nbsp;<br /><br />Coding and booking DN and CN from or to overseas brokers&nbsp;<br /><br />Apply manual check for weekly wire payment&nbsp;<br /><br />Monitor banking team transactions and problem shooting on routine operations&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Requirement :</strong><br />5 yrs experience in AR, AP, and reconciliation on the balance of general ledger.&nbsp;<br /><br />2 yrs experience in importer / distributor operations and familiar with logistics and banking transactions.&nbsp;<br /><br />2 yrs supervision experience&nbsp;<br /><br />Must be well organized, self-motivated, detail oriented, and have good communication skills and able to operate in a team environment.&nbsp;<br /><br />Strong PC skills (Excel / Word) and mainframe system exp.(JDE a plus)&nbsp;<br /><br />B.S. degree in Accounting&nbsp;<br /><br />Bilingual (Chinese / English) with the ability to read and write a plus.&nbsp;<br /><br />Pleaseemail resumes along with salary history. Those who dont provide salary requirements will not be considered for the position.&nbsp;<br /><br />JIMWAY is a rock-solid company that offersexcellent benefits including:&nbsp;<br /><br />Comprehensive medical&nbsp;<br />Dental and vision program&nbsp;<br />Life insurance&nbsp;<br />Short-term disability&nbsp;<br />401(k) with company match&nbsp;<br />Paid vacation&nbsp;<br />10 paid holidays&nbsp;</span></p>', '', 'egarcia@jimway.com', 5, 134, 2),
(519, 1403627621, 'Storage Consultant', 'Optivest Properties', 'Consulting', 'Alhambra, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Alhambra', 34.095287, -118.127014, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Are you looking to work for a business that you operate like it is your own? Optivest Properties is an industry leader and looking for high quality candidates to join our team. We pride ourselves on not only having one of the highest quality management training programs, but INVESTING in our employees. Join a team where YOU matter! See below how your experience and expertise can be utilized at Optivest Properties.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>A Day in the Life&hellip;..</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Display a "customer comes first" attitude delivering legendary customer service.</li>\n<li>Assess the best rate and unit size for the customer&rsquo;s needs and close the deal</li>\n<li>Face to face marketing with the local community</li>\n<li>Know the ins and outs of your property and manage improvements</li>\n<li>Being a Team Player and accepting new challenges</li>\n<li>Exceed monetary and operational goals</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The Qualifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bilingual Chinese and English (required)</strong></li>\n<li>Minimum (2) years in customer service/selling position.</li>\n<li>Comfortable working in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel and Power Point)</li>\n<li>Ability to demonstrate effective problem solving</li>\n<li>Ability to adjust priorities and manage time wisely in a fast-paced environment</li>\n<li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</li>\n<li>Can work any day of the week including weekends.</li>\n<li>Willingness to perform pre-employment background test and drug screen</li>\n</ul>', 'http://optivestproperties.theresumator.com/apply/job_20140619005022_DOL55ABBWNEFNG68/Storage-Consultant-Bilingual-.html', '', 5, 137, 2),
