(525, 1403713512, 'Purchasing Coordinator', 'Mega Green Recycles', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Mega Green Recycles is in the business of import/export of recyclable goods. We are looking for a highly organized and multi-talented individual who can provide strong purchasing support.</p>\n<p><strong>CHINESE SPEAKING PREFERRED.</strong><br /><br />DUTIES:<br /><br />- Perform buying duties (purchasing of recyclable goods primarily electronic waste)<br />- Respond to customer and supplier inquiries about order status, changes, or cancellations.&nbsp;<br />- Track the status of requisitions, contracts, and orders.<br />- Contact suppliers in order to schedule or expedite deliveries and to resolve shortages, missed or late deliveries, and other problems.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare purchase orders and send copies to suppliers and to departments originating requests.&nbsp;<br />- Review requisition orders in order to verify accuracy, terminology, and specifications.&nbsp;<br />- Determine if inventory quantities are sufficient for needs, ordering more materials when necessary.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare, maintain, and review purchasing files, reports and price lists.&nbsp;<br />- Compare suppliers'' bills with bids and purchase orders in order to verify accuracy.&nbsp;<br />- Locate suppliers, using sources such as catalogs and the internet, and interview them to gather information about products to be ordered.&nbsp;<br />- Calculate costs of orders, and charge or forward invoices to appropriate accounts.&nbsp;<br />- Compare prices, specifications, and delivery dates in order to determine the best bid among potential suppliers.&nbsp;<br />- Check shipments when they arrive to ensure that orders have been filled correctly and that goods meet specifications.&nbsp;<br />- Approve bills for payment.&nbsp;<br />- Maintain knowledge of all organizational and governmental rules affecting purchases, and provide information about these rules to organization staff members and to vendors.&nbsp;<br />- Monitor in-house inventory movement and complete inventory transfer forms for bookkeeping purposes.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare invitation-of-bid forms, and mail forms to supplier firms or distribute forms for public posting.&nbsp;<br />- Monitor contractor performance, recommending contract modifications when necessary.<br />- Provide assistance to the Team with projects and tasks.<br /><br />REQUIREMENTS:<br /><br />- Proactive and self-controlled work ethic; Self-starter.<br />- Good organizational and excellent time management skills.<br />- Exceptional skills of customer service.<br />- Superior written and verbal communication skills.<br />- Able to develop and maintain good relationships with our suppliers.<br />- Highly proficient level computer skills including Ms Word, PowerPoint and Excel.<br />- Strong record tracking of work with various levels at every account.<br />- Able to understand our business needs.<br />- Willingness in traveling and working in a team of professionals.</p>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/Purchasing-Coordinator-Job-El-Monte-CA-US-135843412.aspx', '', 5, 156, 2),
(526, 1403733321, ' Fund Manager', 'M&E Financial Group', 'Finance', 'Irvine, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Irvine', 33.683949, -117.794693, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>ME Finance Group (Orange County)</strong><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Sales and sales closing experience</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Capable of handling rejection and overcoming objections&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Strong Time Management and self-management skills</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Ability to grow with an expanding organization&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Highly motivated to achieve and exceed goals</strong><br /><strong>&bull; A strong entrepreneurial spirit with a passion for excellence</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Proficient in the use of a computer&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>&bull; Professional appearance and work ethic</strong><br /><strong><a href="http://www.thebizcash.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">www.thebizcash.com</a></strong><br /><strong><a href="mailto:ali@thebizcash.com">ali@thebizcash.com</a>&nbsp;949-468-0945</strong></p>\n<p><strong></strong></p>', '', 'ali@thebizcash.com', 832, 23, 2),
(527, 1403797027, ' Business Development Associate - Entry Level', 'Axon US Corporation', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are seeking highly motivated and creative individuals to join our company. Applicants who can demonstrate work place professionalism and uphold strong work ethics are strongly encouraged to apply.</p>\n<p>This is a great opportunity for recent graduates that have an interest in eCommerce.</p>\n<p><strong>Immediate hire and position open till filled.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>Conduct research and screen for new business opportunities<br />Maintain existing professional business relationships with third-party vendors<br />Assist in various ad-hoc projects<br />Provide regular feedback on progress reports<br />Resolve customer issues regarding their orders, questions about products<br />Represent the company with pride</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<p>Associate or Bachelor degree<br />Proficient in Microsoft Office<br />Exceptional attention-to-detail with the ability to meet aggressive deadlines<br />Strong quantitative, analytical, and creative problem solving skills<br />Excellent verbal and written communication and interpersonal skills<br />Able to multitask and be organized<br />Professionalism<br />Available for Full Time work Monday through Friday</p>\n<p><strong>Pluses, but not required:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Bilingual in English and Chinese Mandarin</strong><br />High GPA<br />Experience in management<br />Experience in online retail</p>\n<p>Axon US Corp is an online retail company based in New York, but operating globally. Business includes international sourcing, web marketing, and database analyzing covering the fields of international purchasing and selling, products development, market exploitation and brand promotion.</p>\n<p>We offer you an open and equal atmosphere, challenging work and unlimited space to make progress. We welcome individuals with passion, dreams, experience and ability to join us, growing with us and creating our better future.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Axon-US-Corporation/jobs/Business-Development-Associate-bd31680af2c8acbf', '', 5, 308, 2),
(528, 1403797435, '', 'Asian Community Care Management', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>General Summary</strong><br />The Social Worker assists in the facilitation and coordination of community resources, in-home support services and other community-based services. He /She develops and maintain a therapeutic relationship with the client, which may include linking the client with systems that provide him or her with needed services, resources, and opportunities.</p>\n<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Services within the company include care management, counseling, life coaching and bereavement groups</li>\n<li>Responsible for the assessment and intervention of the psychosocial needs of patients, families, and/or significant others in the home setting.</li>\n<li>Will work in close conjunction with patient, patient''s family and company practitioners</li>\n<li>Provides education and counseling/therapy to patients</li>\n<li>Promote community resources and assist with coordination of care</li>\n<li>Screen new patients that meet high-risk criteria</li>\n<li>Completes comprehensive psychosocial assessments on assigned patients</li>\n<li>Collaborates with an interdisciplinary team to develop a patient focused, safe, feasible plan</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Valid New York State licensed Social Worker</li>\n<li>Must be fluent in Chinese (Mandarin and/or Cantonese) and English</li>\n<li>Must have strong analytic capacity with ability to make professional decisions in a highly communicative manner</li>\n<li>Excellent administrative, organizational and communication (oral and written) skills, especially with long-term care patients</li>\n<li>Proficient in MS Office Suite</li>\n<li>Minimum of one year social work experience in a health care setting preferred</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8ea72d3bd27d8a31', '', 5, 131, 2),
(529, 1403797890, 'Part-time Front Office Manager', 'AJ Construction', 'Management', 'Walnut, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Walnut', 34.020290, -117.865341, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<ul>\n<li>Hiring one part time office manager/assistant for a Construction company.</li>\n<li>Must be good at Windows softwares, independent, hardworking.</li>\n<li>Age around 20 to 35 years old, live within 30 minutes from Walnut, CA.</li>\n<li>*<strong>Must be fluent in English and Chinese</strong>*, and able to use social media</li>\n<li>The assistant is asked to *visit construction sites*, purchase construction materials and supplies, communicate with workers, type paperworks, post on social media, and so on.</li>\n<li>Prefers experienced people and people with related major.</li>\n<li>Work for around 20 hr/week.</li>\n</ul>', '', 'andyjiang922@gmail.com', 5, 147, 2),
(530, 1403798549, '', 'Broadway Elementary School', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Broadway Mandarin Immersion, located in Venice, CA and part of Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD), is seeking highly motivated applicants for the full-time position of elementary Mandarin teacher. Broadway&rsquo;s Mandarin Immersion program serves grades K-5 and operates on the 50/50 model. Successful applicants will be enthusiastic collaborators who can develop innovative instructional units with their teaching partners. Candidates should have a strong understanding of second language acquisition across the four language skills, and be able to integrate Chinese culture in creative classroom lessons. Teachers work in partnership with administration, staff, and parents to foster a nurturing and supportive learning environment.</p>\n<p>For more information on the program, visit: http://www.broadwayelementary.org/mi</p>\n<p>Qualified candidates should email resume and cover letter to Principal Susan Wang.</p>\n<p>Candidates must have native-level proficiency in spoken and written Mandarin, and be able to teach traditional characters. Must have California Elementary Multiple Subject Credential and a Bilingual, Cross-Cultural, Language and Academic Development (BCLAD) authorization in Mandarin. Applicants with certification from other states must be prepared to apply for a California teaching credential, and to pass all associated exams. (Please do not apply if you are unable or unwilling to obtain the needed California teaching credentials.)</p>\n<p>Prior experience in dual language elementary education and project-based learning are highly valued. Training in Gifted and Talented Education (GATE) is strongly desired.</p>', '', 'swang1@lausd.net', 5, 188, 2),
(531, 1403799108, ' Health Care Coordinator', 'Chinese American Service League', 'Management', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="post_description">\n<p>The Health Care Coordinator will work closely with the FCS Program Manager and other team members to streamline health initiatives within the agency to ensure effective service delivery and high quality health services. He/She will develop strategic collaboration with community partners, identify gaps in services and&nbsp; educate the community about the ECHO (Enhancing Community Health Outreach) Program. He/She will also work on evaluation of the effectiveness of CASL''s health programs, develop evaluative tools to implement within the agency by centralizing program outcomes through surveys, client feedback and quality assurance.</p>\n<h2>Mandatory Job Qualifications</h2>\n<p>Requires a Master''s Degree in Public Health, Social Work, or related field and a minimum of 1 year&rsquo;s work experience in health, social service, and/or education fields.&nbsp;Knowledge and experience in developing Client Database System, strong computer skills in data analysis of outcome performance, excellent written and verbal communication skills are required, as are the ability to speak, write, and read Chinese. (Cantonese preferred.) .</p>\n</div>\n<div class="post_apply">\n<h2>How to Apply</h2>\n<p>This job is open for online applications.</p>\n<p>To apply, please email the followings to Jobs@CASLservice.org:</p>\n<p>Cover letter<br />Resume<br />CASL Application (which can be downloaded at<a href="http://caslservice.org/images/stories/pdfs/employment_application.pdf">http://caslservice.org/images/stories/pdfs/employment_application.pdf</a>)</p>\n</div>', 'http://www.npo.net/job/health-care-coordinator-bilingual-chinese-english/64031', 'Jobs@CASLservice.org', 5, 136, 2),
