(537, 1404143012, ' Provider Account Manager', 'MJHS', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>The challenges of affordable healthcare continue to create new opportunities. Elderplan and HomeFirst, our Medicare and Medicaid managed care health plans, are outstanding examples of how we are expanding services in response to our patients'' and members'' needs. These high-quality healthcare plans are designed to help keep people independent and living life on their own terms.<br /><br />We truly value our staff and further acknowledge their contributions by offering:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Employee and family health coverage</li>\n<li>Competitive salaries</li>\n<li>Employer contributed pension plan</li>\n<li>Generous time off</li>\n<li>Tuition reimbursement</li>\n<li>403(b) retirement plan</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /><br />Responsibilities:&nbsp;<br />The Provider Account Manager develops and maintains strong relationships with strategically important IPAs. The Provider Account Manager coordinates with appropriate cross functional resources to ensure successful execution of the provider contract and the achievement of provider membership growth and financial results.<br /><br />Qualifications:&nbsp;<br />Four year college degree from an accredited institution. Minimum one to three years of experience in managed care or health care organization. Superior communication skills; <strong>bilingual English/Chinese required</strong>. Strong critical thinking skills and work ethic; strong problem-solving capacity.&nbsp;</p>', 'https://careers-mjhs.icims.com/jobs/2873/provider-account-manager/job', '', 5, 199, 2),
(538, 1404143213, 'Financial Analyst', 'MKVF Management', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="jobwrapper">\n<div id="jobcopy">\n<div id="jobBodyContent"><span id="TrackingJobBody">Financial Analyst. NYC. Financial analysis of Chinese listed companies: Review financial statements &amp; legal documents; Develop flexible financial models to perform valuation analysis; Gather data &amp; info from multiple Chinese sources including Nat''l Bureau of Statistics &amp; Chinese companies in the same industry. Req''d: Master''s degree economics, finance or related. Knowledge of Int''l Finance, Financial Markets &amp; Financial Risk; Securities Law; Financial Derivatives; Security Investment Analysis; Chinese Civil &amp; Economic Law. M-F, 9-5. Send resume to Job#3, MKVF Management Co. LLC, 1212 6th Avenue, 16th. Fl, NY, NY 10036.</span>&nbsp;<img src="http://media.newjobs.com/jobview_standard/images/pixel.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'http://jobview.monster.com/FINANCIAL-ANALYST-Job-US-136071153.aspx', '', 5, 289, 2),
(539, 1404143432, '', 'Chicago State University', 'Language', 'Chicago, IL, United States', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>All faculty positions are governed by the tenets of a collective bargaining agreement. Faculty are hired, evaluated, and retained on the basis of conditions covered in the union contract. Primary duties include teaching and related activities assigned during a term of 4.5 months. It is expected that each faculty member engages in teaching and teaching-related activities. Non-tenure track faculty report to a department chairperson or director.<br />Teaching: faculty members are expected to teach; develop syllabi and teaching materials (ability to organize, analyze, and present knowledge or materials) related to courses taught. Some disciplines require discipline specific certifications and/or licensure in the field for practice or functioning within the State of Illinois; degree specific course work and/or graduate degrees in the discipline.</p>\n<p>Appropriate educational background with a Master degree from an accredited institution and completed 60 semester hours or the equivalent of graduate study toward an advanced degree;</p>\n<p>Experience in teaching Chinese language to adults.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://chicagostate.peopleadmin.com/pools/2989', '', 5, 424, 2),
(540, 1404143814, 'Project Manager', 'Yoyo Chinese', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', 'Carson', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="q1" class="question">\n<div class="qContent">\n<div class="qBody">\n<section id="description">\n<p><em>To weed out spammers and make sure you read our job post carefully, please use &ldquo;I love pizza&rdquo; as the subject line. Thank you!</em></p>\n<p>We are an online Chinese language education company that uses videos to teach Chinese to students from all over the world.</p>\n<p>In our opinion, there are two sides to being a stellar project manager - managing projects and managing people. We&rsquo;re looking for someone who&rsquo;s absolutely great at both.</p>\n<p>IF YOU&rsquo;RE INTERESTED IN WORKING FOR US, YOU ARE:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Extremely organized and detail-oriented:&nbsp;You&rsquo;re so organized that you always have some kind of to-do list at hand. You&rsquo;re so detail-oriented that when you approve something, people are confident it&rsquo;s ready to go out, error-free. Errors and inconsistencies immediately jump out at you, and you care about details like file-naming practices.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Crazy about building systems:&nbsp;You love building systems so the whole company can run on autopilot. You believe the success of a company should be independent of any specific individual. You believe that any mistake that happens in a business is not just human error, but a problem with the system.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Obsessed with planning:&nbsp;You always have fun taking a big idea and translating it into a plan with a timeline of clear deliverables. You are skilled at both macro and micro thinking. You make sure the big picture is always moving forward by way of all the tiny details that need to get done.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A solution-driven problem solver:&nbsp;Your goal is to get things done. You hate playing the &ldquo;blame game&rdquo; but instead like to just correct the issue and move on. You love unraveling any problem, figuring out what&rsquo;s really going on, and finding the missing pieces.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A self-starter:&nbsp;You have an entrepreneurial spirit and hate to be micromanaged. You are always proactive about what else you can do to add value to the company.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Clear and straightforward communicator:&nbsp;You have to be an absolutely clear communicator. You can always express your thoughts clearly and make sure listeners are on the same page. You constantly ask thoughtful questions and provide constructive feedback at the same time.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Someone we can lean on:&nbsp;You are a natural mentor and sounding board, and knowing that you helped someone else succeed gives you enormous satisfaction. You love coaching and pushing people to do their best. You see people&rsquo;s strength and talents and have the ability to draw it out of themeven more.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Just like any startup company, we look for people who can wear different hats. Here are some job responsibilities you&rsquo;ll have:</p>\n<p>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<p>Manage Projects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Build / refine our internal business system to make it more scalable, in terms of designing and documenting the business process and workflow to streamline the training of new staff.</li>\n<li>Supervise and coordinate our new academic courses like a producer (hiring writers, overseeing course planning, scheduling shoot, editing video, uploading schedule)</li>\n<li>Oversee and plan our app development process (hiring developers, uploading the app onto different mobile platforms, etc.).</li>\n<li>Organize and guide daily/weekly planning meetings.</li>\n</ul>\nManage People:\n<ul>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll be serving as HR director to take charge of hiring and employee related issues.</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll be delegating work to different staff and tracking each one&rsquo;s progress.</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll help the company president to review each staff&rsquo;s progress and make sure everyone&rsquo;s on track.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>REQUIREMENTS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3-5 years of project management experience</li>\n<li>Ability to speak Chinese is a big plus</li>\n<li>Video/audio producing or editing experience is a plus</li>\n<li>Project experience with developing a mobile app is a plus</li>\n<li>Basic knowledge of accounting is a plus</li>\n<li>Knowledge of common CMS and CRM</li>\n<li>Experience working with overseas team members is a plus.</li>\n<li>Graphic design and web design background is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>ABOUT OUR COMPANY</p>\n<p>We officially launched the website of the company (<a href="http://www.yoyochinese.com/" target="_blank">www.yoyochinese.com</a>) in 2012. In two short years, the company has grown to a comprehensive Chinese learning site with tens of thousands of members. While we continue to grow the company organically by developing more popular products and expanding our marketing efforts, we are also keen on building a strong foundation so the company is highly scalable to accommodate explosive growth.</p>\n<p>NEXT STEP:</p>\n<p>This job will start out part-time, but depending on how fast you can excel and demonstrate your abilities, this can change to a full-time position.</p>\n<p>If you&rsquo;re interested, please complete the questionnaire in the following link AND send your resume to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@yoyochinese.com" target="_blank">info(at)yoyochinese(dot)com</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/yoyoprojectmanager" target="_blank">https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/yoyoprojectmanager</a></p>\n<p>Thank you, and we look forward to hearing from you soon!</p>\n</section>\n<section id="perks"></section>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/yoyoprojectmanager', 'info@yoyochinese.com', 5, 174, 2),
(541, 1404144370, 'Staff Accountant', 'Wu and Wang Associates Inc', 'Finance', 'Rowland Heights, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Rowland Heights', 33.976124, -117.905342, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>CPA firm in Rowland Heights seeking experienced full-time staff accountant. Duties include preparing individual and business income tax returns, sales tax returns, payroll tax returns and bookkeeping. Must be fluent in Chinese and English. Will train if needed.</p>\n<p>Please email resume and salary history.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=95a536f44be1f94c', '', 5, 152, 2),
(542, 1404144432, ' Marketing Coordinator', ' Cathay General Bancorp', 'Marketing', 'El Monte, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'El Monte', 34.068623, -118.027565, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create strategic, thoughtful media plans for bank campaigns/promotions and make recommendations based on target market/audience analysis, pricing, etc.</li>\n<li>Serve as the primary media contact and foster ongoing media relationships.</li>\n<li>Execute media buys (TV, print, online, radio, and directories) and manage deadlines.</li>\n<li>Provide ad material information for ad creation/adaptation.</li>\n<li>Coordinate Chinese press releases and marketing copy for various marketing materials/collaterals.</li>\n<li>Review and edit Chinese copy submitted internally and from ad agencies/vendors.</li>\n<li>Invoicing &ndash; review all media contracts and final invoices; verify expenses for project leaders&rsquo; approval.</li>\n<li>Maintain marketing statements for bank control accounts; prepare monthly statements for approval; prepare petty cash (by checks) for corporate events, recordkeeping, etc.</li>\n<li>Support other units in the bank for Chinese translation, e.g., web page content updates, HR documents, VRS scripts (Call Center), Compliance notices, customer letters, branch signage, etc.</li>\n<li>Source and review new media channels for potential advertising opportunities.</li>\n<li>Coordinate and assist with branch merchandising and merchandising communications.</li>\n<li>Provide support to team leaders as needed for various projects and ad hoc tasks.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Some marketing and/or banking experience a plus.</li>\n<li><strong>Bilingual &ndash; strong written and verbal skills in Cantonese or Mandarin</strong>.</li>\n<li>Proficient Chinese copywriting ability.</li>\n<li>Can multi-task and work within tight deadlines.</li>\n<li>Possess a strong interest in media planning 