(602, 1407272542, '', 'LanguageLine Solutions', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="content-sections">\n<section id="job-description-section" class="minimized">\n<h2>JOB DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<div id="pnlJobDescription" class="section-body">\n<p><strong>LanguageLine Solutions</strong>, the world&rsquo;s leading over-the-phone interpretation provider, is seeking to increase its&nbsp;<strong>Chinese (Mandarin, Cantonese)</strong>&nbsp;interpreter personnel.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />Work from home the days and hours that suit you best! Our interpreters work from the comfort of their home and it is one of the biggest benefits of being a LanguageLine Solutions interpreter. The U.S. Census Bureau says an average employee spends 1,000 hours a year commuting to and from work. By working at home, our interpreters save time, money, gasoline and have a better quality of life.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />If you have excellent language skills we, will help you become an Over-the-Phone Interpreter. Make a difference in people&rsquo;s lives!&nbsp;<br /><br />Work from the comfort of your home!&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong>We offer:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Paid orientation &amp; on-going training</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No experience necessary-- We help you get started!&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you are a&nbsp;<strong>Chinese(Mandarin or Cantonese)&nbsp;</strong>speaker and have excellent proficiency in English with a strong listening and comprehension skills as well as good customer service skills you can become an interpreter for LanguageLine Solutions.&nbsp;<br /><br />For over 25 years, LanguageLine Solutions has provided telephone interpretation and document translation services to all cultural communities in over 175 languages, 24 hours a day, every day of the year. For that entire time, it has provided a voice for speakers of Asian, American, European, African and the Pacific island languages, as well as for those who wish to provide services to them.&nbsp;<br /><br />The company is now increasing numbers of employment opportunities in the global economy to all telephone interpreters, particularly&nbsp;<strong>Chinese(Mandarin or Cantonese)&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>English&nbsp;</strong>speakers.&nbsp;<br /><br />If you would like to work from home and are proficient in English and a second language, please apply.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="center">EOE/AA</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="jobDescriptionTextFade">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-requirements">\n<h2>JOB REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<div class="section-body">\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excellent English proficiency along with&nbsp;<strong>Chinese(Mandarin or Cantonese)&nbsp;</strong>proficiency</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strong listening and comprehension skills</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Outstanding customer service skills</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligible to work in the US</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Must be 18 years or older</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a work at home position</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-snapshot-section">\n<h2>JOB SNAPSHOT</h2>\n<div class="section-body">\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Employment Type</strong>Full-Time/Part-Time</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Job Type</strong>Customer Service, Telecommunications, Other</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Education</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Experience</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Manages Others</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Industry</strong>Other Great Industries, Telecommunications</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Required Travel</strong>Not Specified<br /><br /></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/jobs/jobdetails.aspx?Job_DID=JHT0NV6MH911TSMDGC5&siteid=cb001&showNewJDP=yes&ipath=EXINDsep_google_feed#', '', 980, 196, 2),
(603, 1407272793, '', 'Regional Centers Holding Group Inc.', 'Finance', 'Long Beach, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Long Beach', 33.770050, -118.193741, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>A fast growing international business is seeking a full-time Accounting Assistant to collect and report its financial data to help CPA in tax return and financial report preparation, book keep its capital, asset/liability, loan, and investment accounts, compiling monthly reports, opening and maintaining investment accounts etc.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities<br />Document company and client financial transactions<br />Prepare revenue/sales monthly entries<br />Open, maintain and resolve issues on clients&rsquo; accounts<br />Reconcile both domestic and overseas corporate bank accounts</p>\n<p>Qualifications:<br />Undergraduate degree in accounting or equivalent.<br />A foreign language in CHINESE is required.<br />Willing to relocate to Long Beach, CA<br />Familiarity with Quickbooks and Microsoft Excel, experience using any other accounting software a plus.<br />Must be a quick learner and team player, strong knowledge in Accounting and Corporate Finance is needed.<br />Good reporting and presentation skills, attention to detail, deadline-oriented, able to read and research on internet and report results, keep confidentiality, knows how to manage time, decent data entry and math skills.</p>\n<p>Salary/Pay: Competitive W-2 salary, medial insurance, vacation days etc. based on individual qualifications.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Regional-Centers-Holding-Group-Inc./jobs/Chinese-Speaking-Accounting-Assistant-b153365173cc000b', '', 980, 241, 2),
(604, 1407273271, '', 'Confidence USA, Inc', 'Technology', 'Port Washington, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'Port Washington', 40.825657, -73.698189, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Confidence U.S.A. Inc., an international manufacturer and retailer of premium dietary supplements and natural health products is searching for a bilingual (English/Mandarin) Internet Marketing Specialist to join our company. The Internet Marketing Specialist coordinates all aspects of e-commerce product marketing material. Works with other internet partners and outside agencies to ensure marketing directions are clear, accurate, and on schedule.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:<br />- Maintain product marketing and informational content on all applicable websites.<br />- Meet regularly with management and IT for status updates and to discuss new initiatives. Prioritize projects to meet deadlines.<br />- Implement enhancements and updates to the website as well as provide recommendations on how to best meet marketing goals while maintaining usability.<br />-Investigating and implementing new marketing trends and strategies.<br />- Liaise with management and IT to develop new site functionality and to assist in their online initiatives. Troubleshoot site issues and determine appropriate resolution as needed.<br />- Work with outside vendors for creative and production services as necessary.</p>\n<p>Requirements:<br />-Bilingual in Mandarin and English (both written and oral)<br />-Graphic design a plus<br />-SEO experience a plus<br />-Copyright experience a plus<br />-Knowledge of dietary supplement and/or natural health food industry a plus</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=Confidence-USA,-Inc.&t=Bilingual+Internet+Marketing+Specialist&jk=b338a5ff8deadae2&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvSj0hztkggTN-w372Dbd460JrIjyCvg1xRxymVcO9XI09rhwz1m_ykxr1ANi_F0YqFw0xrM7GNqrdgbxJAYsGkmBbBTVppmnyceHLuu1WaJG', '', 980, 107, 2),
(605, 1407273518, '', 'Caffbene Inc', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Caffebene USA is looking for a Franchise Sales Manager to head the franchise sales efforts in the Chinese American Market.</p>\n<p>Caffe Bene is the leading coffee franchise chain from South Korea. Established in 2008, we have grown to over 1,300 stores all over the world. Entering the US market in 2012, we have opened in 10 American stores, with 20 more to be opened within this year. With our exquisite interior design, healthy diverse menu, and organized business operations system, we distinguish ourselves from our competitors and create a trendy environment of comfort and relaxation.</p>\n<p>Currently, we are looking for a Sales Manager to manage the Chinese team at our NYC headquarters.</p>\n<p>Main duties and responsibilities will include but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pitching our company and franchise opportunity to potential Chinese clients</li>\n<li>Building and maintaining trustful relationships with clients</li>\n<li>Following up with clients in a timely manner</li>\n<li>Travelling and working at different franchise shows and seminars</li>\n<li>Coming up with creative ideas for Chinese advertising</li>\n<li>Effectively manage the Chinese sales team</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Education and Experience required:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelors Degree</li>\n<li>3 years minimum of previous sales experience</li>\n<li>Experience in managing others</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Skills and abilities required:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fluency in Mandarin Chinese (speaking, reading, writing)</li>\n<li>The candidate must be able to work independently</li>\n<li>Be able to multitask</li>\n<li>Ability to communicate verbally, and understand and follow written and verbal instructions</li>\n<li>Team player who can work well with different personalities</li>\n<li>Ability to work and adapt in an Asian cultural work environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All interested candidates please respond. We are looking to hire as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>Compensation: Based on Experience</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Caffbene-(NYC)/jobs/Chinese-Franchise-Sales-Manager-7974b3938c91eee9', '', 980, 150, 2),
(606, 1407273705, '', 'China Institute in America', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>China Institute in America , a non-profit, non-partisan, educational, and bi-cultural organization based in NYC, is seeking experienced children&rsquo;s Mandarin teachers. Grouped by ages three and up, children learn a dynamic mix of Chinese language and culture through a whole language approach in active classroom environments. Successful candidates should be native speakers of Chinese who have teaching experience using simplified characters and who have a very good command of spoken English. They should be vivacious in the classroom and eager to nurture children&rsquo;s learning and growth. They must feel comfortable creating their own curricula and finding materials to suit classroom needs, levels, and abilities. Teaching assignments may entail classroom teaching or private tutoring and may be onsite, offsite in other schools, or in students&rsquo; homes. Classes are taught using simplified characters. Competitive hourly wage.&nbsp;<br /><br />Please send cover letter and CV, including resident status, to:&nbsp;<br /><br />Ms. Shenzhan Liao&nbsp;<br />Director of Education&nbsp;<br /><br />China Institute&nbsp;<br />125 East 65th Street&nbsp;<br />New York, NY 10065</p>', '', 'sliao@chinainstitute.org', 980, 188, 2),
(607, 1407273897, '', 'China Institute in America', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>China Institute in America , a non-profit, non-partisan, educational, and bi-cultural organization based in NYC, is seeking experienced Mandarin teachers within the tri-state region for its Adult Language Program. Positions currently available include teachers for our group classes, and tutors for our private and corporate tutoring programs.&nbsp;<br /><br />Successful candidates should be native speakers of Chinese who speak standard Mandarin with clear diction and who have a good command of spoken English. They should be comfortable with dealing with students from diverse backgrounds within the business world and private sector; be presentable in appearance and disposition; punctual; enthusiastic in their instruction and, for private tutoring, must be able to choose materials suited for each students&rsquo; needs, level, and abilities. Minimum educational requirement: B.A. degree.&nbsp;<br /><br />Group classes are held onsite at China Institute. All classes use pinyin and simplified characters. Most tutoring assignments are offsite and held at our students&rsquo; office or home with some assignments taking place onsite at China Institute. Competitive hourly wage available. Applicants must have permission to work.&nbsp;<br /><br />Please send cover letter and CV, including resident status, to:&nbsp;<br /><br />Wanling Zhang&nbsp;<br />Program Manager, Adult Language &amp; Studio Programs&nbsp;<br /><br />China Institute&nbsp;<br />125 East 65th Street&nbsp;<br />New York, NY 10065</p>', '', 'wzhang@chinainstitute.org', 980, 272, 2),
(608, 1407278336, 'Customer Service Representative/', 'GotoBus.com / TakeTours.com', 'Service', 'Monterey Park, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Monterey Park', 34.062511, -118.122849, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>GotoBus.com / TakeTours.com is a leading online marketplace for interstate bus tickets, tours, sightseeing trips, vacation packages and hotels. We partners with over 300 bus and tour operators worldwide and we are one of the fastest growing travel businesses on the internet.<br /><br />We have an immediate opening for Customer Service Representative full-time/part-time positions (9am to 6pm PST). The ideal candidate will have excellent customer service, effective communication skills, and the ability to multitask in a fast paced environment.<br /><br />Job Description:<br /><br />- This position is responsible to assist customers with all phases of their travel arrangements. The individual will be required to respond to customer''s inquiries over the phone, email and live-chat in a courteous manner.&nbsp;<br />- Prepare monthly statements and mail out checks.<br />- Confirm bookings with the tour operators and notify travelers any updates with their itinerary in a timely fashion.<br />- Maintain a close relationship with the service providers and solve any issues related to the booking process.<br /><br />Job Requirements:<br /><br />- Associate Degree or higher education.<br />- Must be able to speak, read and write fluently in both English and Chinese.<br />- Must be able to work on one day on the weekend.<br />- Experience in the travel industry is a plus.</p>', 'http://www.taketours.com/ps/p1/43788.html', 'jobs@gotobus.com', 980, 228, 2),
