(610, 1407380622, '', '130 Administrative Services', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Job Responsibilities:<br />This position will provide detailed administrative project support and requires both knowledge of architecture/engineering/construction project processing and strong general hands on administrative skills.</p>\n<p>PRIMARY FUNCTIONS:</p>\n<p>Provide word processing for specifications and contracts (AIA forms) to create Project Manuals and Office Master Specification and Provide administrative support to one or more Managers or Project Teams, including maintaing individual and project related schedules.</p>\n<p>TYPICAL DUTIES <br />&bull;Type project specifications and AIA contract forms using all aspects of the word processing system including spell check, editing techniques and program enhancements to maximize efficient use of the system. <br />&bull;Make typing revisions to specifications for revised editions (i.e. Addenda/Bulletins, Construction Issues etc.) including format revisions to pages as required. <br />&bull;Assemble Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues by obtaining the Project Master folder and pulling the corresponding front or back sheet master to maintain "two-sided" specification page formatting. <br />&bull;Type Office Master Specifications (used in reproduction of the ivory master "mark-ups"), using all aspects of the word processing system. <br />&bull;Whenever possible, proofread work directly from computer screen. When necessary, work with another processor to ensure accuracy. <br />&bull;Return typed, proofread specifications to author. <br />&bull;Advise Manager of Specifications of problems with workload, scheduling or equipment and software. <br />&bull;File Project Specification Masters after project is run for issue. Subsequent Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues shall be filed with Project Masters (in proper location to ensure Project Master folder is always complete and current. Previous issue Project Masters will be replaced by current versions and stored in the back of the Project Master). <br />&bull;Work with managers assigned to desk to become a valued team member. Develop good rapport and interaction with other staff and with the Company''s clients. <br />&bull;Prepare a variety of documents; letters, reports, spreadsheets, memos, confidential material lists, etc. <br />&bull;Compile/prepare various reports for manager''s use or distribution. Write reports, memos or letters for manager''s signature or distribution. <br />&bull;Create and maintain filing system; maintain required records for manager and team. Maintain updated job log for desk. <br />&bull;Answer phones, screen calls, take and forward messages, answer routine questions and follow through on requests. Organize priority items for manager''s attention. Screen and route mail/phone messages during manager''s absence. <br />&bull;Maintain electronic calendar for manager and review with them daily. Keep switchboard informed of their availability. <br />&bull;May be required to relieve the switchboard. <br />&bull;Perform routine administrative duties involved in the operation of office programs, projects and activities, many of which are confidential and require the use of judgment, tact and knowledge of our Operations and Personnel standards. <br />&bull;Provide assistance with work overload from other desks when necessary. <br />&bull;May be responsible for, or cross-trained for corporate travel including airline, hotel and car reservations, preparation of itineraries; schedule meetings and take minutes; preparation of confidential government reports; handling of confidential personnel information; client proposals/contracts containing employee rates; maintain telephone or voice mail systems, maintaining office project files; maintenance of office lists (i.e. phone extensions, home addresses, etc.); or conference room scheduling and distribution of daily schedules.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Job Qualifications:<br />&bull;High school diploma. <br />&bull;Minimum three years word processing and secretarial experience or two-year degree in Secretarial Science.<br />&bull;Bilingual written and verbal skills in Mandarin Chinese is required<br />&bull;Excellent proofreading, grammar and typing skills. <br />&bull;Working knowledge of business procedures, letter/report formats, business machines, transcription equipment and general office routines necessary.<br />&bull;Ability to type 65-75 wpm accurately. <br />&bull;Computer literacy with experience in word processing software.</p>\n<p><br />PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS <br />&bull;Ability to sit for long periods of time. <br />&bull;Ability to use office equipment for communication and documentation purposes. <br />&bull;Visual acuity to perform responsibilities. <br />&bull;Ability to access and file documents from file drawers.</p>', 'http://cr.harleyellisdevereaux.com/careers/Careers.aspx?adata=ECzEettUENJ%2bMsA8mkSBDUtcBUMA1TDrvY1ehFrCFohD36Tgiwhwv2KgcJ6pyAqYkhLOZJWDs7vIGyvPqIUQtoO6s%2bIRG7DMz6hGFrV0a1aTvaSR1fWw44aB0w2tDbQvmrb%2fmu%2fAk2AQXeNJWnZvQmvikDmtSzWew9pb1%2fKGWqVYJxDJqPncQ%2fVnpzJicLZlnzlOQ1ZOMxG265UdJGv8V559FG96jvOMul9FQRfgRohU', '', 980, 155, 2),
(611, 1407380768, '', 'Sysco', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Overview:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>At Sysco we understand that building a great company is just like creating a great product - you must have all the right ingredients. For us, those ingredients are the cultures, backgrounds, ideas, and experiences behind our diverse workforce that embodies Sysco.&nbsp; Sysco is the global leader in selling, marketing and distributing food products to restaurants, healthcare and educational facilities, lodging establishments and other customers who prepare meals away from the home.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This Sysco Los Angeles position will be servicing the Los Angeles, CA area.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>This position is responsible for promoting the company&rsquo;s products and services and for building relationships with new and existing accounts.&nbsp; The main focus is to help Sysco customers succeed while achieving sales and profit goals established by the company.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a 100% sales commissioned opportunity with a salaried based training.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This position often requires working non-traditional hours (evening, weekends and holidays) in order to successfully meet customers&rsquo; needs.&nbsp; You must reside within the territory you are applying for.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>An individual must be able to satisfactorily perform each essential duty listed below.&nbsp; The requirements listed are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Essential Skills and Knowledge:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop new business, penetrate existing accounts, and minimize lost business to achieve profitable sales growth and special objectives within assigned territory.</li>\n<li>Seek and qualify prospects in accordance with Company account stratification goals.</li>\n<li>Research customer business needs and develop a mix of products and service to meet needs. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Evaluate market trends and recommend products to customers, based on business needs and goals.</li>\n<li>Be informed of market conditions, product innovations, and competitors'' products, prices, and sales; share information with customers as part of value-added services provided.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Essential Duties</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sales Activities:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develops, on a daily basis, a product mix penetration of each account by selling all major product categories through the presentation of new products, services, ideas, uses and applications in an effort to meet all established sales and profit objectives; demonstrates a working knowledge of all product categories sold.</li>\n<li>Develops and maintains a list of prospective accounts and sales forecasts to ensure complete market coverage and long-term sales efficiency.</li>\n<li>Completes and up-dates "Training Guide and Checklist" evaluation system and submits information for review by District Sales Manager and Regional Sales Manager as required.</li>\n<li>Develops prospective accounts through market analysis, personal and telephone contacts, and other sales techniques to ensure complete market coverage and long-term sales efficiency.</li>\n<li>Maintains, on a daily basis, a product price book, merchandising material, route list, and lead list to enhance sales activities through planning based on accurate and precise information; completes and up-dates, on a daily basis, all applicable sales forms and call reports to ensure a complete and timely flow of sales information.</li>\n<li>Sells, on a daily basis, excess and/or obsolete inventory items, as identified, through special customer contacts and sales techniques in an effort to reduce product waste and unsatisfactorily high inventory levels.</li>\n<li>Works closely with Sysco specialists, manufacturing representatives, and brokers in supporting company promotions or obtaining information on products or services.</li>\n<li>Performs merchandising research of, on a daily basis, product discounts, product service information, special offers and/or company promotions; utilizes information in sales activities in an effort to increase profitability and enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Attends and participates in informational seminars, learning based meetings, and other sessions in an effort to advance individual knowledge of sales techniques, product specifications, and department functions.</li>\n<li>Attends all department sales meetings, as scheduled and participates in other activities as requested; reports on industry/market competition as requested; assists with reviewing inventory levels.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Customer Service&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Provides service to existing accounts, on a daily basis, through proper salespersonship, service, or response to complaints in an effort to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Notifies supervisor immediately if an existing account is determined to be in jeopardy of being discontinuedto ensure that every possible effort is made to retain that account.</li>\n<li>Up-dates customer, on a continuous basis, about any new products/services and pricing information to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Checks messages, on a continuous basis, for customer complaints, problems, or interests and takes the necessary actions in an effort to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Responds to any customer questions or inquiries by providing relevant information or obtaining the information from the appropriate source and immediately relaying it to the customer in an effort to retain/enhance customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>May make product deliveries to customers as needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Credit Activities&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maintains an appropriate average of accounts receivable days outstanding as determined by supervisor to maintain cash flow and profitability objectives.</li>\n<li>Completes and routes to Credit Department a properly completed credit application for new accounts, as needed, to ensure a complete and timely flow of sales information.</li>\n<li>Provides customers with relevant information concerning company credit terms to avoid interruptions in cash flow and to ensure customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Ensures that customers are adhering to company credit terms and notifies supervisor and applicable departments if a problem exists to avoid interruptions in cash flow and to ensure profitability.</li>\n<li>Performs related duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>High School diploma or GED required and a minimum of one year experience working in an outside/commissioned sales position in a related industry is required.&nbsp; Experience as either a chef, foodservice/catering operations manager, or procurement manger is preferable.</li>\n<li>A demonstrated ability to plan and organize work activities; manage work time efficiently; follow procedures and policies; perform moderate mathematical calculations; identify and solve problems; write clearly and concisely.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of sales techniques, marketing principles, communications related to sales, credit and customer service activities.</li>\n<li>Must have computer skills in order to utilize sales tools and techniques and be proficient with office applications such as Microsoft Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.</li>\n<li>Must possess excellent interpersonal and communication abilities.</li>\n<li>Must possess and maintain a valid State of California Driver&rsquo;s License. A conviction for DUI within the last three years will render the candidate ineligible to apply.</li>\n<li>Must obtain and provide adequate liability insurance as determined by Sysco ($300,000 per accident, $100,000 per person, $100,000 property and uninsured motorist $30,000/$60,000).</li>\n<li>Must have reliable transportation for use in sales activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Preferred Requirements:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business, Sales, Marketing, Hospitality; or Culinary Arts.</li>\n<li>Restaurant management / chef experience.</li>\n<li>Preferred proved track record of successful selling and a stable work history.</li>\n<li><strong>Fluent in English/Chinese (Mandarin and/or Cantonese) or English/Spanish.</strong>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Competencies:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Building Trust</p>\n<p>Building Customer Loyalty</p>\n<p>Follow-up</p>\n<p>Sales Ability / Persuasiveness</p>\n<p>Managing Work</p>\n<p>Adaptability</p>\n<p>Communication</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Physical Demands:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This work requires the following physical activities: climbing, bending, stooping, kneeling, twisting, reaching, sitting, standing, walking, lifting up to 20 lbs. of material, finger dexterity for activities such as data entry and calculator use, grasping, repetitive motions, speaking, hearing, visual acuity, and mobility between departments.&nbsp;&nbsp; Use of both hands is required.&nbsp; The work is performed primarily indoors.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Applicants must be currently authorized to work in the U.S. on a full-time basis without future employment sponsorship.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sysco&nbsp;Los Angeles&nbsp;is proud to be an EEO/AA employer - M/F/D/V.</p>\n<p>This opportunity is available through Sysco&nbsp;Los Angeles.&nbsp; This is not a Corporate position.</p>\n<p><strong>All hiring decisions will be made at the sole discretion of Sysco&nbsp;Los Angeles.</strong></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://jobs-sysco.icims.com/jobs/13876/*marketing-associate--sysco-los-angeles-%28los-angeles%2c-ca-territory%29*/job?hub=7&mode=job&iis=Indeed&iisn=Indeed.com', '', 980, 160, 2),
