(621, 1407944885, '', 'Weill Cornell Medical College', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Position Title: Program Assistant II</p>\n<p>Working Title: Community Research Coordinator</p>\n<p>Department: Clinical and Translational Science Center</p>\n<p>Immediate Supervisor: JiFeng (Jeff) Zhu</p>\n<p>Minimum Salary: $41,144</p>\n<p>Salary Level: Grade 4</p>\n<p>Position Summary</p>\n<p>Under direction of the Program Director and Project Coordinator, the Program Assistant assists<br />in coordinating and developing existing community research programs that are part of the Weill<br />Cornell Medical College, Clinical and Translational Science Center (CTSC). This position<br />interacts with communities to maintain, expand, and develop CTSC community networks.<br />Assists in development of new community engagement programs, including community-based<br />research programs.</p>\n<p>Position Activities<br /> Assists with the evaluation and organization of community programs to assess their<br />impact on communities; assists with the creation and development of community based<br />programs and research studies.<br /> Assists in the identification and completion of grants and other funding sources for<br />community programs and projects.<br /> Completes regulatory paperwork with Program Coordinator in order to ensure<br />appropriate documentation of research activities and community based programs.<br /> Maintains contact with community organizations to organize and conduct community<br />events and expand community networks; maintain CTSC social media and web presence.<br /> Interacts with and translates for non-English speaking populations for community based<br />programs and research studies. Assists in the development of non-English versions of<br />research study materials and community based program information.<br /> Organizes and maintains study forms, documents, and applications for regulatory<br />purposes.<br /> Coordinates community outreach programs and research studies, including: coordinating<br />community sites with CTSC programs; ensuring that necessary staff, volunteers, faculty,<br />and or physicians are present at community events; coordinating logistics and<br />administrative tasks for community programs; advertising events; overseeing event setup;<br />and other administrative duties.<br /> Assists in analyzing current program components; assists in ensuring that study designs<br />adhere to Institutional Review Board (IRB), HIPAA, and other relevant guidelines;<br />maintains and analyzes research data.<br /> Participates in screening of potential research subjects, ensuring that subjects meet<br />appropriate criteria; answers inquiries about research protocols, notifies appropriate<br />research team members, Principal Investigators, and research subject advocates regarding<br />problems and concerns reported by subjects; performs other necessary administrative<br />duties to ensure the proper operation of research studies and community based programs.<br /> Performs other related duties as assigned.</p>\n<p>Qualifications</p>\n<p>Minimum Requirements<br /> High School Diploma required.<br /> Must be willing to work flexible hours as needed on evenings and/or weekends.<br /> At least 2 years'' work experience and/or research experience in a clinical or public health<br />setting.<br /> Must be willing to travel around New York City.</p>\n<p>Highly Desired Requirements<br /> Driver&rsquo;s License and willingness to drive around New York City.<br /> Past experience with clinical research studies.<br /> Proficiency in Chinese or Spanish.<br /> Familiarity with working with and engaging culturally and ethnically diverse<br />communities.<br /> Bachelor''s Degree.<br />Skill and Abilities<br /> Excellent organizational and time management skills and the ability to manage multiple<br />concurrent tasks.<br /> Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to communicate (oral and written)<br />professionally, quickly and accurately.<br /> Computer proficiency in Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Web-based calendar systems and email<br />required.<br /> Proficiency with Adobe CS software.<br />Physical Demands<br /> Must be willing to assist in moving teleconferencing equipment (50 lbs).</p>\n<p>No relocation assistance is provided for this position.<br />Visa sponsorship is not available for this position.</p>\n<p>Founded in 1898, and affiliated with what is now New York-Presbyterian Hospital since 1927,<br />Weill Cornell Medical College is among the top-ranked clinical and medical research centers in<br />the country. In addition to offering degrees in medicine, Cornell also has Ph.D. programs in<br />biomedical research and education at the Weill Graduate School of Medical Sciences, and with<br />neighboring Rockefeller University and the Sloan-Kettering Institute, has established a joint<br />MD-PhD. program for students to intensify their pursuit of Cornell''s triple mission of education,<br />research, and patient care.<br />Weill Cornell Medical College''s educational mission emphasizes the importance of combining a<br />strong foundation in the medical sciences with extensive clinical training in patient care. By<br />promoting a true social commitment, stimulating creativity, and fostering independent thought<br />and study, Weill Cornell Medical College continues to cultivate the best of tomorrow''s leaders in<br />the field of medicine.<br />Weill Cornell Medical College is an employer and educator recognized for valuing<br />AA/EOE/M/F/Protected Veterans, and Individuals with Disabilities</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Weill-Cornell-Medical-College/jobs/Program-Assistant-16b15f8c092bf967', '', 980, 144, 2),
(622, 1407945009, '', 'TUMI', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Maximizing&nbsp;sales by enhancing&nbsp;our brand image.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensuring a consistent and superior customer experience.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Development of&nbsp;new customer relationships and interaction&nbsp;with existing customers to increase sales.</p>\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attainment of&nbsp;monthly sales, conversion and other KPI goals.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>In addition to intelligence and&nbsp;high energy,&nbsp;the ideal candidates will have related luxury or specialty retail experience, a good selling presence and superior customer service skills. Fluency in both Mandarin Chinese and English is required.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://retailcareers-tumi.icims.com/jobs/2140/sales-associate-%28mandarin-chinese-speaking%29/job?mode=job&iis=Indeed&iisn=Indeed.com', '', 980, 132, 2),
(623, 1407946088, '', 'Wells Fargo', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table id="ACE_HRS_SCH_PSTDSC$0" class="PABACKGROUNDINVISIBLE" border="0" width="885" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$0"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$0" class="PABOLDTEXT">Job Description</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="18"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$0">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$0" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv326" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">\n<p>Wells Fargo Securities - Eastdil Secured</p>\n<p>Eastdil Secured is the foremost provider of financial advisory services to real estate owners.&nbsp; Eastdil Secured combines superior capital markets expertise with a deep understanding of real estate fundamentals to execute a wide range of real estate transactions for our clients ultimately producing superior results.&nbsp; By maintaining an effective platform that combines conventional real estate advisory and brokerage with the corporate finance and capital markets expertise of an investment bank, Eastdil Secured creates value for clients through unparalleled advisory services, individually-tailored structures, and marketing/placement programs that set the industry standard.&nbsp; Through the ability to navigate the challenges presented in any economic environment, Eastdil Secured maximizes opportunities with &ldquo;customer-crafted&rdquo;, revolutionary strategies that produce the most optimal and efficient transactions possible.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Our team is dedicated to the sale, financing and recapitalization of all major real estate product types including office, retail, hospitality, industrial and multifamily properties throughout North America.&nbsp; Widely recognized for our capital markets and real estate expertise, our team is also known for its distinguishing access and credibility, incomparable experience, outstanding client service, and proven track record.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Description:</p>\n<p>We are seeking an Analyst for the Asia transaction team based in our Santa Monica office..</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>- Working closely with senior team members on presentations and financial analysis</p>\n<p>- Assisting team in financial modeling for asset sales and debt placement transactions across all property types</p>\n<p>- Performing comprehensive and in-depth company, real estate, and market analysis</p>\n<p>- Due diligence collection and review</p>\n<p>- Creating pitches, proposals, and marketing materials</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$1"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$1" class="PABOLDTEXT">Basic Qualifications</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="18"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$1">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$1" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv212" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">1+ years account relationship or credit analyst experience.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$2"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$2" class="PABOLDTEXT">Minimum Qualifications</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="18"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$2">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$2" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv644" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">Demonstrated quantitative and technical abilities. Strong technical/computer skills to maintain various models, and handle multiple ad hoc requests. Ability to effectively communicate with varying internal bank personnel, customers, consultants, and external counsel. Working knowledge of MS Office applications.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$3"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$3" class="PABOLDTEXT">Additional Minimum Quals</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="18"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$3">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$3" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv612" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">\n<p>Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both English and Chinese (Mandarin) are required.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="20"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$4"><span id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCR$4" class="PABOLDTEXT">Preferred Qualifications</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td height="12"><img src="https://employment.wellsfargo.com/cs/PSEA/cache/PT_PIXEL_1.gif" alt="" /></td>\n<td align="left" valign="top">\n<div id="win0divHRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$4">\n<div id="HRS_SCH_PSTDSC_DESCRLONG$4" class="PSLONGEDITBOX"><br />\n<div id="RTEDiv907" class="PT_RTE_DISPLAYONLY">\n<p>Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, personal motivation, and distinguished written and oral communication skills. It is strongly preferred that your background includes:</p>\n<p>- Completion of a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree with above-average GPA at a reputable university</p>\n<p>- Coursework in financial accounting, finance and/or real estate</p>\n<p>- Internship and/or work experience with a focus on commercial real estate</p>\n<p>- Proficiency in real estate valuation utilizing Argus and Excel software</p>\n<p>- Dedication to building a career in the financial services industry with a focus on real estate finance</p>\n<p>- Willingness to work long hours in a demanding, highly focused, collaborative, and team environment</p>\n<p>- Energetic self-starter who is flexible, organized, conscientious, proactive, and detail-oriented</p>\n<p>- Ability to articulate goals, accomplishments and desire to be an Analyst</p>\n<p>- An individual who demonstrates a sense of personal accountability and urgency for achieving results</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'https://employment.wellsfargo.com/psc/PSEA/APPLICANT_NW/HRMS/c/HRS_HRAM.HRS_APP_SCHJOB.GBL?Page=HRS_APP_JBPST&FOCUS=Applicant&SiteId=1&JobOpeningId=5027576&PostingSeq=2&', '', 980, 212, 2),
