(632, 1408327572, '', 'Time Inc', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Intern, New Business Development &nbsp;&ndash; Time Inc.</strong><br />&nbsp;<br />Time Inc is one of the largest branded media companies in the world. The company engages more than 138 million U.S. consumers in print, online and via mobile devices each month. With influential brands such as TIME, PEOPLE, SPORTS ILLUSTRATED, INSTYLE, and REAL SIMPLE, Time Inc. has owned some of the biggest news stories of the decade and is home to celebrated franchises such as the FORTUNE 500, TIME 100, PEOPLE''s Most Beautiful and the SPORTS ILLUSTRATED Swimsuit Issue.<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Position Description:&nbsp;</strong><br />This is an intern role with the individual contributing to multiple projects at one time.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re looking for somebody who&rsquo;s good with research, data collection, analysis, creation of presentations and other written materials, and presentation and discussion of such materials with senior management. The intern will have exposure to all of Time Inc. (including magazines, all things digital and non-magazine operations) and across all of Time Inc. brands.<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Responsibilities can include projects in the following areas:&nbsp;</strong><br />- Strategic reviews (print and digital) for individual business units and Time Inc. as a whole<br />- New business development<br />- Evaluation of industry trends and competitive landscape<br />- Advertising sales go-to-market<br />- Strategic and operational implications of potential acquisitions or investments<br />- Customer segmentation<br />- Growth strategy<br />- Advertising solutions innovation<br />- Cross-divisional project management on ad hoc strategic initiatives<br />- Presentation creation for senior executives<br />- Financial and operating data gathering and analysis<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>The person:&nbsp;</strong><br />- Strong ownership and ability to work independently and be resourceful<br />- Excellent analytical skills, both quantitative and qualitative<br />- Ability to tackle unstructured problems and solve them<br />- Ability to interpret financial data<br />- Strong communication skills<br />- Strong interpersonal skills including ability to work in teams and to interact with internal and external senior level management<br />- Ability to work on multiple projects simultaneously and set priorities under tight timeframes in an unstructured environment<br />- Displays professional maturity and initiative<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Education and Background:&nbsp;</strong><br />&bull; Prior internship experience a plus<br />&bull; Knowledge and understanding media industry (including digital businesses)<br />&bull; MS Excel, Word and Powerpoint<br />&nbsp;<br />To apply, please include a cover letter with your submittal. Tell us about yourself and why you&rsquo;d be a good fit for this position and for Time Inc.<br />&nbsp;<br />Time Inc. is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to attracting, retaining and maximizing the performance of a diverse and inclusive workforce.</p>', 'https://careers.timeinc.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?jobId=682978&PartnerId=25960&SiteId=36', '', 980, 183, 2),
(629, 1408202966, ' 10%', 'M&E Financial Group', 'Finance', '', 'United States', 'Illinois', 'Chicago', 41.878113, -87.629799, '', '', '', 'H1B', 'Part Time', '<p>M&amp;E Financial Group </p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>mli@thebizcash.com 626-376-0501</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>M&amp;E Financial Group is Hiring Full Time &amp; Part Time Chinese Market Commercial Loan Agent</p>\n<p>Could work at home, flexible working time, 10% commission.</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>Could file tax within United States</p>\n<p>Good communication and sales skills</p>\n<p>Finance industry experience preferred</p>\n<p>Sales experience preferred</p>\n<p>Mandarin and Cantonese speaking agents preferred</p>\n<p>Insurance agents and real estate agents are welcomed to work as part time employees</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Company Address: 2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>Please send your resume to <a href="mailto:mli@thebizcash.com">mli@thebizcash.com</a> or call 626-376-0501</p>', '', 'mli@thebizcash.com', 1044, 189, 2),
(630, 1408218654, '', 'America Chung Nam', 'Management', 'City of Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are looking for experienced and professional administrative individuals to join our growing company.&nbsp;&nbsp;The main duties are to provide administrative support to a member of our senior management team.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Job duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Produce reports, summaries, communications and other information for senior management using available technologies.</li>\n<li>Handle requests for information, most of which are highly confidential, preparing all correspondences.</li>\n<li>Support the senior management team member by reading, researching, and routing correspondences; drafting letters and documents; collecting and analyzing information; initiating telecommunications.</li>\n<li>Maintain appointment schedule by planning and scheduling meetings, conferences, teleconferences, and travel.</li>\n<li>Accurately represent the senior management team member by attending meetings in their absence.</li>\n<li>Greeting clients and guests in person or on the telephone.</li>\n<li>Prepare reports by collecting and analyzing information.</li>\n<li>Provide historical reference by developing and utilizing filing and retrieval systems; recording meeting discussions.</li>\n<li>Maintain office supplies inventory by checking stock to determine inventory level; anticipating needed supplies; evaluating new office products; placing and expediting orders for supplies; verifying receipt of supplies.</li>\n<li>Maintain professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating in professional societies.</li>\n<li>Perform other administrative duties as assigned or requested.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;Job requirements are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>REQUIRED: Strong Proficiency in English and Chinese</strong></li>\n<li><strong>REQUIRED: Excellence in Written and Verbal Communication in English and Chinese.</strong></li>\n<li>College degree preferred.</li>\n<li>Highly desired characteristics: honesty, dependability, and hard working.</li>\n<li>Detail-oriented and proactive thinker.</li>\n<li>Relentless follow-up skills with a friendly and positive attitude.</li>\n<li>Ability to Multi-Task.</li>\n<li>Excellent computer skills with MS Office and Outlook</li>\n<li>Local Candidates Preferred</li>\n</ul>', 'http://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?k=Job&c=qnz9VfwK&j=oAfoZfwW&s=Indeed', '', 980, 148, 2),
(631, 1408249156, 'Senior Accountant - External Reporting', '', 'Management', 'Parsippany-Troy Hills, NJ, United States', 'United States', 'New Jersey', 'Parsippany-Troy Hills', 40.859634, -74.423347, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="description-module container">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="description-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Tiffany &amp; Co. is currently seeking a Senior Accountant &ndash; External Reporting. The Senior Accountant &ndash; External Reporting will be responsible for assisting with the coordination and preparation of the Company''s external financial reporting requirements and other required government (census) reporting. Additionally, this position will assist with the preparation and review of other financial statements such as for the Company&rsquo;s pension and 401(K) plans. This individual will partner with Investor Relations and business units across the Company to gather and analyze information to be included in the Company&rsquo;s publicly reported financial information.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Senior Accountant &ndash; External Reporting will assist with the preparation of SEC-compliant quarterly 10-Q filings, Press Releases and the Company''s Annual Report (Form 10-K and Proxy). Responsibilities include researching, drafting and supporting footnote and MD&amp;A disclosures. S/he will also coordinate and complete special projects as requested by management, as well as assist in the preparation of various internal reports as requested by management. The Senior Accountant will assist with the preparation of other financial statements such as for the Company&rsquo;s pension plan and the 401k plan. This position will prepare and submit all required U.S. Government and Canadian census filings.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="skills-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Desired Skills and Experience</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>To be qualified for this position you must have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A 4 year Accounting degree</li>\n<li>4+ years professional experience</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of U.S. GAAP, including experience in researching accounting literature</li>\n<li>Strong communication (oral and written), listening and analytical skills</li>\n<li>Ability to manage own work and multi-task amid shifting priorities</li>\n<li>Ability to work under tight deadlines and must be willing to work extended hours</li>\n<li>Ability to interface with all levels of management as well as with external auditors\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Preferred Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CPA strongly preferred</li>\n<li>Experience working with HFM and JD Edwards</li>\n<li>Experience working with WebFilings and knowledge of XBRL reporting requirements</li>\n<li>Previous experience, such as public accounting or comparable accounting/finance experience, with 10Q, 10K and other SEC filings</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id="company-module" class="company-module container">\n<h2 class="container-header">About this company</h2>\n<div class="content">\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Tiffany &amp; Co. operates jewelry and specialty retail stores and manufactures products through its subsidiary corporations. Its principal subsidiary is Tiffany and Company. The Company operates TIFFANY &amp; CO. retail stores and boutiques in the Americas, Asia-Pacific and Europe and engages in direct selling through Internet, catalog and business gift operations. Other operations include consolidated results from ventures operated under trademarks or trade names other than TIFFANY &amp; CO.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/18670815?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3301255351408139899981%2CVSRPtargetId%3A18670815%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 125, 2),
