(649, 1408843280, '', 'LinguaLearn', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>LinguaLearn is currently seeking native speakers of the following foreign languages to teach their language to language learners through Skype: Dutch, French, German, Greek, Hindi, Indonesian, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Mandarin Chinese, Mixteco, Nahuatl, Portuguese, Quechua (of Cuzco), Spanish, Swedish, Tagalog (Filipino), Vietnamese, and Yucatec Maya. To apply, you do not necessarily need to already be an experienced professional teacher, but please respond to the following questions in your application:</p>\n<p>1. What is your name (first and last)?</p>\n<p>2. What is your native language/language you want to teach?</p>\n<p>3. Please provide a general outline (in any form you desire) of how you plan to teach the language to your students. (For example, "I plan to start with greetings and introductions in the first lesson, then...") Please be as detailed as you can.</p>\n<p>4. Do you have any experience teaching the language? (Note that lack of experience does not automatically disqualify you from being hired.) If so, please describe.</p>\n<p>5. Do you have any kind of certificate of sufficient knowledge of your native language? (Again, if you do not, this does not automatically disqualify you from being hired.) If so, please upload a copy of the certificate and include it in the email as an attachment.</p>\n<p>6. In what country do you currently reside?</p>\n<p>7. Please note that we are more interested in you being passionate about teaching your language, and having a good plan/method to teach your language, therefore being able to teach it well, than we are in holding of credentials (although credentials may also be taken into consideration). Thus, please describe why you think you would make a good language teacher, and if you feel you have the sufficient passion for the language to teach it.</p>\n<p>8. It is of utmost importance that the teacher not be in any way, shape, or form, rude, disrespectful, judgmental, condescending, or impatient towards his/her student(/s). Violation of this policy will not be tolerated, and students will be given the opportunity to report violation of this if they need to. If you prepared to refrain from displaying these qualities regardless of the student''s personal qualities, including, but not limited to, age, gender, religion, nationality, sexual orientation, and demeanor, then please respond "Yes." Otherwise, you need not apply.</p>\n<p>9. Another policy that will not be tolerated on part of the teacher is not showing up for the student''s lesson(s). Do you promise to respect this policy? (Yes/No)</p>\n<p>Please note that lessons will be reviewed by the students on our website, so the higher ratings you get for your lessons, the more likely students will be to book their lessons with you.</p>\n<p>Pay rate will be $20 per each hour of teaching.</p>\n<p>After we receive your emailed application, you will be contacted within 24 hours informing and congratulating you if you have been hired. Thank you very much for applying, and good luck in the application process! : )</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/LinguaLearn/jobs/Foreign-Language-Instructor-13c9e3d4e55e3e28', '', 980, 187, 2),
