(644, 1408590175, '', 'Harley Ellis Devereaux', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table id="CRCareers1_tblJobDescrDetail" border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="JDHeaderStyle" colspan="2">Job Responsibilities:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="MainBodyText" colspan="2">This position will provide detailed administrative project support and requires both knowledge of architecture/engineering/construction project processing and strong general hands on administrative skills.<br /><br />PRIMARY FUNCTIONS:<br /><br />Provide word processing for specifications and contracts (AIA forms) to create Project Manuals and Office Master Specification and Provide administrative support to one or more Managers or Project Teams, including maintaing individual and project related schedules.<br /><br />TYPICAL DUTIES&nbsp;<br />&bull;Type project specifications and AIA contract forms using all aspects of the word processing system including spell check, editing techniques and program enhancements to maximize efficient use of the system.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Make typing revisions to specifications for revised editions (i.e. Addenda/Bulletins, Construction Issues etc.) including format revisions to pages as required.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Assemble Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues by obtaining the Project Master folder and pulling the corresponding front or back sheet master to maintain "two-sided" specification page formatting.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Type Office Master Specifications (used in reproduction of the ivory master "mark-ups"), using all aspects of the word processing system.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Whenever possible, proofread work directly from computer screen. When necessary, work with another processor to ensure accuracy.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Return typed, proofread specifications to author.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Advise Manager of Specifications of problems with workload, scheduling or equipment and software.&nbsp;<br />&bull;File Project Specification Masters after project is run for issue. Subsequent Addenda, Bulletins and Construction Issues shall be filed with Project Masters (in proper location to ensure Project Master folder is always complete and current. Previous issue Project Masters will be replaced by current versions and stored in the back of the Project Master).&nbsp;<br />&bull;Work with managers assigned to desk to become a valued team member. Develop good rapport and interaction with other staff and with the Company''s clients.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Prepare a variety of documents; letters, reports, spreadsheets, memos, confidential material lists, etc.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Compile/prepare various reports for manager''s use or distribution. Write reports, memos or letters for manager''s signature or distribution.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Create and maintain filing system; maintain required records for manager and team. Maintain updated job log for desk.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Answer phones, screen calls, take and forward messages, answer routine questions and follow through on requests. Organize priority items for manager''s attention. Screen and route mail/phone messages during manager''s absence.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Maintain electronic calendar for manager and review with them daily. Keep switchboard informed of their availability.&nbsp;<br />&bull;May be required to relieve the switchboard.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Perform routine administrative duties involved in the operation of office programs, projects and activities, many of which are confidential and require the use of judgment, tact and knowledge of our Operations and Personnel standards.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Provide assistance with work overload from other desks when necessary.&nbsp;<br />&bull;May be responsible for, or cross-trained for corporate travel including airline, hotel and car reservations, preparation of itineraries; schedule meetings and take minutes; preparation of confidential government reports; handling of confidential personnel information; client proposals/contracts containing employee rates; maintain telephone or voice mail systems, maintaining office project files; maintenance of office lists (i.e. phone extensions, home addresses, etc.); or conference room scheduling and distribution of daily schedules.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="JDHeaderStyle" colspan="2">Job Qualifications:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="MainBodyText" colspan="2">&bull;High school diploma.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Minimum three years word processing and secretarial experience or two-year degree in Secretarial Science.<br />&bull;Bilingual written and verbal skills in Mandarin Chinese is required<br />&bull;Excellent proofreading, grammar and typing skills.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Working knowledge of business procedures, letter/report formats, business machines, transcription equipment and general office routines necessary.<br />&bull;Ability to type 65-75 wpm accurately.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Computer literacy with experience in word processing software.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;<br />&bull;Ability to sit for long periods of time.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Ability to use office equipment for communication and documentation purposes.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Visual acuity to perform responsibilities.&nbsp;<br />&bull;Ability to access and file documents from file drawers.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://cr.harleyellisdevereaux.com/careers/Careers.aspx?adata=EBT4ezAzJhY8XLyYOaB3ATRAA2oqS1i7JYOGtdvKjn%2bK05nTwIJc80qAt60R5tvHhX9VfohKCf8p1CwU%2fowhvUhnsxkT9Jk7OoXj8Hwsbt%2fRviSPJphOsFfz0vCF1lzZFphz1RsYYtoNZ0Gj9w3w3ZSsrF33zIPPrne7cRJCbn%2bFZKkVcILwsEsTR28JsNY3LkuDZbNshdjVC6TAGjfG2j0hvVPJIqOU7ElmkDFeTdHF', '', 980, 153, 2),
(646, 1408650504, '', 'Wells Fargo ', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="content-sections">\n<section id="job-description-section" class="minimized">\n<h2>JOB DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<div id="pnlJobDescription" class="section-body">\n<p>IMPORTANT NOTE:&nbsp; Please ensure your contact information (e-mail address and phone number) is current in your Wells Fargo Jobs Profile. Initial contact will be made via e-mail. Please check your e-mail regularly for updates.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Please note: If there is an exceptionally high volume of applicants for this job posting, this job posting may close before the indicated expiration date.</p>\n<p>Currently hiring for a training class starting on August 4<sup>th</sup>.&nbsp; Training hours are 8:30am &ndash;5:00pm Monday-Friday for 6 weeks (Must be available to attend entire paid training class).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Current schedules being offered after training will be:</p>\n<p>Mandarin &ndash; 8:00am-4:30pm or 9:00am-5:30pm with Saturday and Sunday off</p>\n<p>Cantonese &ndash; 6:00am-2:30pm with Saturday and Sunday off</p>\n<p>Salary Range - $13.62/hr. - $14.81/hr. DOE plus eligible to participate in the WFCC Service Incentive Plan</p>\n<p>Our next big investment is in you!&nbsp; Wells Fargo offers:</p>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><br />A broad array of medical, dental, and vision plans</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Paid Time Off</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>401 (k) and Stock Purchase Plans</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Discounts and Savings on Wells Fargo financial products, home mortgages and services</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Tuition Reimbursement</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Wellness Benefits</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Commuter Benefits</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<p>Please review the requirements for a Phone Banker before applying<strong>.</strong>&nbsp; A Phone Banker spends nearly 100% of his/her time on the phone answering questions for Wells Fargo customers. The working environment is fun and relaxed with a casual dress code but is also demanding and structured, and involves overcoming customers&rsquo; banking concerns which can include some escalated issues.</p>\n<p>Phone Bankers are expected to sell products and services and achieve aggressive sales goals which are measured daily.&nbsp; Our best Phone Bankers thrive on customer interaction and never miss an opportunity to enhance the customer&rsquo;s relationship with Wells Fargo by marketing new products and services. They always handle each customer with a friendly, courteous touch while following strict procedures for handling various types of inquiries.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We provide our Phone Bankers with continuous coaching and development which not only enhances their ability to provide exemplary service and product solutions to our customers, but also enhances the Phone Bankers&rsquo; career growth. Our successful bankers demonstrate self-motivation, a positive attitude, have the ability to work well on a team and have a solid work history.&nbsp; They also demonstrate strong listening, written and verbal communication skills.&nbsp; They are receptive to coaching and feedback, have the desire to meet/exceed goals and solve problems while working in a fast paced environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Our Phone Bankers play a critical role in our customers&rsquo; lives; therefore, predictable and reliable attendance is an essential function of the position.&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="jobDescriptionTextFade">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-requirements">\n<h2>JOB REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<div class="section-body"><strong>* Basic Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong><br />6 months customer service and sales experience.<br /><br /><strong>* Minimum Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong><br />\n<p>Basic computer skills including the ability to navigate multiple windows and applications and utilize search tools to find information.</p>\n<p>6+ months sales experience (list specific sales experience in resume/work history)</p>\n<p>Experience with supporting both Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese) and English speaking customers.<br /><br /><br />The successful passing of the language proficiency assessment (speaking and reading) is required to qualify for the bilingual Chinese (Mandarin/Cantonese)/English queue (administered during the interviewing process).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section id="job-snapshot-section">\n<h2>JOB SNAPSHOT</h2>\n<div class="section-body">\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Employment Type</strong>Full-Time</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Job Type</strong>Sales, Banking</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Education</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Experience</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Manages Others</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Industry</strong>Banking - Financial Services</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Required Travel</strong>Not Specified</div>\n<div class="snap-line"><strong>Job ID</strong>5009238<br /><br /></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>', 'http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/jobs/jobdetails.aspx?Job_DID=J3F3CT65C1GK8L7T6R7&siteid=sep_cb001_13_2072_00&showNewJDP=yes&ipath=EXGOO', '', 980, 163, 2),
