(648, 1408740476, '', 'East West Bank', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" width="92%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" align="center">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span class="TEXT"><span class="TEXT">East West Bank is a one of the largest independent banks headquartered in California serving consumers and businesses throughout the U.S. and Greater China. East West Bank is publicly traded with 27.4 billion in assets. With over 130 locations worldwide including California, Texas, New York, Georgia, Massachusetts, Nevada, Washington, and Greater China &ndash;East West Bank is committed to helping their customers&rsquo; enterprises succeed. At East West Bank, we build bridges that provide an important financial link that turns opportunities into growth and prosperity.<br /><br />As an East West Bank employee, you will be part of a growing and stable organization that provides career path development opportunities while serving a growing and profitable market.<br /><br />As a valuable East West Bank team member, your duties (not limited to) will include:&nbsp;<br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Expand customer portfolio and develop new business opportunities&nbsp;</li>\n<li>New Accounts&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Consumer and Commercial lending&nbsp;</li>\n<li>International Banking&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Work closely with other business units to create sales opportunities for the Bank</li>\n</ul>\n<span class="TEXT"><span class="TEXT">Qualifications/Requirements:&nbsp;<br /></span></span><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Bilingual in English and Chinese (Mandarin) is a plus&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Understanding of East West Bank&rsquo;s processes to exercise the Bridge Banking concept&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Strong ownership&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Self-motivator with sense of urgency to serve and develop business&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Ability to meet and exceed goals successfully by managing daily and weekly sales routines/activities</li>\n</ul>\n<p>East West Bank is an Equal Opportunity Employer<br /><br />&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Job Family">Job Family</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Job Family" class="TEXT">Commercial Banking</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Auto req ID">Auto req ID</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Auto req ID" class="TEXT">3821BR</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Position Type">Position Type</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Position Type" class="TEXT">Full-Time</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Country">Country</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="Country" class="TEXT">United States</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="State / Province">State / Province</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="80%"><span id="State / Province" class="TEXT">New York</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'https://sjobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?jobId=1906378&PartnerId=25446&SiteId=5504', '', 980, 154, 2),
(653, 1409028996, '', 'M&E Financial Group', 'Finance', 'Irvine, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Irvine', 33.683949, -117.794693, '', '', '', 'H1B', 'Part Time', '<p>M&amp;E Financial Group </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>10%5</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>mli@thebizcash.com 626-376-0501</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>M&amp;E Financial Group is Hiring Full Time &amp; Part Time Commercial Loan Agent.</p>\n<p>Could work at home, flexible working time, 10% commission. Commission would be distributed to agents&rsquo; bank account within 5 days after the funding of the loan. If clients default, agents have no responsibility.</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>Could file tax within United States</p>\n<p>Good communication and sales skills</p>\n<p>Finance industry experience preferred</p>\n<p>Sales experience preferred</p>\n<p>Insurance agents and real estate agents are welcomed to work as part time employees</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Company Address: 2082 Business Center Drive, Suite 195, Irvine, CA 92612</p>\n<p>Please send your resume to <a href="mailto:mli@thebizcash.com">mli@thebizcash.com</a> or call 626-376-0501</p>', 'http://www.thebizcash.com/', 'mli@thebizcash.com', 1044, 201, 2),
(654, 1409078814, '', 'Chinese Language Academy of Los Angeles', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>Chinese Language Instructor position (part-time) available at Chinese Language Academy of Los Angeles. We offer competitive salary and a supportive environment for your to grow. The Chinese Language teacher will be developing curriculum and instructing students of various levels and backgrounds. Since we offer classes at the client&rsquo;s site (LA County and Orange County) as well, the actual teaching place may vary.</p>\n<p>Job Qualifications:<br />1. Native fluency in Chinese Mandarin;<br />2. Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree or above in Chinese Linguistics, Chinese Literature, Foreign Language Education, Asian Studies or a closely related field. A Master''s degree is strongly preferred;<br />3. High proficiency level in English; a deep understanding of American culture;<br />4. At least two years&rsquo; experience in teaching Chinese as a foreign language in a classroom setting;<br />5. Knowledge of current teaching methodologies and practices in teaching Chinese language in the U.S..<br />6. Currently live in Greater Los Angeles area.</p>\n<p>Only candidates who have met all qualifications above will be considered. If interested, please send your resume and cover letter.</p>\n<p>Your resume will be thoroughly reviewed. Degree verification, reference checks and background check will be conducted on provisionally hired instructor(s) prior to the first class.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your interest!</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Chinese-Language-Academy/jobs/Chinese-Mandarin-Instructor-b080a7ea3ba751ce', '', 980, 191, 2),
(651, 1409007004, '', 'Cartier', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Cartier, l''artisan des passions.<br />Purpose<br />We are seeking a Team Player who represents the highest standards of the Maison to assist with providing<br />sales assistance to all boutique staff and clients as needed.<br />Responsibilities<br />- Greet the clients in a professional and positive Cartier manner.<br />- Determine through detailed and specific discovery process the objectives of the client&rsquo;s visit.<br />- Escort the client to a viewing desk and deliver refreshments personally or with the aid of the available<br />boutique assistants.<br />- Assist in managing the phone volume and delegate the calls to the proper people through systematic<br />allocation.<br />- Assist in the merchandising and overall daily maintenance of the HJ cases and under stock.<br />- Maintain proper visual standards for all HJ cases, including jewelry polishing/steam cleaning.<br />- Qualify sales leads and assure each is directed to the appropriate sales team member in a systematic<br />manner.<br />- Maintain and update VIP client-care and event list database by partnering with HJ Sales Associates and<br />Management.<br />- Daily review of open service orders for HJ sales.<br />- Call clients as needed for service order pick up.<br />- Special projects as needed.<br />- Rotation into other departments as needed for similar responsibilities.<br />Profile<br />- Excellent interpersonal and communication skills are required<br />- Must be available to work retail hours including weekends<br />- Previous experience in luxury retail or hospitality is a plus<br />www.cartier.comales Assistant<br />- Strong understanding of Customer Service needs and Customer (internal and external) priorities<br />- Strong attention to detail with the ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously and with precision.<br />- Bi Lingual or tri lingual Chinese or Portuguese would be a plus<br />- Professional appearance, demeanor and communication needed<br />- Self-Starter with Team-Player approach<br />- Detail oriented<br />- Data Entry as needed<br />- 4-year College degree preferred<br />Type of Position<br />Permanent<br />Work Location<br />USA - New York<br />Contact<br />Should you wish to apply, simply click the "Apply" button above. We look forward to hearing from you.<br />Our employees are part of a global family working in a fair, open and trusted environment. It is important for us to<br />ensure that new employees joining the Group have a strong commitment to our shared values.<br />We therefore reserve the right to ask all candidates in the final stages of recruitment to undergo a pre-employment<br />screening. Our approach to pre-employment screening is based on the principles of transparency, mutual respect and is<br />conducted in line with all applicable regulations.</p>', 'https://jobs.richemont.com/sap/bc/webdynpro/sap/hrrcf_a_posting_apply?PARAM=cG9zdF9pbnN0X2d1aWQ9NTNERjExQzk5NzU3MDkzMEUxMDA4MDAwMEEyNDA3REMmY2FuZF90eXBlPUVYVCZwYz0y&sap-ep-themeroot=SAP_CORBU&sap-client=010&sap-language=EN#', '', 980, 168, 2),
(652, 1409008712, '', 'VisaHQ', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<section class="section section--text">\n<h2 class="section__header">DESCRIPTION</h2>\n<p>We are looking for a full-time Passport and Visa Specialist to join our growing team in Los Angeles, CA. There is a good potential for growth with and within the company.<br /><br />Work directly with the Department of State, Embassies and Consulates. Receive, prepare, and submit applications for travel visas to various countries. Provide wide range of support to our clients that include answering telephone calls, emailing, responding to inquires, and using a variety of online applications. The person in this position must be highly organized, detailed oriented, and punctual.</p>\n</section>\n<section class="section section--text">\n<h2 class="section__header">REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>At least an Associate''s Degree</li>\n<li>Experience in the field of travel preparation is highly desired</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\n<li>Knowledge of foreign languages is preferred (Russian, Spanish, Chinese, French)</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class="section section--text">\n<h2 class="section__header">BENEFITS</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive salary</li>\n<li>Medical and dental insurance</li>\n<li>Vacation, sick days</li>\n<li>Paid holidays</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>About VisaHQ</em></strong></p>\n<p>VisaHQ is undisputed leader of the passport and visa services industry in North America. We are privately owned, nimble, and technology savvy. We pioneered the shift to online visa application processing, and we have a sustainable competitive edge that is widening every day.&nbsp;We have 8 offices across the United States and Canada, as well as a number of international offices.&nbsp;We have been ranked as an Inc 5,000 fastest growing company three times in a row, including a top-20 ranking in the travel industry and a number 1 position in the D.C. metro area.</p>\n<p><em><strong>We are on the move... Join us!</strong></em></p>\n</section>', 'http://visahq.workable.com/jobs/16935', '', 980, 185, 2),
