(656, 1409114799, 'google', 'google', 'Technology', 'Beijing, China', 'China', 'Beijing', 'Beijing', 39.904030, 116.407524, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<p>The Online Partnerships Group (OPG) uses our portfolio of product solutions, including AdSense and DoubleClick tools, to help online publishers grow their businesses. You''ll provide innovative, industry-leading online advertising solutions for publishers and developers and proactively identify new opportunities. Some of the largest publishers on the web rely on our products and we''re always trying to exceed their expectations and strengthen our long-term partner relationships. Our team helps grow Google''s business with the largest online publishers and provides account management for users of AdSense, DoubleClick and more.</p>\n<p>As an Acquisition Strategist, you will proactively identify the growth opportunities for online or mobile partnerships and acquire prospective publishers to AdSense or AdMob networks. You have advanced data and analytical capabilities to identify large opportunities from the market. Your knowledge of online media combined with your communication skills and analytical abilities shapes how new business grows. You leverage your entrepreneurial drive to target, educate and persuade new customers to embrace Google''s latest advertising products and technologies. Using your influencing and relationship-building skills, you provide Google-caliber client service, research and market analysis. You anticipate how decisions are made, understand the industry and verticals as well as details of individual campaigns and persistently explore and uncover the business needs of clients.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="heading">Responsibilities</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>Acquire new customers to the network and build a&nbsp;strong&nbsp;pipeline for sustainable business growth.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with global teams to meet local markets'' expectations.</li>\n<li>Scalable initiatives for the larger pool of publishers to drive business growth and customer satisfaction.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="tagstory">\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Minimum qualifications</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience</li>\n<li>Ability to speak and write Mandarin and English fluently and idiomatically.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Preferred qualifications</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<ul>\n<li>MBA or advanced degree.</li>\n<li>Technology/online industry experience. Knowledgeable about consumer mobile products, internet, online products, customers, online advertising technologies and strategies, and market dynamics.</li>\n<li>Working experience in internet, advertising, e-commerce, publishing and online services. Ad sales experience.</li>\n<li>Self-directed, motivated and&nbsp;driven&nbsp;performer with exceptional multi-tasking abilities toward goals.</li>\n<li>Strategic thinking and&nbsp;strong&nbsp;data analysis skills.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="heading">Area</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<p>There''s always more information out there, and our Partnerships team works to get it. We develop relationships with a range of organizations, from content providers to publishers, and find ways for them to reach their audiences and manage their digital businesses. We find great content for our products, and we also work with partner sites to syndicate our own Google products. From&nbsp;negotiating&nbsp;agreements to solving technical problems for partners, we''re in pursuit of gathering the world''s information.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-content offset">\n<div class="tagstory">\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Partnerships</div>\n<img class="conditional-format" src="https://www.google.com/about/careers/files/team_partnerships_image_348x348.jpg" alt="" />\n<div class="conditional-format">\n<p>Expand our business into new territories.</p>\n<span style="color: #444444;"><a href="http://www.google.com/about/careers/teams/partnerships/">Learn more about our Partnerships teams</a></span></div>\n</div>\n<div class="double">\n<div class="heading">Beijing</div>\n<img class="conditional-format" src="https://www.google.com/about/careers/files/location_beijing_image_348x348.jpg" alt="" />\n<div class="conditional-format">\n<p>As Google''s biggest office in China, we&rsquo;re located in a part of Beijing known as a tech epicenter. Our Googlers come from across the country and around the world, and we&rsquo;re home to engineers developing core Google products for global markets and sales teams working with advertisers big and small.</p>\n<span style="color: #444444;"><a href="http://www.google.com/about/careers/locations/beijing/">Learn more about our Beijing office</a></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="detail-item">\n<div class="heading">Job details</div>\n<div class="detail-content">\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Team or role:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Partnerships</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Job type:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Full-time</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Last updated:</div>\n<div class="info-text">Jul 23, 2014</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class="greytext info">Job location(s):</div>\n<div class="info-text">Beijing, Beijing, China</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.google.com/about/careers/search?from=singlemessage&isappinstalled=0#!t=jo&jid=36605001&', '', 980, 132, 2),
(657, 1409185049, '', 'Markwins International Corporation', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Markwins is an global cosmetic manufacturer with expertly designed cosmetics and beauty care collection. We have leading beauty brands of Monster High, Front Cover, Wet n Wild, and Fergie both global and nationwide trend focused. We are seeking professional Senior Cost Accountant to join the US headquarters in City of Industry.</p>\n<p>Responsible for cost accounting, analysis and associated management including formulation of procedures and deal with external auditors<br />- Prepare, analyze and report weekly, monthly &amp; quarterly gross margin analysis by brand by customer type<br />- Analyze cost accounting data and assist with cycle count/physical inventories<br />- Prepare detailed account analysis and reconcile sales, cost and inventory, liability accounts by customer type by division<br />- Review and analyze inventory and margin reports, conduct research and perform analytical studies in regards to cost analysis and profitability<br />- Assist in month end closing, prepare journal entries as necessary, analyze inventory evaluation, inventory roll forward<br />- Communicate daily with China accounting team to work on the accounting books and coordinate with China manufacturing department<br />- Support and assist internal department reporting requirements such as audit &amp; tax schedules; deal with internal and external auditors<br />- Monitor inventory, costing, gross margin schedules and ensure timely submission to management<br />- Monitor and check the rationality of original expenses evidences<br />- Evaluate and audit the performance of factory productivity</p>\n<p>We require a Bachelors Degree in Accounting with 3+ years of related experience, proficient in Microsoft Excel &amp; Office and is able to adapt to different computer programs for efficient data gathering and analysis, strong organizational and communication skills. Able to research, compile, analyze, interpret data with recommendation. Able to work on details, analyze and reconcile complex accounts and reserves. Knowledge of GAAP &amp; cost accounting standards is required. Knowledge of Power Link systems is preferred. Cosmetic industry background is a plus. Able to work independently under minimal supervision. Bilingual/Chinese is required.</p>\n<p>Qualified candidates should submit their full resume with salary history and expectation to Human Resources via either facsimile (909) 595-8820 or email. Only local candidate without the need for work visa sponsorship will be considered. Ref- CA</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Markwins-International-Corporation/jobs/Senior-Cost-Accountant-44feda1d2b4ca203', '', 980, 121, 2),
