(683, 1410655667, '', 'First Pay Solutions', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>First Pay Solutions was established in 2002 with the goal of setting an innovative standard in merchant payment processing. By offering merchants the ability to accept electronic payments, backed by cutting-edge technology, PCI-compliant software, terminals &amp; POS systems, outstanding service and a strict code of ethical business practices, First Pay Solution has become a partner in the growth and success of our merchant customers.</p>\n<p>Our mission is to offer quick, secure and reliable payment processing solutions to merchants whether they are small or large businesses. This vision has taken First Pay Solutions from a two-man operation to one of the country''s fastest-growing businesses, with a portfolio of nearly 20,000 merchants and growing.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assist customers and sale agents with technical support for POS equipments and credit card terminals including Nurit, Hypercom, Verifone, Eclipse, check services, and wireless terminals;</li>\n<li>Replace and reprogram equipment;</li>\n<li>Daily functions included account updates and ownership changes;</li>\n<li>Inspect returned equipment for functionality and possible replacement issues;</li>\n<li>Provide technical support for all POS equipments and credit card terminals such as general</li>\n</ul>\n<p>troubleshooting, downloading new applications and training;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Set up new account entries in the gateway and assisted with shopping cart integration.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Qualifications</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bilingual in Chinese and English is required;</li>\n<li>Experience in merchant service industry preferred;</li>\n<li>Efficient in Microsoft Applications such as Word, Excel and Outlook;</li>\n<li>Strong responsibility ethics and able to work well with a team;</li>\n<li>Professional attitude and dependable;</li>\n<li>Extremely organized and detail oriented with strong follow-through skills;</li>\n<li>Ability to maintain calm under pressure;</li>\n<li>Proficient with Microsoft Office; and</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Salary<br />Commensurate with experience.</p>\n<p>Application<br />Send resume, cover letter and salary history in the email. Use the following format in the subject line: first name and last name, job title of position you are applying for.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/First-Pay-Solutions/jobs/Technical-Support-Representative-d8272df678a7e09e', '', 980, 115, 2),
(684, 1410655752, '', 'Flushing Endoscopy Center ', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>New and fast growing outpatient facility in Flushing, Queens in need of an assistant for the accounting/finance department.<br />Candidate must have a can-do attitude and the ability to multitask; must be a team player and willing to take initiatives.<br />Must be fluent with windows and Microsoft office<br />Must be generally comfortable with technology, a quick learner with new IT software and hardware<br />Must be detail oriented<br />Must be excited about learning new things and not afraid to ask questions<br />Must be a strong communicator in BOTH oral and written forms; bilingual with strong English plus Chinese/Korean/Spanish preferred but not required<br />You must have a background and work experience in accounting, financial management, insurances or business administration.<br />Experience in bookkeeping or healthcare billing a big plus</p>\n<p>What we can offer:<br />$12-20 an hour with company sponsored health benefits and paid vacation time<br />Potential to grow and valuable learning experience</p>\n<p>Please email your resume with &ldquo;Financial Assistant&rdquo; in the subject line</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Flushing-Endoscopy-Center/jobs/Finance-Accounting-Assistant-c7ac55d3ff1d5414', '', 980, 200, 2),
