(692, 1410921937, 'C/C++ Developer - Network Design and Security', 'Bloomberg', 'Media', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>CS. 3+C/C++ Python and/or Perl,  . Data Structures, Algorithms, and Object-Oriented design</p>\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text"><strong>Job Requisition Number:</strong>42540<br /><br />The Role:<br /><br />Bloomberg''s Network Design Information Security (NDIS) Team is looking for a developer to provide the building blocks for an automation system encompassing both Open Source and third party vendor solutions that will encompass all aspects of monitoring, alarming, and network security configuration for several hundred proxy servers, firewalls, caches, and load balancers. The successful detail-oriented candidate will have the opportunity to work on the initial builds and implementation of this multi- platform and multi-tiered system, and be involved from requirements generation, to development planning, development, implementation, and feature and bug fix prioritization.<br /><br />Responsibilities:<br /><br />- Evaluate new technologies and growing NDIS'' internal automation projects<br />- Evaluate infrastructure requirements from dev and design/deploy production solutions<br />- Create productive models for integrating internal dev teams and vendors with our infrastructure<br />- Understand and collaboratively derive common dev workflows for a variety of security-related technologies<br /><br /><strong>Qualifications:<br /><br /></strong>- Bachelor''s or Master''s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering or related field (or equivalent expertise)<br />- Minimum of 3 years of C/C++ development experience, or related higher level languages. Along with strong Python and/or Perl development experience<br />- Solid understanding of Data Structures, Algorithms, and Object-Oriented design<br />- Strong problem solving skills<br />- Strong (especially written) English communication skills<br />- Experience with High-Performance Unix Programming will be an advantage<br />- Knowledge of open source queuing systems (RabbitMQ) will be an advantage<br /><br />Desired Qualifications:<br /><br />- Prior successful experience as a systems performance or site/systems reliability engineer<br />- Extensive experience working with fault tolerant approaches in a large scale distributed environment and high performance systems<br />- Demonstrated experience working in large, complex systems environments<br />- Deep understanding of internet and networking protocols<br />- A passion for performance excellence, robustness and engineering mindset<br />- MS in Computer Science or related technical field<br />- 6+ years relevant work experience, including experience in a high-volume or critical production service environment<br />- Expertise analyzing and troubleshooting large-scale distributed systems<br />- Knowledge of IP networking, network analysis and performance and application issues using standard tools such as tcpdump<br />- Ability to handle periodic on-call duty as well as out-of-band requests</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/21767347?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3301255351410900225162%2CVSRPtargetId%3A21767347%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 144, 2),
(693, 1411087817, '-', 'Arclyte Technologies', 'Technology', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Quality Assurance Engineer<br />Arclyte Technologies &ndash; Alhambra, CA<br />Arclyte Technologies is looking to add a Quality Assurance Engineer to its growing team. This individual will be responsible in continuing the quality reputation Arclyte has built in the industry for the past 5 years. You will work with the executive VP of Supply Chain to reinforce and create testing standards and procedures as well as execute on the actual testing. Attention to detail and an eye for quality is critical, along with the ability to communicate effectively to internal team and external customers on results. In your role as a Quality Assurance Engineer, you will be the subject matter expert having great impact on Arclyte''s products and supply chain.</p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities<br />*Perform inspections and set quality assurance testing models for finished and semi-finished products<br />*Utilize standard engineering concepts, practices and procedures in electrical/mechanical engineering<br />*Communicate test results both verbally and written to manufacturers in Asia via email, phone, and/or QQ<br />*Assist Operations during Purchase Order receipt checking all products meet testing/quality standards<br />*Provide detailed evaluation reports to Supply Chain on all suppliers and manufacturers</p>\n<p>Requirements<br />*Fluent in reading, writing, and speaking Mandarin Chinese is a must<br />*Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering or Mechanical Engineering<br />*At minimum 2-3 years of engineering experience is preferred<br />*Very strong written and documentation skills<br />*Knowledge and/or experience in battery technology</p>\n<p>Compensation<br />*Annual Salary Range: $45,000 - $55,000<br />*Medical Insurance: 100% company covered policy<br />*401k: Eligible after 1 year of employment<br />*Paid Vacation, Holiday, and Sick Days</p>\n<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Arclyte-Technologies/jobs/QA-Engineer-f326a18c2af409a4', '', 980, 106, 2),
(694, 1411176583, 'Executive Assistant ', 'Global Law Group', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Our Pasadena office has an immediate need to hire a Bilingual (Mandarin) Executive Assistant. This person report directly to the President and provides executive support in a one-on-one working relationship. The Executive Assistant serves as a primary point of contact for internal and external constituencies on all matters pertaining to the Office of the President. Responsibilities include but not limited to completes a broad variety of administrative tasks for the President including: managing and maintain all the schedules, plan and make travel arrangements, arrange and coordinate meetings and events, liaise with internal staff at all levels, interact with external corporate and personal contacts, assorted personal assistance tasks as requested by the President and coordinate project-based work as needed.</p>\n<p>Qualification:<br />- Bilingual in Chinese (Mandarin) is required.<br />- Proficient in Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word , Excel and Power Point).<br />- Strong organizational skills that reflect ability to perform and prioritize multiple tasks seamlessly with excellent attention to detail.<br />- Demonstrated proactive approaches to problem-solving with strong decision-making capability.<br />- Emotional maturity.<br />- Highly resourceful team-player, with the ability to also be extremely effective independently<br />- Bachelor''s degree required.<br />- 3 to 5 years of experience supporting C-Level executives.</p>\n<p>Compensations:<br />- We offer competitive salary and would vary depending on work experience.<br />- Medical insurance<br />- Dental insurance<br />- Vision Insurance<br />- 401K with company matching<br />- Vacation time off<br />- Sick time off<br />- Personal time off<br />- FSA<br />- Paid holidays</p>\n<p>Please email your resume with desired salary for immediate consideration.</p>\n<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Global-Law-Group/jobs/Bilingual-Executive-Assistant-bd19cfd8df752095', '', 980, 174, 2),
