(699, 1411339638, '()', 'Metropolitan Jewish Health System', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Overview:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>Our groundbreaking hospice and palliative care programs offer a significant difference when dealing with a life-limiting condition. We offer a broad range of services in the community or facility-based to help patients and their families ease the burden of managing a life-limiting illness or end of life care. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We truly value our staff and further acknowledge their contributions by offering:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Employee and family health coverage</li>\n<li>Competitive salaries</li>\n<li>Employer contributed pension plan</li>\n<li>Generous time off</li>\n<li>Tuition reimbursement</li>\n<li>403(b) retirement plan</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>The Spiritual Care Coordinator is responsible for coordinating and providing direct pastoral support services to patients and families. &nbsp;The Coordinator also coordinates additional spiritual support with religious affiliations as requested by patients and families. In addition, the Spiritual Care Coordinator completes and prepares documentation from clinical contacts and patients, inputs clinical data into MISYS database and maintains updated intake reports.</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>We are seeking a candidate who is bilingual Chinese speaking (Cantonese and Mandarin) and possesses a Bachelor''s degree from an accredited college (Divinity Degree required) and a minimum of one year experience post graduate in a healthcare setting. &nbsp;Also, he or she needs to be proficient with the Microsoft Word and Microsoft Excel software applications. &nbsp;The candidate must have the ability to work within an interdisciplinary team environment and have excellent communication, listening and organizational skills. Strong teaching and public speaking abilities are a must for the role, as well as the ability to input clinical data proficiently. &nbsp;A valid NYS driver''s license is preferred. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_Navigation">&nbsp;</div>', 'https://careers-mjhs.icims.com/jobs/2886/spiritual-care-coordinator-part-time/job?mode=job&iis=Indeed.com&iisn=Indeed.com&mobile=false&width=950&height=500&bga=true&needsRedirect=false', '', 980, 122, 2),
(700, 1411441910, '', 'At Comfort Keepers ', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">JOB DESCRIPTION</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<div id="jobdescri"><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobDescriptionFR"><strong>At Comfort Keepers</strong>&nbsp;nothing is more important than helping seniors live full, independent, and dignified lives within the comfort of their own homes.&nbsp;<strong>Comfort Keepers&nbsp;</strong>is dedicated to providing in-home elder care that enriches our clients'' lives and helps them maintain the highest possible level of independent living.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />Comfort Keepers is seeking highly dependable and reliable Companion/Caregivers who love to work with the elderly population. We are currently looking for candidates who are willing to serve the Brooklyn area.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />The Companion/Caregiver provides non-medical, in-home support and home management services to clients. He or she provides companionship to those individuals requiring socialization and minimum guidance for a safe, protected, clean, and orderly environment.<br /><br />The ideal candidate for this position has a high school diploma or GED and has at least two years of experience in this or a similar job, can work a flexible schedule that includes weekends and holidays, and is fluent in English and Chinese (speaking and writing).&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;We prefer, but is not required, that the candidate&nbsp;&nbsp;has reliable transportation, a valid driver''s license, a clean driving record, and current automobile insurance. In addition, he or she is genuinely concerned about helping people and has high moral standards of honesty and integrity. Empathy and the ability to listen, good time management skills, and professional dress, speech, and behavior are all required for this position.</span></div>\n<div class="clear height50">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">RESPONSIBILITIES</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_0" class="spaceleft20">Provides general attention to client&rsquo;s non-medical needs following an established Plan of Care</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_1" class="spaceleft20">Helps with activities of daily living by providing approved personal care activities, including bathing, dressing, toileting, grooming, oral hygiene, and/or ambulation as specified in the Plan of Care</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_2" class="spaceleft20">Provides companionship for the client, including talking and listening to, reading aloud, and providing social and emotional support</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_3" class="spaceleft20">Promotes the client&rsquo;s mental alertness through involvement in activities of interest</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_4" class="spaceleft20">Provides emotional support and promotes a sense of well-being</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_5" class="spaceleft20">Provides a clean, safe, and healthy environment for clients and family members by performing light housekeeping tasks including laundering of client&rsquo;s garments and linens and changing the bed</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_6" class="spaceleft20">May prepare and serve meals as directed and ensures that dishes are washed and kitchen is clean after each meal</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_7" class="spaceleft20">Helps client complete necessary phone calls, letter writing, etc., and accompanies client on walks, community trips, doctor&rsquo;s office, bank, beauty salons, etc.</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_8" class="spaceleft20">Reminds client to take self-administered medications</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_9" class="spaceleft20">Observes and reports any changes in the client&rsquo;s mental, physical, or emotional condition or home situation to the appropriate supervisor</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_10" class="spaceleft20">Establishes and maintains effective communication and a professional relationship with clients, family members, and co-workers</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_11" class="spaceleft20">Participates in in-service and continuing education programs, staff meetings, and client conferences as requested by his or her immediate supervisor</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_12" class="spaceleft20">Uses equipment and supplies safely and properly</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_13" class="spaceleft20">Maintains confidentiality regarding client information</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptResponsibility_lblResponsibilityName_14" class="spaceleft20">Performs other related duties as assigned</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class="clear height50">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">QUALIFICATIONS</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_0" class="spaceleft20">Must be at least 21 years old</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_1" class="spaceleft20">High school diploma or GED preferred</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_2" class="spaceleft20">Two years relevant experience required</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_3" class="spaceleft20">Bilingual English/Chinese (speaking and writing)</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_4" class="spaceleft20">Successful completion of the Comfort Keepers training and orientation program</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_5" class="spaceleft20">Able to follow verbal and written instructions and document services provided</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_6" class="spaceleft20">Able to function independently in the home setting with minimal direct supervision</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_7" class="spaceleft20">Able to fulfill assignments with reliability and punctuality</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_8" class="spaceleft20">Able to maintain satisfactory relationships with clients, family, and team members</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_9" class="spaceleft20">Neat, clean, and professional appearance</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_10" class="spaceleft20">Able to stand, sit, walk, reach, kneel, crouch, and lift up to 25 pounds</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_11" class="spaceleft20">Unrestricted driver''s license and clean driving record</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_12" class="spaceleft20">Reliable transportation and valid automobile insurance</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptRequirement_lblRequirementName_13" class="spaceleft20">Able to work days, evenings, weekends, and holidays</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class="clear height50">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class="tdHeader left">BENEFITS</span></div>\n<div class="hrspacetop">&nbsp;</div>\n<hr />\n<div class="hrspacebottom">&nbsp;</div>\n<ul>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_0" class="spaceleft20">Holiday Pay</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_1" class="spaceleft20">Vacation Pay</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_2" class="spaceleft20">Retirement Plan</span></li>\n<li><span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_rptBenefit_lblBenefitName_3" class="spaceleft20">Disability Insurance</span></li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'https://comfortkeepers459.hyrell.com/UI/Views/Applicant/VirtualStepPositionDetails.aspx?TemplateId=114030&IsAutoRefresh=True&r=Indeed&tzi=Pacific%20Standard%20Time', '', 980, 165, 2),
