(702, 1411442582, '', 'Yoyo Chinese Inc ', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>We are an online Chinese language education company that uses video lessons to teach to students from all over the world. As a start-up, we have seen great success so far, but want a marketing manager who has the skills and vision to take the company further.</p>\n<p>This will be an exciting full-time position. You''ll not only design and execute creative marketing plans, you''ll also get to see, first-hand, how your hard work directly impacts the growth of a company with a strong product. As marketing manager, you''ll work closely with the company founder Yangyang Cheng and leading junior marketing staff to develop and execute concrete marketing strategies that will mold and shape the direction of this company.</p>\n<p>We''re looking for candidates who have an entrepreneurial spirit, who are comfortable working in a dynamic startup environment and enjoy the challenge of wearing different hats.</p>\n<p>We believe marketing is both a science and an art. If you''re someone who can achieve that beautiful balance of being analytical and creative, strategic and hands-on, thinking big and detail-oriented at the same time, we''ll be eager to meet you!</p>\n<p>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<p>*Plan and execute weekly/monthly/quarterly marketing strategies with clearly defined goals.<br />*Coach, mentor, train and supervise daily activities of the marketing team.<br />*Review and improve the company''s existing sales funnel (autoresponder emails, website copies, existing social media channel)<br />*Develop social media and sharing strategies that drive new users and membership from social media platforms (company Blog, Youtube, Facebook, Linkedin, Twitter)<br />*Supervise the publication of content through various social media channels<br />*Design, execute and track ads campaigns.<br />*Identify partnerships and opportunities that will help grow our audience<br />*Prepare Google analytics and sales report and adjust strategies based on the report<br />*Plan and execute in-house PR plans (HARO, contact media) and/or work with external PR firms to manage the execution of PR plans.<br />*Plan and execute new revenue streams for the company<br />*Advise Yangyang, the company president, on various issues including budgeting, hiring, PR, company direction and strategy etc.</p>\n<p>REQUIREMENTS</p>\n<p>*Native English speaker<br />*Knowledge of the Chinese language is a big plus<br />*3-5 years previous online marketing experience<br />*Organized and detail-oriented<br />*Persuasive writing skills (understanding of marketing psychology)<br />*Results-driven, proven track record of meeting targets<br />*Non-conventional, creative and can think outside the box<br />*Respectful and outstanding leadership skills that motivate staff</p>\n<p>SKILLS</p>\n<p>*Familiar with analytics tools, A/B testing, SEO, online marketing automation platforms<br />*Familiar with email systems (mailchimp, constantcontact, etc)<br />*Familiar with CRM systems to track and analyze data.<br />*Hands-on knowledge of affiliate marketing<br />*Experience with basic design software (photoshop, inDesign, balsamiq mockup software), HTML/CSS and web design is a plus.<br />*Experience with editing videos and audio is a plus<br />*Experience with the language-education industry or any industry that focuses on delivering results to customers (e.g. fitness industry) is a plus</p>\n<p>We are growing fast and we are good to our people. If you''re interested, please apply for the position by filling out the following form AND sending an email with your name, cover letter and resume. Be creative and no cookie-cutter letters please! We''ll contact you shortly. Thank you and have a wonderful day!</p>\n<p>https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/YOYO_Marketing_Manager</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Yoyo-Chinese-Inc/jobs/Online-Marketing-Manager-c5749bd6a85a90b2', '', 980, 173, 2),
(704, 1411595120, 'CFT', 'Panda Restaurant Group', 'Resturant', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1617.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title=""><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1660.row1" class="text" title="">Panda Restaurant Group</span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p>At Panda, we all share a common mission: "Deliver exceptional Asian dining experiences by building an organization where people are inspired to better their lives." We invest in our people because great people run great operations that will exceed our guests'' expectations. Talk to any of our associates and you will experience a culture dedicated to its mission and our five fundamental values- Proactive, Respect/Win-Win, Growth, Great Operations, and Giving.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group includes the original Panda Inn fine dining restaurants, Panda Express, our Gourmet Chinese food concept served in a fast casual environment, and Hibachi San, our Japanese grill concept. The family owned and operated company is still run by founders Andrew and Peggy Cherng.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda offers competitive benefits and rewarding opportunities, from entry-level positions to management. We have restaurant positions available nationwide and support center positions in Rosemead, CA. Come join the nation''s largest and fastest growing Asian restaurant company.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Property Coordinator assists with repair and maintenance of plaza properties and performs lease administration work related to billing, accounts payable, and accounts receivable.&nbsp; This position coordinates with vendors and tenants on maintenance and repair and helps resolve property repair and maintenance issues.&nbsp;&nbsp; The Property Coordinator also reviews recurring charges in the property management system (Yardi) for all tenants to ensure charges are accurate and makes billing changes and corrections as needed.&nbsp; This position tracks, reviews, and codes property invoices (e.g., property tax, utility, repair and maintenance invoices) and ensures payment is processed on a timely basis.&nbsp; This position interacts with tenants to ensure repair and maintenance issues are resolved and amounts due to tenants related to the terms of the lease agreement are paid accurately and on a timely basis.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create and maintain lease/tenant files into property management database software (Yardi Voyager)</li>\n<li>Prepare Rent Commencement Letters for new tenants</li>\n<li>Perform yearly CAM Reconciliation and handle any disputations</li>\n<li>Track, review and approve all monthly invoices (utility, vendor services invoices, etc.) and provide assistance in processing repair &amp; maintenance and other invoices to make sure payment is processed on time</li>\n<li>Assist in sending/mailing out Water Charge Back and other tenant receivables</li>\n<li>Assist in posting tenant receivables into Yardi tenant ledger</li>\n<li>Work closely with Accounting Team on all tenant related billing/payment issues</li>\n<li>Coordinate with vendors, contractors, tenants to resolve all repair &amp; maintenance issues</li>\n<li>Search for onsite property manager candidates for new properties</li>\n<li>Create and file vendor agreements</li>\n<li>Arrange turnover trip for respective regions</li>\n<li>New Property Set Up</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class="staticcontentlinepanel">&nbsp;</div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1685.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1701.row1" class="inlinepanel" title=""><span class="subtitle">Qualifications</span></div>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a related field required</li>\n<li>Minimum one to two years of relevant experience required</li>\n<li>Successful completion of annual store training</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group&rsquo;s culture is strongly guided by our Mission and Values, highlighted on the Panda websites. We recommend all interested candidates become familiar with our Mission and Values, as well as the principles of The Seven Habits of Highly Effective People, by Stephen Covey.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Panda Restaurant Group, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span class="blockpanel"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></div>\n<div id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1749.row1" class="contentlinepanel" title="">\n<h2 class="no-change-header-inline"><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1765.row1" class="subtitle" title="">Primary Location</span></h2>\n<span class="inline">&nbsp;</span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1786.row1" class="subtitle" title="">|</span><span class="inline">&nbsp;</span><span id="requisitionDescriptionInterface.ID1796.row1" class="text" title="">United States of America-CALIFORNIA-Rosemead</span></div>', 'https://pandarg.taleo.net/careersection/panda+corporate/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=14000843&src=JB-10061', '', 980, 117, 2),
