(720, 1412396377, '', '', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Part Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Seeking for a part time job? Here is a great opportunity! WholeRen Education is a fast growing and fun multinational education company in United States. We are seeking candidates for our part time Market Investigators at colleges and universities in California! Come help us spread and share our passion for education, and help more and more students achieve their dreams!</p>\n<p>Job Requirements &amp; Responsibilities<br />- Enthusiastic, energetic, friendly and responsible<br />- Good interpersonal communication skills preferred<br />- Proactive, highly self-motivated, task driven with sense of responsibility<br />- Distribute questionnaire and hand out advertising materials<br />- Collect effective questionnaire<br />- Approximately 20-30 hours per week<br />- Understand Chinese Preferred</p>\n<p>Please send application email with the subject line "Part Time Market Investigator".</p>\n<p>Job Category<br />Marketing</p>\n<p>Primary Location<br />USA-California, Los Angeles</p>\n<p>Job Type<br />Part time</p>\n<p>Regular/Temporary<br />Temporary</p>\n<p>Apply Before<br />Oct 10, 2014</p>\n<p>Paid / Unpaid<br />Hourly + bonus commission</p>\n<p>Posting Statement: WholeRen Education prohibits discrimination based on race, color, religion, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation or any other legally protected status.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/WholeRen-Education-/jobs/Part-Time-0701689afa20b734', '', 980, 144, 2),
(721, 1412467571, '', 'Sunrider International ', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Internal Auditor/Accounting/Finance</p>\n<p>Exciting opportunity for aggressive professional to travel worldwide, expose different cultures and advance to management position. The opening is located in our beautiful Headquarters in Torrance, CA.</p>\n<p>Company Information</p>\n<p>Sunrider International is an herbal and beauty product manufacturer and distributor with 30 years of history. We continue to grow, and have over 40 offices and 10 manufacturing facilities worldwide. We recently stepped into the hotel business and have purchased 3 hotels in Beijing and Taipei.</p>\n<p>As an auditor, you will travel to our affiliates all over the world (4 to 6 times per year), in addition to:<br />Conduct financial, operational and compliance audits of various operations and functions.<br />Be responsible for the execution of fieldwork; determine whether operating units are performing their accounting and control activities in accordance with policies, procedures and company objectives, and present recommendations to management for correcting deficiencies.</p>\n<p>We view our auditors as management trainees, and offer great opportunity for future growth.</p>\n<p>Qualifications<br />Bachelor degree in Finance/Accounting or related field<br />CPA, CIA, or CISA preferred<br />Audit experience preferred, but not required<br />Hotel audit or management experience preferred<br />Self-started with strong interpersonal, technical, and organizational skills<br />Good verbal and written communication skills.<br />4-6 times international travel per year.<br />Must be US citizen or green card holder.<br />Bilingual in Mandarin strongly preferred.<br />Hotel experience and/or Bi-lingual English/Chinese, a big plus.</p>\n<p>We offer a competitive salary, excellent benefits (including a great 401k plan), and an on-site fitness center. Please email resume, including salary requirements</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Sunrider-International/jobs/Internal-Auditor-ab4ded19d37f0209', '', 980, 120, 2),
(722, 1412467734, '', 'Momoko International Inc.', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Bilingual English and Chinese Office Operation Assistant<br />Momoko International Inc. &ndash; South El Monte, CA<br />Position Summary: This Office Operation Assistant will report directly to the office manager. This person will work on daily assignments to input and update all information on our eCommerce website as well as answer customer&rsquo;s inquiries. Excellent communication skills and a possitive attitude with customers is required.</p>\n<p>Primary Responsibilities:<br />1) Compose description, how to use, ingredients and pictures for new products. Both English and Chinese information shall be composed.<br />2) Update the quantity of products online once deliveries from our vendors arrive.<br />3) Answer customers&rsquo; inquries through phone, email and online chat.<br />4) Take care of walk-in customers.<br />5) Assist warehouse operation if needed.<br />6) Other duties, as assigned<br />7) fluent level of English and Chinese<br />8) knowledge of Japanese is a plus</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Momoko-International-Inc./jobs/Bilingual-English-Chinese-Office-Operation-Assistant-f441e10579796acc', '', 980, 163, 2),
(723, 1412467914, 'YouTube Video Inventory', 'ICONMA', 'Technology', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h4 class="des-job">Description:</h4>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="navlistforjob">\n<p>Duration: 1 year</p>\n<p>Description: Video Inventory Analyst (Client Advertising Policy/Video Inventory Analytics) - MTV</p>\n<p>As a Client Video Inventory Classification Product Specialist you are responsible for ensuring the quality of Client&rsquo;s monetizable video inventory that is at the core of generating revenue from a broad range of new Client advertising products and content partner programs. Candidates are an independent, critical thinker with sound judgment who has a passion for Internet policy and a penchant for defining precise and scalable standards, especially in areas that are still evolving. Candidate will develop detailed knowledge of our constantly evolving technologies and product offerings, and ensure that feedback flows to the product team to fuel improvement and innovation. Candidate will assist with the implementation and enforcement of Client''s advertising and program policies through video classification. As a product expert in Client&rsquo;s Video Inventory Analytics, Candidate will work closely with Policy, Product Managers and Engineering Leads in Client Ads and also serve as the central point of contact for other departments and vendors. You will also be responsible for creating user-facing documentation and content to educate internal users and vendors about our product.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:<br />Watch Client videos and become an expert in Client&rsquo;s Video Inventory classification systems.<br />Analyze data effectively to support the development of strategy and recommendations to video classification initiatives.<br />Actively drive tactical improvements for classification operations, including enhancements to tools and processes that increase quality and efficiency.<br />Work with cross functional stakeholders to ensure readiness for launch.<br />Directly interact with users and user feedback to understand their needs and champion these needs across internal stakeholders.</p>\n<p>Requirements:<br />BA/BS degree preferred with strong academic record.<br />2 years of experience preferred in support operations and/or technology product management.<br />Self-starter with ability to work independently and on multiple initiatives at the same time; excellent project manager.<br />Proficiency in the Chinese Language (Mandarin). Candidates who speak both Mandarin and Cantonese are desirable, but Mandarin is a requirement. No other dialects will be considered.</p>\n<p>Preferred experience:<br />Ability to design and deliver scalable support offerings for different channels.<br />Technical experience in machine-learning methodology a plus (e.g., solid understanding of product development flow, ability to translate technical concepts into non-technical terms).<br />Knowledge of Client&nbsp; content and publisher policies a plus.<br />Excellent communication skills (written and verbal).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h4 class="des-job">About Company:</h4>\n<p>ICONMA is a nationwide consulting firm with corporate headquarters in Troy, MI, providing Professional Staffing and Project Based Services and Solutions for Fortune 1000 clients in a broad range of industries. Core Industries served include: Biotech/Pharmaceutical, Cable, Clinical, Consumer Services, Energy, Engineering, Financial Services, Food &amp; Beverage, Government/Defense, Healthcare, Insurance, Logistics, Manufacturing, Media, Mortgage, Oil &amp; Gas, Pharmaceutical, Retail, Scientific, Services, Technology, Telecommunications, Transportation, and Utilities.</p>\n<p>ICONMA is a certified Woman-Owned &ldquo;Woman-Owned Business Enterprise&rdquo;, certified by Women&rsquo;s Business Enterprise National Council (WBENC) and National Women Business Owners Corporation (NWBOC).</p>\n<p>The company was founded on the principle that success is derived from delivering high quality service and resources in the most responsive, flexible, and innovative way. ICONMA invests in people and resources with a single goal: To provide our customers with the highest quality service in the most responsive manner.</p>\n<p>We measure success by the results of our customers. As a business partner, we know that world-class service and cost effective solutions are the primary keys to success. ICONMA uses technical expertise and business knowledge to help customers achieve these objectives.</p>', 'http://www.iconma.com/jobs_by_category_description.php?jid=1147&search=none', '', 980, 119, 2),
