(744, 1413598467, '', 'Fanstang', 'Entertainment', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>MUST SPEAK CHINESE!</p>\n<p>Are you an entertainment junkie?<br />Are you into video editing<br />Now, you can work on what you&rsquo;re addicted to and get paid!!</p>\n<p>Our company is looking for a video editor who&rsquo;s super passionate about entertainment and show production, and also have video editing experiences. You will work as a video editor to our various entertainment reality show. If you&rsquo;re very insightful on video editing and programming, you&rsquo;ve find the right place to shine!</p>\n<p>The ideal candidate must be LA local, super addicted to video production and sports/entertainment. MUST SPEAK CHINESE</p>\n<p>RESPONSIBILITIES:<br />- Video editing<br />- Research videos/pictures<br />- Assist in other realms of production</p>\n<p>SKILLS<br />- MUST SPEAK CHINESE<br />- Knowledge on Chinese pop culture<br />- Adobe Premiere Pro, Photoshop, After Effect will be a PLUS<br />- Microsoft, IOS, GOOGLE</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Fanstang/jobs/Video-Editor-70f5f9e1368b71e3', '', 980, 144, 2),
(745, 1413599034, '', 'Nan Hai Co Inc', 'Art', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>NanHai Art is currently looking for a full time Gallery Associate.</p>\n<p>Founded in San Francisco in 1986, NanHai Art is currently located in Millbrae, California, providing an easy access for the Greater San Francisco and Silicon Valley audience. NanHai Art focuses on introducing major artworks by contemporary Chinese artists that reflect the unique aesthetics of Chinese art while transcending cultural and artistic boundaries with a contemporary sensibility. With a thoughtful selection of artists and a particular emphasis on academic discourse, NanHai Art is committed to present the highest level of Chinese contemporary art to a global audience.</p>\n<p>Please visit NanHai Art website www.nanhaiart.com before applying for this position.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities<br />-Receive, document, and manage the storage, conservation, and preservation of all artworks moving in and out of the gallery&rsquo;s inventory<br />-Manage the records of gallery artists&rsquo; works, sales, exhibitions, and press<br />-Assist the Director in coordinating gallery artists&rsquo; exhibitions, duties include but not limited to obtaining artwork information and curatorial texts, working with designer and printer to publish exhibition catalogues and brochures, arranging exhibition logistics including the shipment and installation of artworks, planning and managing related programs<br />-Coordinate the application, planning, and logistics for selected air fairs<br />-Manage gallery publicity including updating gallery website, editing and sending<br />e-Newsletters, monitoring and updating the gallery&rsquo;s social media outlets, working with PR contractor for publicity campaigns</p>\n<p>Qualifications:<br />-Passion for Chinese art<br />-Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in art, art history, art management, graphic design, advertising, public relations, communications, and related fields<br />-Strong communication skills and teamwork<br />-Fluent in both English and Mandarin<br />-Work experience in art management preferred<br />-Familiar with ArtSystems and Constant Contact preferred</p>\n<p>Eligible candidates will be contacted for interview. No phone calls or walk-ins please.</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Nan-Hai-Co-Inc./jobs/Gallery-Associate-ae4d54d0255962b8', '', 980, 197, 2),
(746, 1413693207, 'SALES & MARKETING COORDINATOR&', 'Dai Cheong Trading Company, Inc', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>BI-LINGUAL SALES &amp; MARKETING COORDINATOR (English + Chinese/Vietnamese)</p>\n<p>Company: Dai Cheong Trading Inc.<br />Industry: Food Importing &amp; Distribution<br />Location: Los Angeles, CA (warehouse district) 90031<br />Career Level: Entry Level Sales &amp; Marketing</p>\n<p>Dai Cheong Trading Inc. is rapidly expanding its distribution nationwide. We are seeking a bi-lingual coordinator help grow the business. This person must be comfortable working in both Chinese and in English (ideally also in Vietnamese -the more Asian languages, the better!).</p>\n<p>ROLES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Receive and process orders</li>\n<li>Manage and grow existing accounts (retail stores and online)</li>\n<li>Coordinator with overseas suppliers</li>\n<li>Coordinate and attend trade shows and street fairs</li>\n<li>Create sales and progress reports</li>\n<li>Forecast inventory</li>\n<li>Respond to email inquiries</li>\n<li>Other administrative projects as needed</li>\n</ul>\n<p>QUALIFICATIONS:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Education: College level graduate</li>\n<li>Languages: MUST be at least bi-lingual (English, Cantonese, Mandarin, Vietnamese)</li>\n<li>Computer: Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, Powerpoint., and Photoshop</li>\n<li>Communication: Excellent verbal and written/email communication required.</li>\n<li>Must be comfortable working in an Asian culture environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>BENEFITS:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive Base Salary (Entry Level DOE)</li>\n<li>Health &amp; Medical Benefits</li>\n<li>Paid vacation, holidays and sick days</li>\n<li>Casual Family Culture</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ABOUT THE COMPANY:<br />Asian (Ethnic) part of the business: http://daicheonginc.com/<br />American (Mainstream) part of the business: http://dcdistributions.com/</p>\n<p>Established in 1979, Dai Cheong Trading Company is a three-generation family business headquartered in the heart of Los Angeles''s warehouse district. The founder, Mr. Wong Shui Cheong, had one simple vision - to create an import and distribution company that would share quality Asian food products with the US market. The company has been an active member in the Asian Trade Food Association since its inception, leading discussions around the opportunities and challenges faced by the oriental food trade industry.</p>\n<p>Today, Dai Cheong Trading has four warehouses and a team that together speak over eight different languages. The company''s international distribution network spans across the country. The company''s inventory of 2,000+ items has been carefully selected from exclusive brands to bring consumers the highest quality and best tasting foods. As Dai Cheong Trading continues to expand, the teams seek new talent and welcome you to join us in this prosperous journey.</p>\n<p>INTERESTED?<br />Email customerservice@ dcdistributions.com with your resume and your availability for a pre-screening phone interview. Cover letter preferred but not required.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Dai-Cheong-Trading-Company,-Inc./jobs/Sales-Marketing-Coordinator-9231f9b035720de0', '', 980, 132, 2),
