(778, 1414717432, '', 'Ivy Bridge Group', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Job Description: We are currently seeking an experienced and polished bilingual and bi-cultural (simplified Chinese and English) project manager, who will provide administrative support to executive and ensure the successful operation of an education project.</p>\n<p>Salary: DOE</p>\n<p>Project Manager who will be responsible for planning and reporting on all phases of the project life cycle, including: compliance with work orders and contracts, chain of custody and materials tracking, financial and time-based projections and forecasts, billing and volume metrics, and reporting on project-level information. The Project Manager is the primary communications channel to the client and works closely with operations and account management.</p>\n<p>Specific duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Oversee projects from initial set-up to delivery of the finished product, with a focus on client relations and communication.</li>\n<li>Work closely with executive to set up projects, job turnaround estimates, and job specifications.</li>\n<li>Continuously monitor multiple tasks and jobs within each department to ensure deadlines are met.</li>\n<li>Work closely with staff to ensure proper allocation of resources based on deadlines and priorities.</li>\n<li>serves as a liaison between Account Management, staff, and the client during the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Communicates frequently with executive to resolve issues and provide status updates according to the client''s needs. Manage executive&rsquo;s expectations throughout the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Ensure jobs are completed according to executive, industry standards, and that job specifications and deadlines are adhered to.</li>\n<li>Maintain accurate and current records of all aspects of a project relating to job tracking, specifications, and chain of custody related documents.</li>\n<li>Interact with clients to develop strong client relations.</li>\n<li>Provides final quality control check on client deliverables.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Background and Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; Master&rsquo;s degree preferred but not necessary.</li>\n<li>Native &ndash;level grasp of English and Mandarin Chinese, in regards to speaking, reading, professional writing and translating.</li>\n<li>Working exposure to the education industry highly preferred but not necessary</li>\n<li>Knowledge and sensitivity to both western and Chinese culture nuance</li>\n<li>Prior administrative and project &ndash;management experience highly preferred.</li>\n<li>Exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail</li>\n<li>High proficiency in Microsoft word and excel, along with all applicable PC and Mac software.</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n<li>Candidates must have legal authorization to work in the US</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For immediate consideration, please send your resume and salary requirements to this posting.</p>\n<p>About Ivy Bridge Group, please visit www.ivybridgegroup.com.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Ivy-Bridge-Group/jobs/Project-Manager-Bilingual-2639105ef49b5b3b', '', 980, 107, 2),
(779, 1414718322, 'Customer Service -Mobile', 'Netherfire', 'Entertainment', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div align="left">Job Summary</div>\n<div align="left">The customer service agent will manage both the community as well as any incoming tickets sent by the player base. This is a position where you will be working in a team environment. You are responsible for working with the project manager and the producer in the development of the game, as well as post-launch events and updates. You&rsquo;ll also be working with the graphic designer and core artist on the creation of any art assets required for post-launch community events and updates. You&rsquo;ll also work with PR on post-launch PR materials, such as but not limited to social media, forum posts, blogs, written articles, and videos. Finally, you will be working with the project assistant on QA related tasks as well as be involved in any brainstorming sessions related to design, monetization, and live-ops.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div align="left">Responsibilities</div>\n<p>&bull;Establish a presence in the community by keeping the players in the loop with the latest news and updates.<br />&bull;Inquire, gather, and organize player comments and suggestions and report them back to the publishing team.<br />&bull;Handle player tickets through Zendesk and solve them according to an established policy.<br />&bull;Monitor the wiki, forum, and all social media outlets with the PR.<br />&bull;Work with PR on post-launch PR materials, such as but not limited to social media, forum posts, blogs, written articles, and videos.<br />&bull;Work with the in-house artists and graphic designers in creating art assets for community purposes.<br />&bull;Team up with the marketing team to prepare and schedule marketing materials and be part of the UA and monetization process.<br />&bull;Be part of the live-ops / post-launch team in designing post-launch events to drive new game updates and breathe life into the games as they continue to grow and improve.<br />&bull;Attend scrums and be ready to give feedback. Your opinions matter!<br />&bull;Be part of discussions about metrics/product decision-making.<br />&bull;Take part in setting up product roadmaps and strategic planning.<br />&bull;Understand and participate in making a game go live on iOS and Android.<br /><br /></p>\n<div align="left">Qualifications</div>\n<p>&bull;Clear communication in proficient English, both written and verbal a must.<br />&bull;Demonstrate high level of organization.<br />&bull;Ability to multitask.<br />&bull;Be prepare to meet, scrum, and work during night time when the Chinese team is online.<br />&bull;Be willing to crunch before deadlines.<br />&bull;Be ready to QA art portion of the game as the development process progresses.<br /><br /></p>\n<div align="left">Plusses</div>\n<p>&bull;Bilingual in English and Chinese.<br />&bull;Previous experience working with video games.<br />&bull;Prior leadership.<br />&bull;Passion for games.<br />&bull;Familiar with internet culture.<br />&bull;Basic proficiency in Zendesk.<br />&bull;Basic proficiency in web analytics.<br />&bull;Basic proficiency with Adobe CS tools.</p>', '', 'hr@netherfire.com', 980, 115, 2),
