(809, 1415753922, '', 'Sequoia Wealth Planning', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p><strong>Job Description:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Due to the rapid growth of our cross border business between China and the United States, Sequoia Wealth Planning Inc is looking for a highly-motivated Business Development Manager, who is responsible for managing existing accounts and driving new business development efforts to achieve sales and profit goals for our line of business. The Business Development Manager will prospect new clients, meet with new and existing clients, identify needs of the current market and promote our existing products and services.</p>\n<p><strong>Duties and responsibilities:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify and utilize a variety of sources to find business opportunities and generate leads.</li>\n<li>Provide market intelligence to management and contact business representatives of potential clients to identify their needs.</li>\n<li>Participate in and contribute to the finance team''s analysis of investment strategy and positioning for our clients, including manager oversight and selection.</li>\n<li>Building and maintaining long term relationships with clients and finance firm representatives.</li>\n<li>Cold-calling key decision makers to set appointments for your client''s sales team</li>\n<li>Generate opportunities for new long term client relationships, including new business presentations, managing RFPs and other inquiries.</li>\n<li>Perform additional assignments per Director''s and Managements'' direction.</li>\n<li>Regional travel, as necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Skills, experience and qualifications:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fully bilingual in Chinese and English. Cantonese-speaking is preferred.</li>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree in Business Management or other related finance degree is strongly preferred.</li>\n<li>Minimum of 4-5 years of finance field experience, with client service and business development experience.</li>\n<li>Solid written and verbal Chinese and English communication skills.</li>\n<li>Must be able to complete duties without supervision.</li>\n<li>Must be detailed-oriented and organized. Able to take initiative and able to prioritize workload.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to interact and communicate effectively and professionally with all levels of company and client management is essential.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Compensation:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Salary plus commission</p>\n<p>Please send your resume to us if you are interested in applying for this position. Thank you</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Sequoia-Wealth-Planning/jobs/Bilingual-Chinese-English-Business-Development-Executive-783f751d50ab6a31', '', 980, 133, 2),
