(818, 1416367209, '', 'MIKADO Marketing', 'Marketing', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div id="job_header"><strong class="jobtitle"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Cantonese or Mandarin Speaking Market Research Surveyor</span></strong>&nbsp;<br /><span class="company">MIKADO Marketing</span>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<span class="location">Los Angeles, CA</span></div>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p><strong>Company:&nbsp;</strong><br />We are a full service multicultural marketing agency based out of Colorado representing a vast number of clients who target the Chinese consumer in the US. We are looking to extend our network for local grassroots marketing activities within the local Chinese communities. Key areas include: Dallas, Houston, Los Angeles, San Francisco Bay Area, Seattle, Detroit, Chicago, Atlanta, Philadelphia/Pittsburg, D.C-VA- MD Metro, New Jersey and New York, Las Vegas, Miami, Boston, Denver.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Description:&nbsp;</strong><br />As a Market Research Surveyor you would work on a project basis. Projects include but aren&rsquo;t limited to; in person street intercepts (face to face surveys), in-store demos, event staffing and management, focus group coordination &amp; recruitment and other promotional activities as needed. Projects typically are held during the weekends.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be bilingual:</li>\n<li>Fluent in English and Cantonese/Chinese</li>\n<li>Must have basic computer and Internet abilities along with own computer and the ability to use a tablet</li>\n<li>Be outgoing and personable</li>\n<li>Have keen market insight into the local ethnic communities, ethnic associations as well as an understanding of buying and media consumption habits of the targeted ethnicity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Experience Required:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Preferred 1-2 years experience in outside marketing, sales or promotional advertising/marketing</li>\n<li>Some college preferred/ HS Diploma required</li>\n<li>Experience conducting street intercepts is a plus</li>\n<li>Having a network of ethnic contacts is also a plus</li>\n<li>Ability to work in the U.S</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Compensation:&nbsp;</strong>$10 -$13 per survey (based on experience) and $15 per hour for events.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/MIKADO-Marketing/jobs/Cantonese-or-Mandarin-Speaking-Market-Research-Surveyor-e418417afd1f43c4', '', 980, 104, 2),
(819, 1416367720, '', 'Zales', 'Marketing', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', '', '', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Jewelry Consultant - Zales - Livermore Premium Outlets.<br />New Store, Opening 11/2014, Tier 1 Location</p>\n<p>At Zale, selling fine jewelry is our business, so it stands to reason that our store operations employees are the backbone of our business. These important positions are vital to the continuing success of our company. So, if you are enthusiastic about a dynamic working environment that focuses on people and their achievements, you will want to check out the employment opportunities at Zale- where you''ll have the chance to pursue a career, not just a job!</p>\n<p>Jewelry Consultants are responsible for identifying and fulfilling our guests'' jewelry needs, as well as maximizing personal and store performance. Jewelry Consultants learn from the best by undergoing a comprehensive new employee training program that teaches all the facets of selling fine jewelry - from making successful sales presentations, learning features and benefits of various types of merchandise, to building lifetime relationships with guests.</p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fluently speak and understand Chinese (Mandarin / Cantonese).</li>\n<li>Results-oriented, strong communication skills, excellent customer service skills, a consistent work ethic and willingness to learn</li>\n<li>Must be able to multi-task and work in a team-friendly environment</li>\n<li>Prior retail, sales or customer service experience is preferred, but not required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Compensation<br />Full time - $11 to $16 an hour. Large commission possibilities. Full tuition reimbursement*. Full Benefits. 401k. Vacation Pay. Sick Pay. Full job training. DCA Certification*. Employee Discounts.</p>\n<p>Part time - $11 to $15 an hour. 