(835, 1416598314, '', 'Logistics Team', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Part Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>General Summary:</p>\n<p>To provide administrative support and assistance to all departments within the corporation.</p>\n<p>Essential Duties and Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>This role requires extensive cross-group coordination at all levels, along with strong written and oral communication skills as well as a superior approach to customer service and team collaboration. A bright, highly polished, talented and highly motivated professional who has a passion for their work and can add value to the organization through their creative, administrative and operational expertise. Must have the ability to handle highly confidential details as well as think strategically.</p>\n<p>Must possess a very professional and refined image. Advanced technical skills in Microsoft Office Suite and Mac are essential. Experience with graphic design programs and exposure to human resourse or marketing would be a plus.</p>\n<p>RESPONSIBILITIES:<br />Responsibilities for this position includes providing comprehensive administrative support and the ability to establish and maintain a solid relationship with all other managers, to proactively manage time effectively, and the ability to complete complex tasks and projects quickly with little to no guidance, react with appropriate urgency to situations that require a quick turnaround, and take effective action without having to know the total picture. Other key responsibilities include:<br /> Proactively coordinate and engage with Executive Assistants in planning and organizing events, activities and scheduling of calendars.<br /> Compose and types correspondences, memos and creates various charts, tables, graphs and presentation materials. Edits copy for spelling, grammar and layout.<br /> Coordinates meetings, organizes and schedules large and complex activities such as cross-functional events, business travel, conferences and department activities. Develops meeting agendas, tasks and distributes minutes.<br /> Tracking and helping drive completion of key deliverables and following up on outstanding items<br /> Manages domestic and international travel plans<br /> Prepares expense reports and credits card reconciliations<br /> Coordinates communications, schedules and information flow between departments.<br /> Organizes and maintains filing systems.<br /> Responds to phone call and written requests for information. Researches issues and gathers information.<br /> Respond to inquiries made by researching inquiries, interpreting policy and making appropriate decisions based on company policy and issuing directions to employees as needed.<br /> Track external and internal documents requiring management review or signature and follow-up to assure documents are executed in a timely manner.<br /> Handle confidential material related to company policy and development; and disseminate information with appropriate discretion.<br /> Work as liaison between management and staff to achieve maximum company performance and address items as needed.<br /> Providing general office and administrative and human resource support<br /> Providing daily personal and business assistance</p>\n<p>REQUIREMENTS:<br /> Can marshal resources (people, funding, material and support) to get things done; is team oriented and highly collaborative.<br /> Can orchestrate multiple activities at once to accomplish a goal; uses resources effectively and efficiently; arranges information and files it in a useful manner<br /> Pursues everything with energy, drive and a need to finish; seldom give up before finishing; especially in the face of resistance or setbacks<br /> Spends time on what&rsquo;s important; quickly zeros in on the critical few and puts the trivial many aside; can quickly sense what will help or hinder accomplishing a goal; eliminate roadblocks; creates focus<br /> Ability to accommodate working styles and perspective of diverse individuals<br /> Progressive administrative responsibility and leadership experience<br /> Encourages and supports leadership and growth in others<br /> Ability to work independently with minimal supervision and direction<br /> Ability to anticipate what needs to be done and to proactively take action<br /> A &ldquo;can-do&rdquo; attitudes with no excuses<br /> Quality execution and follow through<br /> Highly adaptable and flexible with constant change</p>\n<p>QUALIFICATIONS:<br /> At least 3 years of relevant professional experience in a fast paced environment as an assistant for a Manager or above<br />of a 30-75 person company<br /> Superior communication, organizational, multitasking, project management &amp; problem-solving skills<br /> Very strong technical skills and the ability to quickly learn new software<br /> Proven ability to work in a highly ambiguous environment with high levels of integrity and discretion in handling confidential information and dealing with professionals inside and outside the company<br /> A Bachelor&rsquo;s degree is strongly preferred</p>\n<p>The ideal candidate will be differentiated by a couple of additional attributes:</p>\n<p> Strong Powerpoint, graphic design and or marketing experience<br /> Foreign language skills, in particular in Mandarin Chinese.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=Logistics-Team-%2F-SB-Freight&t=Part+Time+Administrative+Assistant+Bilingual+Chinese&jk=a9d36d7bd064d7fa', '', 980, 177, 2),
