(857, 1416969758, 'Contract Bilingual Interpreters (Chinese: Cantonese and Mandarin) /', 'Carmazzi Global Solutions', 'Language', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Part Time', '<p>DO NOT CALL OR EMAIL US, PLEASE COMPLETE THE APPLICATION USING THE LINK PROVIDED</p>\n<p>Carmazzi Global Solutions is seeking fluent, bilingual interpreters as Independent Contractors for On-Site Interpretation in Los Angeles, California.</p>\n<p>This is an on-call opportunity with flexible hours, and opportunity to develop skill. This is currently not a staff position and may be ideal for potential linguists who currently have a part time job that leaves some availability during normal business hours. Employment opportunities may arise in the future based on client need and individual performance.</p>\n<p>Primary Language Need: CHINESE (CANTONESE), CHINESE (MANDARIN)</p>\n<p>Professional experience as an interpreter is preferred but not required. Ideal experience includes community interpreting in the social service sector. Must be punctual, responsible, and have a reliable means of transportation.</p>\n<p>All interpreters will be required to complete a background check, credit check, and fingerprinting.<br />Salary of around $23 per hour based on experience and language pairs.</p>\n<p>Please use the link below to complete our linguist application so we may proceed in working with you.</p>\n<p>http://carmazzi.com/ssainterpreterapplication</p>\n<p>DO NOT CALL OR EMAIL US, PLEASE COMPLETE THE APPLICATION USING THE LINK PROVIDED</p>\n<p>With a network of more than 5,000 qualified linguists positioned around the world, Carmazzi Global Solutions excels in the full spectrum of language services, including localization, document translation, face-to-face and telephonic interpretation, and all aspects of globalization and multi-lingual marketing. Our mission is to enable worldwide clients to connect cultures&mdash;moving them from language to understanding and propelling them into an international presence with success in the global marketplace.</p>\n<p>Salary: $23.00 /hour</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Carmazzi-Global-Solutions/jobs/Contract-Bilingual-Interpreter-a6e5370e7d22a94c', '', 980, 168, 2),
(858, 1417045393, '', 'Diamond Honda of Puente Hills', 'Service', 'Industry, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'City of Industry', 34.019733, -117.958672, '', 'California', 'City of Industry', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="displayFieldBlock">\n<div class="displayField"><br /><strong>Automotive Service Advisor Fluent in Chinese - Diamond Honda of Puente Hills</strong><br /> - <br /><br />If you believe Customer Service &nbsp;is a true craft -- one built on charisma, communication and thorough product knowledge - we want to talk to you!<br /><br />As a Service Advisor at Diamond Honda of Puente Hills you will be responsible to meet and greet service customers promptly in a professional and courteous manner.<br />Inspect vehicle and refer to service history to accurately identify and verify customer&rsquo;s service needs.<br />Promote the sales of appropriate services, parts, and accessories by thoroughly understanding the product and associated service requirements.&nbsp;<br />Provide accurate cost and time of completion estimates for the services recommended, communicate and get proper authorization from customers.<br />Check on progress of services to vehicles throughout the day and contact customer to communicate and receive approval regarding any changes in the cost-estimate, promised time of delivery or recommended services.<br />Administer new and used vehicle warranty repairs in accordance with manufacturer warranty guidelines.<br />Confirm service appointments by telephone the day before the customer is scheduled to arrive and conduct post-repair follow up.<br />Inspect vehicles prior to each customer delivery to ensure vehicles services and/or repairs are performed correctly and communicate the results with the customer.<br />Meet requirements of the state and federal law for automobile repair and consumer protection.<br />Demonstrates behaviors consistent with the Company&rsquo;s Values in all interactions with customers, co-workers and 