(865, 1417480043, '', 'Warner Bros. Entertainment Group', 'Marketing', 'Burbank, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Burbank', 34.180840, -118.308968, '', 'California', 'Burbank', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" width="92%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" align="center">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Posting &lt;BR&gt;Job Title">Posting&nbsp;<br />Job Title</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Posting &lt;BR&gt;Job Title" class="TEXT">Sales Analyst</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Time Warner &lt;BR&gt; Division">Time Warner&nbsp;<br />Division</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Time Warner &lt;BR&gt; Division" class="TEXT">Warner Bros. Entertainment Group</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="WB Business Unit">WB Business Unit</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="WB Business Unit" class="TEXT">WB Pictures International</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Industry">Industry</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Industry" class="TEXT">Film Production and Distribution</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Area of &lt;BR&gt;Interest">Area of&nbsp;<br />Interest</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Area of &lt;BR&gt;Interest" class="TEXT">Sales and Distribution</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Location">Location</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Location" class="TEXT">United States - California - Burbank</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Requisition #">Requisition #</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Requisition #" class="TEXT">144658BR</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Position &lt;BR&gt;Type">Position&nbsp;<br />Type</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span id="Position &lt;BR&gt;Type" class="TEXT">Full Time</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign="top"><span class="Fieldlabel"><label for="Posting Job Description">Posting Job Description</label></span></td>\n<td class="TGAlignLeft" width="87%"><span class="TEXT"><span class="TEXT"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">SUMMARY OF POSITION</span></strong><br />Warner Bros. Distributing Inc. seeks a Sales Analyst for the WB Pictures International Distribution department.<br /><br /><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">JOB RESPONSIBILITIES</span></strong></span></span>\n<ul dir="ltr">\n<li>SALES / DISTRIBUTION ANALYSIS AND REPORTING:\n<ul>\n<li>Generate and distribute reports to Senior Management relating to strategic planning and distribution issues.</li>\n<li>Prepare comparative film indices based on talent and/or genre.</li>\n<li>Track, review and summarize key box office data (i.e. estimates, prints, sites, screens and admissions) on a by title / by territory basis.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Analyze sales data through various OLAP tools to maximize reporting functionality and efficiencies.</li>\n<li>Prepare comparative film analyses based on talent and/or genre.</li>\n<li>At the request of Senior Management, queries field offices or regional supervisors for comparison information, ensuring all data reflected accurately in sales system (EIS).</li>\n<li>Track and maintain key market statistics on a quarterly and annual basis.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>EMERGING MARKETS / CHINA FOCUS:\n<ul>\n<li>Research Chinese websites for industry trends and data.</li>\n<li>Translation of Chinese business documents into English.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Position will act as a liaison with the Asia Regional office for in-depth analyses on China.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Track and maintain key emerging market statistics and trends on a quarterly and annual basis.</li>\n<li>Additional emerging market analyses, i.e. top ranking reports, screen growth, release trends, etc.</li>\n<li>Provide translation services for senior management meetings as necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<span class="TEXT"><span class="TEXT"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">JOB REQUIREMENTS</span></strong></span></span>\n<ul dir="ltr">\n<li>2+ years work experience in multinational sales or trading organization preferred.</li>\n<li>Intermediate level, working knowledge of Excel and any OLAP analysis tools highly preferred.</li>\n<li>Previous experience working on multiple tasks in a deadline driven, fast paced environment.</li>\n<li>Strong written and oral proficiency in Mandarin required.</li>\n<li>PC Skills: Proficient in all Microsoft applications (must have intermediate knowledge of Excel) and OLAP tools.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Must be detail oriented.</li>\n<li>Must be a team player and have the ability to communicate effectively with persons on all levels.</li>\n<li>Must possess superior analytical skills.</li>\n<li>Must have excellent oral and written skills.</li>\n<li>Must have excellent time management skills to work in a fast-paced, high pressure environment.</li>\n<li>Must be able to manage multiple concurrent tasks.</li>\n<li>Must be able to reason through issues and resolve problems.</li>\n<li>Must be able to maintain strict confidentiality.</li>\n</ul>\n<span id="Posting Job Description" class="TEXT"><br /><br /><strong>The Warner Bros. Entertainment Group of Companies is an equal opportunity employer and considers all candidates for employment regardless of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, citizenship, age, disability, marital status, military or veteran''s status (including protected veterans, as may be required by federal law), sexual orientation or any other category protected by law.</strong></span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'https://careers.timewarner.com/TGWebHost/jobdetails.aspx?partnerid=391&siteid=36&jobId=711227&Codes=NIND', '', 980, 113, 2),
