nd functional specifications of projects.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>b.<br /><br />Help prepare project plan, track status, identify issue resolutions, coordinate with business departments to ensure cross-functional requirements are met and report status to executives.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>C.<br /><br />Official documents and stamp management.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>a.<br /><br />Responsible for the official documents management mechanism and update documentation policy.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>b.<br /><br />Review Head Office official documents and brief management with summary of the content.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>c.<br /><br />Manage the branch&rsquo;s stamp and maintain related documentation&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>d.<br /><br />Responsible for critical file management</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>D.<br /><br />Brand management</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>a.<br /><br />Manage the brand awareness as well as corporate banking business promotion advertisement activities including budget planning, review advertisement proposals and track execution plan and return on investment.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>b.<br /><br />Mitigate reputational risks if any</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>E.<br /><br />Customer complaints handling.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>a.<br /><br />Design the customer complaints handling procedure.<br /><br /></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>b.<br /><br />Manage day-to-day customer complaints resolution.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Skills and Experience</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.<br /><br />Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>B.<br /><br />At least 3 years similar working experience in a Chinese commercial bank</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>C.<br /><br />Bilingual (English and Mandarin), fluent in both written and oral communication skills is required</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>D.<br /><br />Proven working reports writing skills</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>E.<br /><br />Experience at working both independently and in a team-orientated, collaborative environment is essential</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>F.<br /><br />Excellent analytical skills</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>G.<br /><br />Strong communication and people skills</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>H.<br /><br />Ability to influence others</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I.<br /><br />Able to prioritize and multi-task, demonstrates flexibility and acceptability.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>J.<br /><br />Willingness to take initiative</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>K.<br /><br />Sophisticated with Microsoft Office</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This position offers an opportunity for professional growth within the Bank.<br /><br />Successful applicants will be asked to show proof that they can legally work in the U.S.<br /><br />without requiring visa sponsorship.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class="job-header">Start:&nbsp;</span>ASAP</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Rate:&nbsp;</span>US$75000.00 - US$85000 per year</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Location:&nbsp;</span>New York, New York</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Type:&nbsp;</span>Permanent</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Industry:&nbsp;</span>Finance</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Recruiter:&nbsp;</span>ACG Resources</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Tel:&nbsp;</span>646 442 5723</li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Email:&nbsp;</span><a class="count" href="http://careers4a.com/search/jobs/2106981/Financial-Services-Office-Mana.html?utm_source=Indeed&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_campaign=Indeed">to view click here</a></li>\n<li><span class="job-header">Posted:&nbsp;</span>2014-11-25 19:39:00 -</li>\n</ul>', 'http://careers4a.com/search/jobs/2106981/Financial-Services-Office-Mana.html?utm_source=Indeed&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=Indeed', '', 980, 250, 2),
(867, 1417480654, 'Social Service/Outreach, Cantonese/English (Brooklyn) /', 'Edith and Carl Marks Jewish Community House of Bensonhurst', 'Service', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>The Neighborhood Naturally Occurring Retirement Community (NNORC) Program provides social and health care services, activities, and advocacy for older adults at Bensonhurst, Brooklyn community center</p>\n<p>POSITION: Social Services/Outreach Worker, Bilingual Cantonese-English (part-time -- 10 hours/week, 9 am -- 2 pm, 2 days/week)</p>\n<p>DUTIES:<br />Conduct outreach activities, with the goal of increasing program enrollment of 60+ adults. Provide outreach in our community center and in the community with individuals, groups, local businesses, community groups, and health providers.</p>\n<p>Assist social and health services staff with case management, activities, service coordination, and referrals for clients. Provide translation assistance.</p>\n<p>Work with various media. Create, translate, and type program materials in English and Chinese -- flyers, brochures, newsletters, using Microsoft Word, Publisher, web.</p>\n<p>Keep records, prepare reports on activities, assist with data entry, office work, etc. Other duties as assigned.</p>\n<p>QUALIFICATIONS:<br />&bull; BA degree preferred. &bull;Bilingual: Chinese/English. Must speak Cantonese. Other dialects a plus. Write in Chinese.<br />&bull; Good phone, communication, and computer skills. Background in community-based settings or customer service.</p>\n<p>SALARY: Commensurate with experience<br />START DATE: Immediate<br />CONTACT PERSON: Fax Resume: 718-232-8461 Attn: Faye;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:Faye@jchb.org">Faye@jchb.org</a></p>', '', 'Faye@jchb.org', 980, 110, 2),
