t" width="100%">\n<div id="_ctl0_ContentPlaceHolder1_pnlComments">\n<div class="headerNoPad" align="left"><a name="comments"></a>Important Comments</div>\n<div><span id="_ctl0_ContentPlaceHolder1_otherInformation">Academia Avance, a small charter school in Highland Park (Northeast Los Angeles area), seeks dynamic, results-oriented, visionary, and committed teachers to realize Academia Avance''s mission of educational excellence for all students. Academia Avance educates grades 6-12.<br /><br />We are currently looking for a instructor for Middle/High School Mandarin course using the pinyin system. This position is a full time position. Grades 8 and 9<br /><br />Our IDEAL CANDIDATES will have:&nbsp;<br />* experience teaching inner-city youth<br />* experience with English Language Learners<br />* experience working with High School students<br />* experience using differentiated instruction<br /><br /><br />Ability:<br />*Maintain effective classroom management.<br />*Lead students in project-based learning activities.<br /><br />Commitment:&nbsp;<br />*A philosophy of education that is committed to student success<br />*A belief that education encompasses life skills, critical citizenry and social justice&nbsp;<br />*A willingness to participate in creating an effective school culture.&nbsp;<br />*A willingness to coordinate duties and plan with a small group of teachers&nbsp;<br />*A desire to see him/herself as part of a team that will include work beyond subject matter instruction.<br /><br />Teaching Assignment:<br />6 courses (grades 8-9)<br /><br /><br />Compensation:&nbsp;<br />&bull; salary based on experience and credentials<br />&bull; health benefits and CalSTRS (California State Teacher Retirement Systems)<br /><br /><br />115 N. Avenue 53<br />Highland Park, CA 90042<br />Phone: 323-230-7270 Fax: 213-652-0994<br />Email: jobs@academiaavance.org<br />www.academiaavance.org<br /><br />Please do not call the school office to inquire about the position.</span></div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.edjoin.org/viewPosting.aspx?postingID=515709&countyID=19&onlineApp=1&utm_source=Indeed&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=Indeed', 'jobs@academiaavance.org', 980, 163, 2),
(886, 1418008213, '', 'Tiny Scholars Daycare ', 'Language', 'Redondo Beach, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Redondo Beach', 33.849182, -118.388405, '', 'California', 'Redondo Beach', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>WHO WE ARE: We are a family daycare in North Redondo Beach that offers family loving care with activities and the structure of a preschool curriculum for children ages 2-5. Our mission is to provide an individualized learning environment for families that want their children to learn Chinese. We offer an immersion approach in a relaxed atmosphere where the children acquire the language naturally through play and a variety of fun activities. Our philosophy is to offer a curriculum that is presented in a non-pressured manner depending on a child''s academic and emotional readiness. We strive to offer all students age-appropriate opportunities to develop their intellectual and social abilities.</p>\n<p>POSITION AVAILABLE: Part-time teacher''s assistant / tutor M-F 20-30 hrs/wk</p>\n<p>RESPONSIBILITIES &amp; DUTIES:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Supervise children at play while helping resolve conflicts and expressing needs in appropriate ways in accordance to program goals and philosophy.</li>\n<li>Assist the teacher in implementing appropriate lesson plans in accordance with program goals and philosophy.</li>\n<li>Assist the teacher in preparing materials and supplies in advance for activities.</li>\n<li>Assist with keeping classrooms neat and organized.</li>\n<li>Assist children with personal hygiene such as but not limited to: potty training, diaper changing, brushing teeth and washing hands.</li>\n<li>Assist during snacks and meals such as but not limited to: food prep and cleanup.</li>\n<li>Perform other duties as required or assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pass TB test and criminal background check.</li>\n<li>Ability to lift 40 lbs.</li>\n<li>Must love children and have a passion for teaching.</li>\n<li>Must be reliable and able to work a 4 hour minimum shift Monday-Friday.</li>\n<li>Must be able to walk, squat/kneel, sit on floor, see, hear and speak with children to ensure children''s health and safety.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bilingual in English and Chinese Mandarin</li>\n<li>Previous child care or preschool experience desirable.</li>\n<li>Coursework in Early Childhood Education or willingness to enroll in coursework.</li>\n<li>First aid and CPR certified.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>COMPENSATION: $9-12 / hr depending on experience and free tuition for employee''s child</p>\n<p>Please reply to this post with your name, phone number, best time I can reach you and the languages your are fluent in.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Tiny-Scholars-Daycare/jobs/Mandarin-Speaking-Assistant-Teacher-72f6762d0a34dde5', '', 980, 166, 2),
