(945, 1420266824, '', 'Forest Lawn Memorial-Park Association', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>If you are a driven and determined Human Resources professional, passionate about creating a culture of respect and support, we would be delighted to meet you!&nbsp;<br /><br />Forest Lawn Memorial Parks &amp; Mortuaries, a well-established and reputable organization is seeking a Bilingual, Chinese speaking Employee Relations Representative to administer, coordinate, and participate in a wide variety of Human Resources functions including employee relations, training and communications. The ideal candidate must possess an outstanding ability to develop and nurture positive relationships with the management team and employees and to influence business results through HR processes. Must be self-motivated, driven, results oriented, and able to take ownership of established policies and procedures, while creating and implementing creative solutions to increase efficiency and boost employee morale. This position will report to the Human Resources Manager.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Essential Functions:&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;</strong>Provide general information to employees and management regarding Forest Lawn policies, practices, and procedures.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Be an important role in the communication flow within our organization by facilitating meetings with various departments, collecting information regarding their processes and recording their suggestions and concerns in a report format.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Guide employees and management members through a variety of employee relations issues such as performance concerns, discipline, terminations, employee development, employee conflict, grievances, and violations of policies/procedures.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ensures prompt response and resolution of employment-related complaints by conducting or overseeing thorough investigations through collaboration with the Human Resources Manager and Human Resources VP; taking the appropriate next steps to resolve the issues in a fair and equitable manner.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist management in creating disciplinary memorandums, performance reviews and New Employee Progress Reports.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Identify, create and enhance areas of training; such as Sexual Harassment Prevention.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain, monitor and ensure the accurate completion of I-9 documents.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Gather HR Metrics information such as quarterly cost-per-hire analysis, turnover rates and tracking exit interviews and reasons for separations.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Conduct New Employee Orientation.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Stay abreast of Human Resources developments and trends by attending seminars and webinars.<br /><strong>Minimum Qualifications:&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;</strong>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; preferably in Human Resources.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Three years of experience in a Human Resources Generalist or similar role, it is also important that you are eager to learn and continue your professional development.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Proficient in Microsoft Office applications required, including Microsoft Excel &amp; PowerPoint.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to thrive in a team environment.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to receive, follow, and provide instructions in a positive and constructive manner&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to work effectively with all employees and management in a professional, courteous, and understanding manner; maintain confidentiality.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Valid California Driver&rsquo;s License, reliable transportation and ability to travel to our 11 Forest Lawn locations in Southern California&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;<strong>Fluency in Chinese required (Speak, Read and write)&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;</strong>Strong business acumen, effective management, leadership, time management and organizational skills necessary&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge of local, state and federal labor and employment laws&nbsp;<br />&bull; Effective presentation and facilitation skills required&nbsp;<br /><strong>We Offer an Outstanding Compensation and Benefits Package, Which Includes:&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;</strong>Medical and Dental Insurance&nbsp;<br />&bull; Free Life Insurance and Long Term Disability&nbsp;<br />&bull; Voluntary Vision Insurance&nbsp;<br />&bull; Supplemental Life Insurance&nbsp;<br />&bull; Cash Balance Retirement Plan&nbsp;<br />&bull; 401k plan with company match&nbsp;<br />&bull; Paid Vacation&nbsp;<br />&bull; Paid Absence Plan&nbsp;<br />&bull; Tuition Reimbursement Program</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e4f7655abb9f4b16&q=chinese&l=Los+Angeles%2C+CA&tk=19an7ol2d1d4i2j3', '', 980, 210, 2),
