(908, 1418525398, '', 'Ivy Bridge Group', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>Job Description: We are currently seeking an experienced and polished bilingual and bi-cultural (simplified Chinese and English) project manager, who will provide administrative support to executive and ensure the successful operation of an education project.</p>\n<p>Salary: DOE</p>\n<p>Project Manager who will be responsible for planning and reporting on all phases of the project life cycle, including: compliance with work orders and contracts, chain of custody and materials tracking, financial and time-based projections and forecasts, billing and volume metrics, and reporting on project-level information. The Project Manager is the primary communications channel to the client and works closely with operations and account management.</p>\n<p>Specific duties include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Oversee projects from initial set-up to delivery of the finished product, with a focus on client relations and communication.</li>\n<li>Work closely with executive to set up projects, job turnaround estimates, and job specifications.</li>\n<li>Continuously monitor multiple tasks and jobs within each department to ensure deadlines are met.</li>\n<li>Work closely with staff to ensure proper allocation of resources based on deadlines and priorities.</li>\n<li>serves as a liaison between Account Management, staff, and the client during the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Communicates frequently with executive to resolve issues and provide status updates according to the client''s needs. Manage executive&rsquo;s expectations throughout the life of a project.</li>\n<li>Ensure jobs are completed according to executive, industry standards, and that job specifications and deadlines are adhered to.</li>\n<li>Maintain accurate and current records of all aspects of a project relating to job tracking, specifications, and chain of custody related documents.</li>\n<li>Interact with clients to develop strong client relations.</li>\n<li>Provides final quality control check on client deliverables.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Background and Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; Master&rsquo;s degree preferred but not necessary.</li>\n<li>Native &ndash;level grasp of English and Mandarin Chinese, in regards to speaking, reading, professional writing and translating.</li>\n<li>Working exposure to the education industry highly preferred but not necessary</li>\n<li>Knowledge and sensitivity to both western and Chinese culture nuance</li>\n<li>Prior administrative and project &ndash;management experience highly preferred.</li>\n<li>Exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail</li>\n<li>High proficiency in Microsoft word and excel, along with all applicable PC and Mac software.</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n<li>Candidates must have legal authorization to work in the US</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For immediate consideration, please send your resume and salary requirements to this posting.</p>\n<p>About Ivy Bridge Group, please visit www.ivybridgegroup.com.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Ivy-Bridge-Group/jobs/Project-Manager-Bilingual-2639105ef49b5b3b', '', 980, 170, 2),
