(911, 1418606990, '/', 'VoyagerMed', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Are you passionate in Search Engine Optimization? Do you enjoy working in an international environment? Then come and join our team and become part of our further success!</p>\n<p>VoyagerMed is the premier &ldquo;destination healthcare&rdquo; company that enables doctors and patients to access cutting edge medical technology anywhere in the world at an affordable price. As a global healthcare platform, VOYAGERMED brings together internationally accredited hospitals and an experienced customer service team. Whether you are looking for a reasonably priced knee replacement or a plastic surgery performed as soon as possible, VOYAGERMED is where patients and doctors connect.</p>\n<p>Your Tasks:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You will write long and interesting articles about medical treatments</li>\n<li>You will prepare press releases and contact journalists</li>\n<li>You will help to translate and check the quality of our website</li>\n<li>You will do on-page/off-page search engine optimization</li>\n<li>You will regularly contact webmasters over the phone and emails in order to establish business partnerships</li>\n<li>You will analyze the results of the performance</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Your Profile:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You are interested in Online Marketing and highly motivated to learn something new</li>\n<li>You are creative and have excellent writing skills</li>\n<li>You speak English on a native level and a plus is to have good communication skills in Chinese.</li>\n<li>You are open and honest and feel very comfortable communicating over the phone and email</li>\n<li>You enjoy working in a young environment with exciting challenges and tasks</li>\n<li>You have some basic knowledge of Excel</li>\n<li>Knowledge of technical SEO is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our offer</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Join a fun, international and highly-motivated team of outstanding talents in a supportive environment with a high performance culture</li>\n<li>The opportunity to be responsible for and manage your own projects</li>\n<li>Access to a well-established network in New York&rsquo;s start-up scene</li>\n<li>Work directly with decision makers and have an impact in the organization</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Excited by the prospect of joining us? If so, we look forward to receiving your application. Send us an email with your resume and short motivation letter outlining your availability and the type of internship you want to do to.</p>\n<p>Please understand that we cannot accept applications from graduates, or any applications that do not specify the type of internship you are applying for.</p>\n<p>Please include into the subject line &ldquo;SEO Country Manager / China&rdquo;.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us via email. We look forward to hearing from you! For further information you may visit our website at www.VoyagerMed.com.</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/VoyagerMed/jobs/SEO-Country-Manager-e0d12a44e428bc55', '', 980, 140, 2),
(912, 1418607190, '', 'International Business Promotion, Inc. (IBP, Inc.)', 'Marketing', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>Our client is a Japanese company which has a number of offices in the US. It is currently looking for a Chinese bilingual candidate as a sales rep. Please note that this is an entry-level sales job, so they are not looking for a candidate who has a master''s degree and needs a visa sponsorship to work in the US.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in this role, please read the following minimum requirements carefully and send us your latest resume in Microsoft Word.</p>\n<p>Minimum requirements:</p>\n<p>-&nbsp;<strong>At least a few years of sales or customer service experience.</strong>&nbsp;No exception for this particular position.<br />- English: Business level.<br />- Mandarin: Native level.<br />- AA degree preferred.<br />- Authorized to work in the US.<br />-&nbsp;<strong>Valid US driver&rsquo;s license to visit customers on a daily basis.</strong><br />- Computer skills to use Microsoft Office.<br />- Able to work overtime as necessary.<br />- Detail-oriented.<br />- Great communication skills.<br />- Team player.<br />- Able to start immediately.</p>\n<p>Compensation: $13/hr. or $35,000/yr</p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />International Business Promotion, Inc. (IBP, Inc.)<br />1601 Broadway 12th Floor<br />New York, NY 10019 USA</p>\n<p>Website: www.ibp-nyc.com</p>\n<p>International Business Promotion, Inc. (IBP, Inc.) is an international recruiting and marketing company, headquartered at Times Square in New York City. For the recruiting business, we are specializing in the Japanese-English bilingual candidates throughout the US. In addition to the recruiting business, we provide a wide scope of marketing services to help Japanese companies expand their businesses in the US. We also help American companies enter into the Japanese market.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.indeed.com/viewjob?cmp=International-Business-Promotion%2C-Inc.-%28IBP%2C-Inc.%29&t=+Sales+Representative&jk=3f6c3575586c95d4&sjdu=QwrRXKrqZ3CNX5W-O9jEvdotEAWm_RAUUxP012oJXYOnHCKOO8S1etoHtOjYJkFdYAkEcYB5QTB3sMgpr688deoh-ERavz1u3ijdCjWfF8BOAh-EIPo9AslRm-GqrFAlBliGPdNrxfVCxK9wSqY0ZQ&pub=pub-indeed', '', 980, 173, 2),
