(1013, 1422944814, 'Trends Data Journalist', 'google', 'Technology', 'Mountain View, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Mountain View', 37.386051, -122.083855, '', 'California', 'Mountain View', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="description-module container">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="description-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3 class="sub-header">/Mountain ViewCATrends Data Journalist, Google.  3+.  RSQL. .&nbsp;Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">There is so much we can learn about the world through Google Trends. Aggregated data from Google searches can help us spot where the flu might be coming next. YouTube viewership statistics can tell us what today&rsquo;s audiences want from their content; and spiking query volume can tell us when a particular celebrity or company is gaining popularity over time. The possibilities to inform our understanding of the human condition through Google data are almost limitless. And today&rsquo;s storytellers are increasingly making use of Google Trends data to create a new type of journalism, rooted in data analysis, that is giving us new insights into the zeitgeist of our times. We&rsquo;re building an effort to work with data journalists globally to make Google Trends the best source of data insight into today&rsquo;s digital public square.<br /><br />The Trends Data Journalist will be part of a new group of data curators at Google - responsible for using Google Trends and other data to tell unique stories that inspire data journalists around the world to leverage Google Trends in their reporting. You&rsquo;re someone who can spot relevant cultural trends from a sea of data. The insights you produce will shed light on what people are thinking, watching, reading, and talking about on the web. Your goals are two-fold: 1) you will produce data sets and visualizations that everyday journalists can report on and incorporate into their reporting, and 2) you will show data journalists what&rsquo;s possible and inspire them to create their own data-driven stories using Google Trends. We&rsquo;re looking for an expert storyteller who loves data as much as they love pop culture, and can use it to help tell great stories that enrich and inform audiences.<br /><br />Responsibilities<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Create original data-driven insights about the zeitgeist of our times on a daily basis, using news pegs and data signals as your guide</li>\n<li>Generate data-driven story models that can serve as guide and inspiration to journalists and media outlets looking to use Google data in their reporting</li>\n<li>Work closely with reporters to develop high-impact, data-driven stories</li>\n<li>Build process and capacity for creating compelling data visualizations for media</li>\n<li>Work with the Trends Product and Engineering teams to create better features for data journalists</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />Minimum qualifications<br />\n<ul>\n<li>BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />Preferred qualifications<br />\n<ul>\n<li>3 years of experience working directly with data to detect trends and insights, and performing in-depth data analysis and computer-assisted reporting (CAR.). Experience with SQL.</li>\n<li>A good understanding of statistics and statistical analysis; familiarity with the R statistical language and data visualization.</li>\n<li>A background in data journalism and/or data science and analysis</li>\n<li>A newshound mentality: someone who follows the news daily, and has a nose for what&rsquo;s happening now - and why it matters</li>\n<li>A love for creative storytelling.</li>\n<li>Excellent written and oral communications skills and good marketing instincts.</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />Area<br /><br />Know the user. Know the magic. Connect the two. At its core, marketing at Google starts with technology and ends with the user, bringing both together in unconventional ways. Our job is to demonstrate how Google''s products solve the world''s problems--from the everyday to the epic, from the mundane to the monumental. And we approach marketing in a way that only Google can--changing the game, redefining the medium, making the user the priority, and ultimately, letting the technology speak for itself.<br /><br />Marketing &amp; Communications&nbsp;<br /><br />Be the voice of our people and our products.<br /><br />Learn more about our Marketing &amp; Communications teams&nbsp;<br /><br />Mountain View (Global HQ)&nbsp;<br /><br />Want to stop talking about changing the world and actually do it? At Google Mountain View, our global headquarters, we make products for hundreds of millions of users around the world that change the ways they create, share, communicate, collaborate and do business.<br /><br />Learn more about our Mountain View global headquarters</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id="company-module" class="company-module container">\n<h2 class="container-header">About this company</h2>\n<div class="content">\n<div class="rich-text">Google is not a conventional company, and we don''t intend to become one. True, we share attributes with the world''s most successful organizations - a focus on innovation and smart business practices comes to mind - but even as we continue to grow, we''re committed to retaining a small-company feel. At Google, we know that every employee has something important to say, and that every employee is integral to our success. We provide individually-tailored compensation packages that can be comprised of competitive salary, bonus, and equity components, along with the opportunity to earn further financial bonuses and rewards. Googlers thrive in small, focused teams and high-energy environments, believe in the ability of technology to change the world, and are as passionate about their lives as they are about their work.</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/12147891?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3301255351422910626496%2CVSRPtargetId%3A12147891%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 179, 2),
