(1019, 1423550808, 'Investor Relations Manager ', 'Golden Gate Global', 'Finance', 'San Francisco, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'San Francisco', 37.774929, -122.419418, '', 'California', 'San Francisco', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><em>Full-time</em><br /><em>Salary, Incentive Compensation plus Benefits</em></p>\n<p><strong>About Golden Gate Global</strong><br />Golden Gate Global (GGG) channels foreign investment dollars into public and/or private projects in the US that create jobs for the US economy.</p>\n<p>GGG operates via a US federal program that helps to bring in foreign direct investment called the EB-5 Investment Immigration program. The intent of the EB-5 is to encourage the flow of capital into the U.S. economy and to promote employment of U.S. workers. It is estimated that in 2012 over $2 billion of foreign direct investment dollars were raised through the EB-5 program.</p>\n<p>GGG is a dynamic, growing company whose ownership and executive leadership have an unbeatable professional network throughout the State of California, US and overseas. Currently, GGG manages 4 EB-5 funds with over $200 million in EB-5 funds raised, and is expanding its portfolio to finance additional projects in California.</p>\n<p>In 2015, it is expected that GGG will raise approximately $300 million in new EB-5 funds.</p>\n<p>For more info please visit www.3GFund.com</p>\n<p><strong>Position</strong></p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager is a dynamic position that will be one of the company&rsquo;s primary interfaces with China-based referral sources, foreign investors and associated partners. He or she will support referral sources needs, and respond to foreign investor requests and inquiries. He or she must successfully grow and deepen existing relationships with our referral partners. In addition, he or she will also assist with case management of new referral source development, follow up on questions, attend EB-5 related networking events and be able to convert potential referral sources into GGG referral partners.</p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager will also act as the central accounts manager working with the client&rsquo;s professional service providers (immigration attorneys, foreign referral sources, escrow and banking providers) to facilitate successful EB-5 case processing. The Investor Relations Manager will provide a high level of customer service in monitoring and tracking all progress for each investor. He or she will also host visiting investors, and be responsible for managing and maintaining a database of investor data, providing regular reports on fundraising and investor status, and working with the entire GGG team.</p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager will respond to all referral sources and investor inquiries about the company&rsquo;s projects. This will require both strong interpersonal skills as well as a strong grounding in business, real estate, investment and legal terms. He or she will need to have worked with high net worth Chinese clientele. The Investor Relations Manager will also provide administrative support to the company. As part of a young company, all staff team members must be flexible, proactive and willing to support a variety of tasks, challenges and opportunities, as they arise. As most investors are from China, it is mandatory that the Investor Relations Manager speaks, reads, and writes in Chinese fluently.</p>\n<p>The Investor Relations Manager will report to the Senior Investor Relations Manager.</p>\n<p><strong>Duties/responsibilities:&nbsp;</strong><br /><em>Investor Accounts</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Monitor and track all developments for the client</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Maintain accurate records of progress<br />o Submit regular reports on Investor progress and status to CEO and Principals</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage Investor caseloads</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Act as primary lead on assigned client case load<br />o Proactively monitor client&rsquo;s immigration process<br />o Proactively communicate with client&rsquo;s professional service providers (e.g. legal, banking and fund administration partners)<br />o Quality control of investor processing<br />o Receive new leads and convert into active investor<br />o Provide regular reporting to the investors</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinate and host investor tours and site visits</li>\n<li>Manage and support all forms of communication to investors including newsletters, investor reports and statements, notifications, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Develop and Manage Referral Sources</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop referral sources</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Conduct regular market research on EB-5 related events in the US<br />o Convert referral source leads into partners<br />o Support marketing efforts including investor event and EB-5 industry events</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage referral sources</li>\n</ul>\n<p>o Grow and deeper relationships with existing referral sources<br />o Provide regularly referral reports to CEO (e.g. referral agreement and referral performance)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make formal and informal presentations to potential EB-5 investors and partners</li>\n<li>Act as referral concierge service to professional service network in-country and in US</li>\n<li>Travel to China and other countries is possible</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Administrative Support</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Provide administrative support to the company</li>\n<li>Office management support</li>\n<li>Support other company functions as directed and as needs arise</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Skills/Background</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Detail oriented and a demonstration of efficient organizational skills</li>\n<li>4-5 years experience in business, investment and/or real estate investment</li>\n<li>Exemplary written and verbal communication in Chinese</li>\n<li>High degree of customer service experience and orientation</li>\n<li>Understanding of China and Chinese business culture</li>\n<li>Fluency in English</li>\n<li>Proven ability to undertake and complete multiple projects and to work efficiently and diligently under pressure</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to work with high net worth individuals</li>\n<li>Ability to travel in China (including all necessary visa/passport requirements)</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge/experience of MS Office Suite, NetSuite</li>\n<li>Mandarin required; additional Cantonese dialect preferred</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>To Apply</strong></p>\n<p>Please submit the following application materials and information via email:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cover Letter explaining your interest in the position and your professional / educational experience</li>\n<li>Resume</li>\n<li>Contact information for at least two references</li>\n<li>Writing Sample in English and Chinese</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Golden-Gate-Global/jobs/Investor-Relation-Manager-43809a9ca7e753d8', '', 980, 180, 2),
(1020, 1423550916, '', 'un He Law Offices', 'Management', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="snip">\n<p>The New York office of one of the most prestigious Chinese law firms seeks Chinese/English bilingual Office Administrator to handle all aspects of office administration and bookkeeping.</p>\n<p>Qualifications:<br />1. College degree and a minimum of two years of professional experience in office administration required.<br />2. Requires strong interpersonal and communication skills and basic knowledge in bookkeeping.<br />3. Proficient in Microsoft Office - Word, Excel, Outlook, etc., with the ability to edit English and Chinese documents.<br />4. Must be detail-oriented, multi-tasking and organized.<br />5. English/Chinese bilingual proficiency in verbal and written are needed.<br />6. Knowledge of Quickbooks software a plus.</p>\n<p>Competitive salary and benefits and great office environment at Rockefeller Center.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'http://www.indeed.com/cmp/Jun-He-Law-Offices/jobs/Chinese-English-Bilingual-Office-Administrator-8acd0a53e2995a8c', '', 980, 180, 2),
(1021, 1423551074, '/', 'MetLang', 'Finance', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p><strong>Description</strong><br />Metropolitan/Metlang, a nationwide government contractor, is looking to hire linguists fluent in English and Cantonese/Mandarin for current and future staffing needs.&nbsp;<br /><br />Opportunities for individuals with or without a valid security clearance are also available if you are fluent in English and Cantonese/Mandarin.&nbsp;<br /><br />Metlang/Metropolitan is the largest employer in this industry, and we only hire employees and not subcontractors. We take pride in building a relationship with our employees while providing a stable work environment, competitive compensation and a weekly payroll.&nbsp;<br /><br />Whether you are new to our industry or a seasoned expert we encourage you contact us so that we can begin discussing employment opportunities with you. All applications will be handled with complete discretion.&nbsp;<br /><br />Metropolitan/Metlang is an EEO/AA employer. Qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, disability, or veteran status. All qualified applicants will not be discriminated against on the basis of disability.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong><br />The questions you are about to answer are specifically designed to determine your ability to qualify for a government security clearance, a key requirement for many of the positions we offer. Complete and truthful answers to these questions are crucial to your acceptance as a potential candidate. Please bear in mind that a seemingly adverse response to a question may not necessarily be a disqualifying factor, but an untruthful answer would be. Certain government agencies will administer a polygraph exam before allowing any linguist access to their facility. The answers you provide on this questionnaire will be used as a comparison for every security document you complete in conjunction with your security access - up to and including the polygraph exam.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong><br />In order to work as a linguist under these contracts, you must be a native speaker of the foreign language with a college degree and/or some hands on experience with translation and/or interpretation.</p>\n<p><strong>Required Skills</strong><br />An excellent command of the English language, with the ability to provide clear and concise oral and written communication.&nbsp;<br /><br />Ability to work well under pressure to meet specific deadlines.&nbsp;<br /><br />Basic typing/word processing skills of at least 40 words per minute.&nbsp;<br /><br />Exceptions to these qualifications can be made for rare and exotic languages such as African, Latin American and Asian tribal languages. If you feel you that have the qualifications required to work as a linguist in the exciting field of law enforcement, please continue to the next screen, which will ask you some more specific questions.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong><br />Atlanta, New York, Los Angeles, Hawaii</p>\n<p><strong>Type</strong><br />Applicants selected will be subject to a Government security background investigation and must meet eligibility and suitability requirements.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://www.metlang.com/jobs_display.php?jobID=34&loc=NYC', '', 980, 208, 2),
(1022, 1423551188, '', 'DISH Network ', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Summary:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p>DISH is an innovative industry leader distinguished by its pioneering spirit. Ever since our establishment in 1980, we&rsquo;ve been the ideal workplace for people with adventurous spirit and creativity, smart risk takers and aggressive winners - all those for whom the status quo just isn&rsquo;t enough. Our Fortune 200 Company continues to define the curve in television entertainment. We are always improving and extending our products and delivering greater value to people, including our workforce of 20,000 plus. Come explore the big picture with us!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Intelligence. Creativity. Innovation. These are the things you&rsquo;ll find at DISH, the pioneer in television entertainment. We offer flexible career paths for dynamic, talented individuals who are ready to be rewarded and recognized. It&rsquo;s our way of giving back to exceptional people who have kept us at the forefront of our industry.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Specialized Sales and Distribution Channel has been a key contributor to DISH&rsquo; success and has helped propel DISH to the Fortune 200 company that it is today. This Sales Channel is responsible for partnering with authorized DISH retailers and developing go to market strategies that will increase our retailer&rsquo;s production and profitability. &nbsp;</p>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Job Duties and Responsibilities:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Develops and implements international strategic sales plans to accommodate corporate goals.</li>\n<li>Identifies and grows new and existing retailer base within international markets.</li>\n<li>Directs sales forecasting activities and sets performance goals accordingly.</li>\n<li>Reviews market analysis and creates SWOTs to help determine current opportunities and customer needs, price promotions, and discount rates.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Advises retailers, distributors, and sales staff concerning international sales and advertising techniques per specific markets.</li>\n<li>Helps support and represent various retailers and company at local grassroots events, tradeshows, etc. to promote International products and programming.</li>\n<li>Travel throughout specific territory to meet with prospects, current retailers, and Account Managers to discuss international updates and sales training.</li>\n<li>Responsible for international retailer development forums within assigned territory.</li>\n<li>Meets with international programmers, agencies, and advertising mediums to assist in increasing retailer sales opportunities and promotions.</li>\n<li>Prepares periodic sales report showing sales volume, potential sales, and areas of proposed retailer base expansion.</li>\n<li>Monitors and evaluates the activities and products of the competition, and works with corporate International team to track retailer participation with competitors.</li>\n<li>Other duties as required.&nbsp; This list is not meant to be a comprehensive inventory of all duties and responsibilities assigned to this position.</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Skills - Experience and Requirements:</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to effectively respond to and interact with all levels of organizational staff.</li>\n<li>Competencies include excellent presentation/facilitation, organizational, analytical, interpersonal and written/oral communication skills.</li>\n<li>Requires high level computer expertise, including use of internet, database, word processing, spreadsheet, and presentation applications.</li>\n<li>Flexible, innovative and the ability to manage staff, responsibilities and priorities in a fast paced, growth-oriented and time-critical environment.</li>\n<li>Ability to travel 50-75% of the time.</li>\n<li>Must maintain valid driver&rsquo;s license with a satisfactory driving record.</li>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree from four-year college or university; 3+ years related experience, 1-2 years outbound sales experience; or equivalent combination of education and experience.</li>\n<li>Mandarin or Cantonese language ability is required.</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_Navigation">&nbsp;</div>', 'https://dish-assessment1-dish.icims.com/jobs/30551/job?mobile=false&width=1209&height=500&bga=true&needsRedirect=false', '', 980, 133, 2),
(1023, 1423551292, '', 'ELECTRONIC COMPANY', 'Finance', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Full Time', '<p>andidate should be able to install, troubleshoot and program DVRs (analog, IP and hybrid) and alarm systems.</p>\n<p>Candidate must be be personable, have excellent customer service skills, and be able to perform custom wiring and installations on residential and commercial jobs in a timely manner. We are looking for someone enthusiastic and able to work in a team-setting as we operate in a family oriented environment. Candidates will have ample room to grow and opportunity to expand with the company.</p>\n<p>IDEAL CANDIDATE FOR TECH SUPPORT:</p>\n<p>Verifies security system functioning by testing equipment, connections, and signals; identifying and correcting problems.<br />Maintains records by documenting installation.<br />Maintains customer rapport by resolving concerns; answering questions.<br />Maintains safe and secure work environment by following safe practices; keeping security information confidential.<br />Updates job knowledge by participating in educational opportunities; reading technical publications.<br />Accomplishes organization goals by accepting ownership for accomplishing new and different requests; exploring opportunities to add value to job accomplishments.</p>\n<p>SKILLS/QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n<p>Safety Management, Facilities Management Systems, Equipment Maintenance, Functional and Technical Skills,Action Oriented, Electronic Systems Verbal Communication, Dealing with Complexity, Informing Others. MUST BE ABLE TO SPEAK CHINESE AND ENGLISH</p>\n<p>HOURS:<br />Mon-Fri 8:30am to 5:30pm<br />PAY RATE:<br />TECH SUPPORT:<br />$90,000/YEAR<br />SALES POSITION: $100,000/YEAR</p>\n<p>Required Skills and/or Knowledge Self-motivated, competitive spirit, and able to work independently<br />Proven prospecting skills<br />Good organizational 