(1099, 1427083138, '', 'Avenues: The World School', 'Management', 'Los Angeles, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 34.052235, -118.243683, '', 'California', 'Los Angeles', 'None', 'Part Time', '<div class="description-module container">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="description-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">Avenues: The World School is looking for a part-time Mandarin Chinese speaking music teacher in our Lower School division (kindergarten to fourth grade). Avenues runs a language immersion program in the Lower School, and the students receive their music instruction in Mandarin Chinese and Spanish. The part time position is two days per week. The school is flexible as to which two days of the week.<br /><br />Music, theater, dance and movement are an intrinsic part of younger children&rsquo;s day at Avenues. Younger students will participate in an age-appropriate progression of music instruction that includes singing, rhythmic movement, and making music with Orff instruments. As students grow older, music instruction will be a fundamental part of the Lower School curriculum. Students will continue to build on their knowledge and understanding of the components of music in song and on instruments.<br /><br />The music teacher should be creative in the use of age-appropriate technologies, expert in communication with parents of children of these ages and excited to work with young children and their parents. Candidates must have training and teaching experience in Dalcroze, Kod&aacute;ly and Orff-Schulwerk approaches. Keyboard skill is strongly preferable.<br /><br />Candidates should have at least three years of music instruction and ideally exposure to immersion education. Collaboration and valuing the importance of inter-disciplinary work are important qualities of our teachers. Candidates should also possess a B.A. or B.S. and commensurate teaching experience of children of these ages. Fluency in Mandarin Chinese and English or Spanish and English is required.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id="company-module" class="company-module container">\n<h2 class="container-header">About this company</h2>\n<div class="content">\n<div class="rich-text">Avenues: The World School, once all campuses are developed across the globe, will be a highly-integrated &ldquo;learning community,&rdquo; connected and supported by a common vision, a shared curriculum, collective professional development of its faculty, the wonders of modern technology and a highly-talented headquarters team located in New York City. The flagship campus in New York City opened on&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/52626898?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3319945561427082775998%2CVSRPtargetId%3A52626898%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 130, 2),
