(1134, 1428200608, 'Quantitative Researcher', 'FB', 'Technology', 'Menlo Park, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Menlo Park', 37.452961, -122.181725, '', 'California', 'Menlo Park', 'None', 'Internship', '<p>/Menlo Park CAFBQuantitative Researcher    CS SQL, R, Python&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 class="sub-header"></h3>\n<div class="rich-text">Facebook was built to help people connect and share, and over the last decade our tools have played a critical part in changing how people around the world communicate with one another. With over a billion people using the service and more than fifty offices around the globe, a career at Facebook offers countless ways to make an impact in a fast growing organization.<br /><br />Facebook was built to help people connect and share, and over the last decade has played a critical part in changing how people around the world communicate with one another. With over a billion people using the service and more than sixty offices around the globe, a career at Facebook offers countless ways to make an impact in a fast growing organization.The Facebook platform offers advertisers unprecedented opportunities to reach and engage consumers. The Marketing Science Research &amp; Development team is responsible for understanding how to measure the impact of paid media. In service of this goal, the team designs systems and methodologies to measure impact on and off of Facebook, and conducts research on our advertising platform. We are looking for an intern to help develop new methodologies and conduct groundbreaking research. The research conducted by the Marketing Science team is instrumental in informing Facebook&rsquo;s advertising product strategy, and in the development of measurement platforms used across the advertising industry.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop and improve methods for measuring the causal impact of Facebook &amp; Instagram advertising</li>\n<li>Establish measurement approaches to assess relative performance of advertising strategies within Facebook and across marketing channels</li>\n<li>Assess potential opportunities and execute world-class research</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong>&nbsp;<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Pursuing an advanced degree (Ph.D. preferred but not required) in economics, political science, sociology, statistics, computer science or a related quantitative field</li>\n<li>Strong background in applied statistics and causal inference</li>\n<li>Research experience with very large data sets and experiments</li>\n<li>Fluency in the languages of data manipulation (e.g., SQL) and statistical analysis (R or Python), with ability to code (e.g., PHP, shell, Java) a plus</li>\n<li>Ability to communicate complex analysis and results to any audience</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />As part of our dedication to the diversity of our workforce, Facebook is committed to Equal Employment Opportunity without regard for race, ethnicity, gender, protected veteran status, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or religion.</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/26933593?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3301255351427830650691%2CVSRPtargetId%3A26933593%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 126, 1),
