(1157, 1428976151, 'Java (Angular / BootStrap)', 'Java', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="description-module container">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="description-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Our client, a Major Entertainment Company with a huge International Digital &amp; Broadcast presence is seeking a Java Developer to join their team interacting daily with their team in China. MUST SPEAK FLUENT MANDARIN CHINESE, NO EXCEPTIONS.<br /><br />Major Responsibilities:<br /><br />. Perform analysis and program design, develop, test and support China digital properties<br />. Backend Java ecosystem development<br />. Front-end AngularJS/Bootstrap web development<br />. Mobile and custom apps development<br />. Provides after hours support as needed for production systems<br /><br />Required Skills/Knowledge:<br /><br />. 4+ years of experience in Java and Web development<br />. Java Technologies: Java/J2EE, Spring 3.x, Spring MVC or Struts 2.x, Hibernate ORM 3.x, JSP/JSTL<br />. Web Technologies: AngularJS, AJAX/JSON/JQuery/JavaScript, XML, HTML, Bootstrap, CSS<br />. Servers: Apache Tomcat, WebLogic, Apache, Linux<br />. Database Technologies: MySQL, MSSQL, Sybase<br />. Tools: Eclipse, Android Studio, ANT, Maven, CVS, GIT, JIRA<br />. Cloud based IaaS/SaaS Technologies (Amazon EC2, Rackspace)<br />. Experience developing high volume web-based applications<br />. Fluency in Mandarin Chinese<br />. BS/MS in Computer Science or related field<br />. MUST BE AUTHORIZED TO WORK IN THE UNITED STATES<br />. CANNOT PROVIDE SPONSORSHIP AT THIS TIME</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id="company-module" class="company-module container">\n<h2 class="container-header">About this company</h2>\n<div id="follow-company-container"><a class="follow-button start-following" href="https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/actions/followCompany/30903?csrfToken=ajax%3A7365993087860628060" data-trk="job_view_company_follow">Follow company</a></div>\n<div class="content">\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Project One provides information technology consulting and staffing services to assist clients with special assignments and critical deadlines. Our recruitment and account management programs are industry and application specific to meet the unique needs of clients and career-minded professionals.<br /><br />Project One has strong emphasis within the Communications, Digital Media &amp; Entertainment Industry, including: broadcast &amp; cable television, telecom &amp; communications, sports media &amp; entertainment, online interactive media, content publishing &amp; digital advertising.<br /><br />Our President &amp; CEO, Gary Zander has been named by Staffing Industry Analysts (SIA) to the Top Staffing 100 in North America - "game-changers" who''ve made a difference in the world of work. Gary and Project One have proven that niche-market specialization and high-touch/high-value services remain a very viable business approach for both clients and candidates vs. a low-cost focus.<br /><br />In the Data Science &amp; Analytics area we supply professionals with deep statistical &ldquo;big data&rdquo; analytics and predictive modeling experience. These are individuals who can help companies move from traditional BI historical reporting to inferential advanced analytics and predicting future outcomes. The result: companies that compete on metrics achieve competitive advantage, increase revenues &amp; profits and optimize performance.<br /><br />We promote our services through unique marketing programs comprising of management advisory services, seminars, symposiums and executive round tables.&nbsp;<br /><br />Project1 focus is helping clients maximize their productivity and investment return in people, projects and technology. Visit us at project1 .com</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/44249693?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3319945561428976064315%2CVSRPtargetId%3A44249693%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 65, 1),
(1158, 1428976283, ' (Bilingual in Chinese)', 'New York Life Insurance Company', 'Finance', 'Pasadena, CA, United States', 'United States', 'California', 'Pasadena', 34.147785, -118.144516, '', 'California', 'Pasadena', 'None', 'Full Time', '<div class="description-module container">\n<div class="content">\n<div class="description-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Job description</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p><strong>New York Life Culture:</strong></p>\n<p>How a company feels is important to consider as you search for career opportunities. You&rsquo;ll be spending a lot of time at your new company&mdash;you want it to be a good fit. And New York Life feels different than other companies. We&rsquo;re passionate about serving our customers. We collaborate. We give back. We deliver our best, but never at the expense of our values. If those things are important to you, then consider New York Life.</p>\n<p>Working as a financial professional for New York Life offers men and women the opportunity to provide vital insurance protection and financial guidance to the people in their communities, while also enjoying flexibility, independence, a generous benefits package and significant earnings potential.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>About New York Life:</strong></p>\n<p>New York Life Insurance Company, a Fortune 100 company founded in 1845, is the largest mutual life insurance company in the United States* and one of the largest life insurers in the world. New York Life has the highest possible financial strength ratings currently awarded to any life insurer from all four of the major credit rating agencies: A.M. Best (A++), Fitch (AAA), Moody&rsquo;s Investors Service (Aaa), Standard &amp; Poor&rsquo;s (AA+).**</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Duties:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop and execute strategic plans</li>\n<li>Schedule appointments and meet with client</li>\n<li>Provide financial analysis on clients'' portfolio</li>\n<li>Present recommendations to help clients meet their financial goals</li>\n<li>Provide ongoing customer service and support to existing clients</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>First year average income of new representatives is approximately $80,000&nbsp;</li>\n<li>2013 average income for top 5 Managing Partners is approximately $2,508,400</li>\n<li>Health/Dental/Life/Disability</li>\n<li>401(k) plan and Pension Plan</li>\n<li>Continuing education reimbursement</li>\n<li>Reimbursement for industry designations</li>\n<li>Discounts from major wireless carriers</li>\n<li>Local discounts (based on location) for gym memberships</li>\n<li>Training - NYLIC University: One of the most comprehensive and well-respected training programs in the industry</li>\n<li>Career Advancement - After two years as a successful agent, additional opportunities that may be available include: sales development manager, product consultant, and Home Office opportunities in recruiting, marketing or training</li>\n<li>Constant Support - During and after formal training, you will receive continuous assistance from your manager and peers in your region and across the country to help you succeed</li>\n<li>On-site trainers and product consultants are available to you and this is coupled with an entire division within the company located in the Home Office dedicated to providing agents with prospecting and sales ideas, product knowledge and application</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>New York Life Recognitions:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ranks #88 on the Fortune 500 list for 2014</li>\n<li>Fortune Magazine&rsquo;s List of World&rsquo;s Most Admired Companies for 2014</li>\n<li>New York Life was named to&nbsp;<em>Training</em>&nbsp;magazine&rsquo;s &ldquo;Training Top 125&rdquo; ranking for 2014, a ranking of a company&rsquo;s excellence in employer sponsored training and development programs.</li>\n<li>New York Life has been named a &ldquo;Best Company for Multicultural Women&rdquo; by&nbsp;<em>Working Mother</em>magazine.</li>\n<li>New York Life was named to&nbsp;<em>Professional Women&rsquo;s Magazine&rsquo;s</em>&nbsp;&ldquo;Best of the Best&rdquo; list for 2014.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>**Source: Individual Third Party Ratings Report as of 2/3/2014.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="skills-section">\n<h3 class="sub-header">Desired Skills and Experience</h3>\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p><strong>Nice to Have:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Outgoing personality with the ability to develop relationships (i.e., &ldquo;People Person")</li>\n<li>Strong presentation skills</li>\n<li>Highly self-motivated and self-disciplined</li>\n<li>Organized with excellent time-management skills</li>\n<li>Positive attitude</li>\n<li>Quick learner</li>\n<li>Good communicator</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id="company-module" class="company-module container">\n<h2 class="container-header">About this company</h2>\n<div id="follow-company-container"><a class="follow-button start-following" href="https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/actions/followCompany/3432?csrfToken=ajax%3A7365993087860628060" data-trk="job_view_company_follow">Follow company</a></div>\n<div class="content">\n<div class="rich-text">\n<p>Since 1845, New York Life Insurance Company has worked with its customers to protect what&rsquo;s most important to them. Today, with our subsidiaries, we insure lives, help provide retirement income, and develop investment strategies. Every business decision we make is in the best interests of our customers.&nbsp;<br /><br />We are a Fortune 100 company, one of the largest life insurers in the world, and a market leader in the U.S. New York Life has the highest possible financial strength ratings currently awarded to any life insurer from all four of the major credit rating agencies: A.M. Best (A++), Fitch (AAA), Moody&rsquo;s Investors Service (Aaa), Standard &amp; Poor&rsquo;s (AA+).**&nbsp;<br /><br />Please visit New York Life''s Web site at www.newyorklife.com/careers for more information. Also read our disclaimers, here: www.newyorklife.com/socialmedia&nbsp;<br /><br />*Based on revenue as reported by &ldquo;Fortune 500 ranked within Industries, Insurance: Life, Health (Mutual),&rdquo; Fortune magazine, May 21, 2012. See http://www.money.cnn.com/magazines/fortune/fortune500/2012/faq/ for methodology.&nbsp;<br /><br />** Source: Third Party Ratings Reports as of 1/25/12.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs2/view/35905923?trk=vsrp_jobs_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A3319945561428976160995%2CVSRPtargetId%3A35905923%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary', '', 980, 99, 1),
(1159, 1428976389, '', 'Brandwatch', 'Technology', 'New York, NY, United States', 'United States', 'New York', 'New York', 40.712784, -74.005943, '', 'New York', 'New York', 'None', 'Full Time', '<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>Brandwatch is a fast growing, international social media monitoring and analysis company (<a href="http://www.brandwatch.com/">www.brandwatch.com</a>) We''re currently looking for a Data Analyst to join the team; If you think you have the right skills please get in contact now to find out more about this exciting opportunity.<br /><br /><strong>If you:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Like using data to tell stories</li>\n<li>Consider problem solving a personal mission</li>\n<li>Enjoy challenges and testing limits</li>\n<li>Are a team player, but can also fly solo</li>\n<li>Love helping people</li>\n<li>See not having the answers as an opportunity to learn new things</li>\n<li>Are comfortable leading meetings</li>\n<li>Can make dificult technical conversations digestible</li>\n<li>Noticed the typo in the bullet point above (yup, we mean SERIOUS attention to detail</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Your responsibilities would include:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Developing and building social media measurement solutions</li>\n<li>Consulting with clients on research methodologies for social data</li>\n<li>Crafting insights gained from social media data analysis</li>\n<li>Pushing the boundaries of social data analytics methodologies</li>\n<li>Leading client and prospect meetings as a subject-matter expert</li>\n<li>Providing feedback to product development and marketing</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One or more years of relevant experience: quantitative media research, market research, consulting clients on using social data, analysis on large datasets</li>\n<li>Bachelor''s degree in quantitative fields such as Economics, Physics, Math, Statistics, Chemistry, Biology or Neuroscience, Linguistic Sciences, Computer Sciences or Engineer